nd notices that they cannot scroll to the left to get to the last level. They must scroll all the way through all the levels to get to the last level.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe level select screen must loop the levels so that users can easily access the woods ball courses. User must be able to scroll to the left while on the first level to get to the last level.','jhh\ntesting\n','[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/18/2008 02:43:32 AM]\nVerified open on the 10/17 build. Issue occurs with the same steps.\n\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/24/2008 01:53:28 AM]\nVerified in the 10/22 buildtest\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(2619,1222128000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer - The user\'s character twists too far at the torso when viewed by other users in gameplay.','Summary:\nWithin multiplayer gameplay, when the user looks to the left or the right with the character, the other users observe the character\'s torso twisting too far before the legs turn with the rest of the body.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User1 creates a default multiplayer match\n2) User2 joins the match\n3) Gameplay begins\n4) User1 navigates the character in front of User2\'s character\n5) User1 turns the character to the right or left as far as they can before the legs of the character move\n6) User2 observes that User1\'s character twists at the torso at an extreme angle\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user\'s character must not twist at an extreme angle when viewed by other user\'s within multiplayer gameplay.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(2630,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1221868800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic: Multiplayer - Gold Mine Field, user observes LOD popping when navigating their character closer then further away from the large building with Tippmann banners.','Summary: During gameplay of an Xbox LIVE multiplayer 