der side-banners missing graphical textures around the perimeter.\n\nExpected Results:\nEnvironmental objects must have graphical textures.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(2696,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,9,2,5,1221868800,0,0,0,2,'(80%-89%)','Frequently (80%-89%) - Collision Detection - Train Depot Field: User is able to Dive into the wood stacks and become stuck inside','Summary:\nFrequently (80%-89%), during Gameplay, at Train Depot Field, the user is able to Dive into the wood stacks and become stuck inside.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 Creates a match at Train Depot Field,\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s game,\n3) Proceeds to Gameplay,\n4) Gameplay begins,\n5) Navigates to a stack of wood,\n6) Runs towards the end cap of the wood,\n7) Presses A button to Dive just before reaching the wood stack,\n8) Observes diving into the wood stack and becoming stuck inside.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll objects must have proper collision.\n\nNOTE(1): Also occurs in PS3.\nNOTE(2): Screenshots attached.','jhh\n','[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/24/2008 01:58:55 AM]\nVerified in the 10/22 buildtest\n',''),(2699,1222128000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1221696000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay: Sliding into obstacles does not stop the Player','Summary:\nIn gameplay, sliding into obstacles or barriers does not cause the Player to stop, and will slide around them.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay,\n2) The Player proceeds towards a bunker.\n3) The Player presses the RB and A buttons to slide into the bunker.\n4) The Player slides into the bunker and is pushed around it while still in the slide animation.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must not slide around bunkers or obstacles','jhh\n','test\n',''),(2701,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,5,5,1221696000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Comment - Gameplay: Sliding is innacurately implemented','Summary:\nIn gameplay, sliding is innacurately implemented.\n\nExpected Results:\nSliding should be implemented as follows:\nThe Player should be allowed control of the duration and length of the slide, as to not get stuck sliding when the Player does not want to. This could be done by utilizing a hold and release button combo.','jhh\n','[George Batog (AMP Production) -- 09/23/2008 01:20:25 PM]\nWe need to have an explanation as to how you can control the length of your slide.\n\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/06/2008 01:49:12 AM]\nThe length could be just like the sprint meter. you have a default slide length and then you could just push the slide button again to cut the slide short. Or hold to slide and if/when you choose to cut the slide short, release the button. Again, using a slide meter.\n\nJust a thought.\n\n[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/20/2008 08:55:40 AM]\nAs of the 10/17/08 Build, the User is able to slightly slow down their slide; however, it is not as accurate as it could be by using button holds as opposed to button presses.\n\nIdeally, the slide should last for as long as the User holds down the A Button. The on screen prompt would be changed to \"Hold [A button graphic] to Slide\". The slide would trigger when the A button is pressed, and would continue until the User\'s Character runs out of momentum, or when the User releases the A button.test\n',''),(2729,1222128000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1221868800,0,0,0,2,'(80%-89%)','Frequently - Gameplay: The aiming reticule when leaning does not indicate where the shots will hit','Summary:\nThe aiming reticule when leaning does not indicate where the shots will hit\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, any level, single player.\n2) The Player holds the Left Bumper (Sprint) down to sprint.\n3) The Player pulls and holds the Left Trigger (Lean) while sprinting.\n4) The Player presses the Right Bumper (Fire) or pulls the Right Trigger (Fire).\n5) The Player releases the Left Bumper.\n6) The Player fires while leaning, and the reticule does not indicate where the shots will hit.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe aiming reticule must always indicate the location the shots will hit.\n\nNotes:\n1) This goes away after running again, without holding down the Left Trigger.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(2850,1222387200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1221696000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay: The Player is able to push other characters when going prone','Summary:\nIn gameplay, when the Player goes prone next to another character, that character is pushed out of the way.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay,\n2) The Player proceeds to any NPC.\n3) The Player presses B (prone) button, and that NPC is pushed away.\n\nExpected Results:\nCharacters must not be pushed away when the Player is only in the prone position.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(2915,1222300800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1221696000,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Gameplay: The Player was reloading and was shot','Summary:\nIn gameplay Career mode Orlando Cup Pro Circuit, the Player crashed while reloading the marker and getting shot.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Orlando Cup Pro Circuit,\n2) The Player was reloading and was shot by the opposing team and the game crashed with a fatal error.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash when multiple actions occur.\n\nNotes:\n1) Crash Dump is available on the FTP.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(2939,1223078400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,4,3,1,1222041600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Dynasty Training Drills - Dodging and Snapping Stage 1: The opponents spawn in front of the user\'s view','Summary: \nDuring Dynasty Training Drills, in Dodging and Snapping Stage 1, the opponents spawn in front of the user\'s view\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter Dynasty Training Drills, in Dodging and Snapping Stage 1\n2) Twist and hold the Wii Remote to the right or left until the user\'s character performs a lean\n3) Shoot and eliminate the opponents that appear behind the \"DYNASTY\" bunkers\n4) Observe that new opponents appear in front of the user\'s view when spawning behind the \"DYNASTY\" bunkers \n\nExpected Results:\nOpponent\'s must not spawn in front of the user\'s view','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/02/2008 06:34:29 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/01/08 Wii build.\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/04/2008 09:59:40 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/03/08 Wii build.test\n',''),(2983,1222387200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1221696000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Gameplay: The Player has no indication as to which Player they are in gameplay','Summary:\nIn gameplay, the Player has no indication as to which Player they are in gameplay\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, any single player mode, with at least one teammate remaining.\n2) The Player is shot and eliminated.\n3) The Player takes control of a teammate, and there is no indication of the teammate\'s name.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe name of the currently controlled teammate must appear.\n\nNotes:\n1) Player\'s can customize their teammates, leading to different strategies based on the skills of the controlled teammate.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3005,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1221868800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Menu System: The Player can only choose to play as one of five different teams','Summary:\nThe Player can only choose to play as one of five different teams\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Exhibition Menu.\n2) The Player highlights the Player Team selection, and only five teams are available.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must be able to select from all available teams.\n\nNotes:\n1) This also occurs in the Team Selection Menu, when creating a new game.','jhh\n','[George Batog (AMP Production) -- 09/26/2008 08:00:00 PM]\nThis bug is valid only for Exhibition mode.\nTournament mode can only be played with one of the 5 made up teams.\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/12/2008 05:12:24 PM]\nI really do not know why this issue is in our ownership. This is a design decision therefore is not a bug. Please not that this is available for ALL platforms so please do not assign again this bug. Thanks\n\n[George Batog (AMP Production) -- 10/12/2008 05:20:34 PM]\nThis was YOUR own design decision. The way we discussed it quite a while back, you shoudl have been able to play all teams (I even sent an email about this at some point). I understand this cannot be fixed now, but please, send it as WNF (which it is) and with the right notes (and tone).\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/18/2008 12:40:04 PM]\nfrom time considerations.\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/20/2008 06:36:19 AM]\nnot enough timetest\n',''),(3029,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,9,4,1,1222300800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Collision Detection - Exhibition - Gold Mine Field: The rock wall outside the fence at the opposing team\'s side does not detect paintball collision.','Summary:\nDuring Exhibition gameplay, Gold Mine Field, when the user\'s character shoots paintballs at the rock wall just outside the fence at the opposing team\'s side, the paintballs pass through, leaving no paint decals.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Select Exhibition from the Main Menu\n2) Press the 2 Button to change to Woodsball\n3) Press the A Button to Continue\n4) Select the Gold Mine Field\n5) Travel the user\'s character to the opposing team\'s side of the field\n6) Shoot paintballs at the rock wall just outside the fence\n7) The paintballs pass through the rock\n\nExpected Results:\nThe rock wall must detect paintball collision and display the appropriate paint decals.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\ntesting\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/02/2008 06:34:29 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/01/08 Wii build.\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/04/2008 09:59:40 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/03/08 Wii build.test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3030,1222732800,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,4,3,1,1222300800,0,0,0,2,'(50%-59%)','Frequently - Video/Graphic - Jacksonville, Florida: At spawn-point, team-mates were facing wrong direction','Summary:\nFrequently, in NPPL Xtreme Paintball Beyond The Paint, when initiating a 2nd preliminary match, the user\'s character\'s teammates were facing the wrong direction.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu user selected Career Mode.\n2) Selected Play Tournament.\n3) Selected Jacksonville, Florida tournament.\n4) Won first game.\n5) Initiated 2nd match.\n6) Upon enter gameplay the user\'s character\'s team-mates were facing the wrong direction.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser\'s character\'s team-mates must be facing down-field towards opponent.\n\nNote():\nVideo-documentation available.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 09/30/2008 01:39:16 AM]\nVerified Open in 09/28/08 Wii build.test\n',''),(3035,1223337600,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,12,2,1,1222300800,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally - Menu/GUI - Team Outfit: User lost left and right menu functionality in the Team Outfit Menu.','Summary:\nOccasionally, when in the Team Outfit Menu, it the user spams the control stick left and right and up and down the user will lose the highlight graphic and the will lose left and right functionality in the Team Outfit Menu until the title has been restarted.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selected the Team Outfit Menu,\n2) Spam the Control Stick while trying to cause the menu to lag,\n4) The user noticed that the circle highlight graphic had disappeared,\n5) The user observed that they had lost all right and left functionality for the Team Outfit Menu until the title was restarted.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must not lose any functionality while using the Team Outfit Menu.\n\nNote(1).\nVideo available on request.\nNote: On 10-6-08 build, the issue occurred once on the Main Menu after backing out from the Career Mode menu','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/03/2008 10:41:41 PM]\ncouldn\'t reproduce it\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/07/2008 04:56:30 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/06/08 Wii build.test\n',''),(3090,1222560000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,3,4,1,1222300800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Breakout Planner: The breakout planner default setting directs a player to a bunker that cannot be 