</li><br>'),(3171,1222646400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1221696000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - Buffalo, New York: Spectators in the bleachers appear with too many of the same character models','Summary:\nIn Buffalo, New York speedball, the spectators in the bleachers appear with too many of the identical character model grouped together.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Buffalo, New York speedball,\n2) The Player proceeds to any of the bleachers.\n3) The same character model appears several times next to eachother.\n\nExpected Results:\nCharacter models must be split up to not appear unrealistic.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3172,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1221696000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - Buffalo, New York: The trees in the background appear with a corrupt texture','Summary:\nIn Buffalo, New York speedball, the trees in the background appear with a corrupt texture.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Buffalo, New York speedball,\n2) The Player proceeds to the center of the field.\n3) The Player looks toward the forested area.\n4) The trees in the background appear with a corrupt texture.\n\nExpected Results:\nTrees must appear properly in gameplay.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\ntesting\n','[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/20/2008 08:45:31 AM]\nVerified on the 10/17/08 Build.test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3174,1223251200,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1221696000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - San Diego, California: The characters do not sit on the stands correctly','Summary:\nIn San Diego, California speedball, the characters sitting on the stands appear incorrectly displaced.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in San Diego, California speedball,\n2) The Player walks to any of the stands.\n3) The characters are not sitting on the stands correctly.\n\nExpected Results:\nCharacters must sit on stands properly.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\ntesting\n','[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/06/2008 04:17:02 PM]\nVerified Open on the 10/4/08 X360 Build.test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3177,1222646400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1221696000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - San Diego, California: The scoreboard appears incorrectly','Summary:\nIn San Diego, California speedball, the scoreboard appears incorrectly with names on it.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in San Diego, California speedball,\n2) The Player views the scoreboard.\n3) The scoreboard appears with names on it, and no scoring numbers.\n\nExpected Results:\nScoreboard must appear correctly with a scoring number system.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3211,1222646400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,2,3,1,1222560000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Scoring - Career Mode (Results) : The Results screen does not correctly add up the team points.','Summary: \nDuring Career Mode, in any NPPL/XPSL tournament, after completing a game in the Preliminary Round of the tournament, the Results screen appears, and the opposing team\'s point total does not include the points received for Remaining Players.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter Career Mode, in any 100pt preliminary gametype matches\n2) Proceed and complete the first preliminary match\n3) User returns to the tournament bracket\n4) Observe that the scoreboard appears incorrect for simulation matches between opponents\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Results screen must accurately add up scores.\n\nNote (1): Opponents do not receive points for Remaining Players.\n\nNote (2): This issue applies to NPPL and XPSL tournaments, as well as any unlicensed tournaments. But it does not apply to Millennium tournaments.\n\nExample: All but 1 player on the opposing team is eliminated, giving them 1 Survivor point. The opposing team eliminated 3 players from the user character\'s team, giving them 15 Elimination points. The final score for the opposing team displays as 15, which does not take into account the Survivor score.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(3225,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,1,1222560000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: Orange/white 4ft Pop can bunkers appears entirely white','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, If the user places a 4ft Pop can bunker on any map and changes the color scheme to Orange/white, the 4ft Pop can bunker appears entirely white. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu user selects Field Creator.\n2) Loads any map.\n3) Places an 4ft Pop can bunker on the map.\n4) Changes color scheme to Orange/White.\n5) Saves map and loads into gameplay.\n6) Observe that the 4ft Pop can bunker appears entirely white in gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen Orange/Black color scheme is applied to the 4ft Pop can bunker the 4ft Pop can bunker must have both orange and white colors applied to it.\n\nNote(1):\nScreen-shot attached.\n\nNote(2):\nIssue occurs with other color pallets as well.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\ntesting\n','[Jason Lembcke (AMP QA Manager) -- 10/01/2008 09:35:39 AM]\nIf a selected color scheme is not applying to the bunker, then this should be fixed.\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/03/2008 03:54:07 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/02/08 Wii build.\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/04/2008 09:59:40 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/03/08 Wii build.test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3259,1223337600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,10,4,1,1222560000,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally - Audio/Sound - Dynasty Training Drills: When returning to the Dynasty Training Drills screen, the audio for Accuracy plays twice','Summary: \nOccasionally, during Dynasty Training Drills, if the user enters a stage, exits from the stage and returns to the Dynasty Training Drills screen, the audio for Accuracy is heard playing twice\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Entered into any Dynasty Training Drills stage\n2) Proceed into gameplay\n3) Exited gameplay to return back to the Dynasty Training Drills screen\n4) Occasionally, observed that the audio for the Accuracy is heard playing twice\n\nExpected Results:\nAudios must play properly throughout gameplay\n\nNOTES(1): Video is available','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\ntesting\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/02/2008 06:38:48 AM]\nClose - Fixed with 10/01/08 Wii build.\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/06/2008 05:20:57 PM]\ncannot reproduce it\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/07/2008 04:56:30 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/06/08 Wii build.test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3417,1225238400,0,1225238400,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,4,1222732800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: Host encounters moderate framerate drop during gameplay.','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer, the Host encounters moderate framerate drop during gameplay. Frame rate drops to 15 FPS when 14 clients have headsets and are communicating with each other.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Host creates a Player or Ranked match\n2) 13 Clients join the Host\'s game\n3) Host starts the game\n4) Gameplay appears\n5) During gameplay, the Host encounters moderate framerate drop during gameplay. Host also encounters ~15 FPS when voice communication is present.\n\nExpected Results:\nHost must not encounter framerate drops.','jhh\r\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/26/2008 11:13:39 PM]\r\nThese issue has been improved. Please feedback\r\n\r\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/27/2008 03:12:50 PM]\r\nThis issue still occurs in the 10.26.08 build. In general, the more bandwidth that is being sent, the worse the lag will be. In example, 14 players all moving and shooting will cause the host to have moderate lag, 10+ players talking over head sets will cause lag for the host as well.\r\n\r\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 04:19:02 AM]\r\nVerified in the 10/28 buildtest\r\n',''),(3574,1222905600,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,3,1,1222819200,0,0,0,2,'(50%-59%)','Frequently - Gameplay - Dynasty Training Drills - Fitness Stage 2: The user is directed to dive into a bunker that has already been completed.','Summary: Frequently, during Dynasty Training Drills, Fitness Stage 2, when the user\'s character performed a dive into a snake bunker and then immediately moved on to perform a dive into the next bunker (before the opposing player finished firing), the bunker in which the user\'s character was performing a dive into would very quickly recognize the dive and switch the indicator arrow graphic to the next bunker, and if the user\'s character performed a dive anywhere on the field thereafter, the indicator graphic switched back to the bunker that the user had previously completed a dive next to.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu select Dynasty Training Drills\n2) Select Fitness\n3) Select Stage 2\n4) Move the user\'s character towards the first bunker while sprinting by holding the B Button\n5) Press the A Button to perform a dive behind the bunker\n6) Immediately after performing the dive press the - Button to put the user\'s character into a standing position\n7) Move and hold the B Button to again sprint towards the next bunker\n8) Press the A Button to dive behind the bunker\n9) As the user pressed the A Button the arrow graphic instantly changed to the next bunker\n10) The user performed a dive by moving forward while holding the B Button and then pressing the A Button in any area of the field\n11) The arrow graphic changed back to the bunker that the user\'s character had already performed a successful dive behind\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must not be required to perform a dive behind a bunker that has already been successfully completed.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(3586,1222905600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,1,1222819200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The user\'s character\'s teammates are not in the proper stance at the start of the round','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, at the start of a round, some of the user\'s character\'s teammates are not in the proper starting stance\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects any mode of gameplay on the Main Menu\n2) Selects any level\n3) Proceeds into gameplay\n4) Some of the user\'s character\'s teammates are not in the proper starting stance, and are instead standing and aiming their markers to the side\n\nExpected Results:\nThe teammates must be in the proper starting stance at all times','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3596,1223078400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,2,3,1,1222905600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Scoring - Exhibition - Speedball (Center Flag) - Match Summary: The scoring texts for elimination and survivor must be taken out','Summary: \nDuring Exhibition, Speedball (In 5v5 and 7v7 Center Flag Matches), during the Match Summary screen, the scoring texts for elimination and survivor must be taken out\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter Exhibition, Speedball \n2) Select the Center Flag gametype\n3) Select any player type match up to 5v5 or 7v7\n4) Proceed to the Match Summary screen\n5) Observe that the scoring includes points for elimination and survivor\n\nExpected Results:\nThe scoring texts for elimination and survivor must be taken out to be consistent with gameplay.\n\nNOTES(1): The Match Summary screen for 5v5 and 7v7 should be changed to match the gameplay.\nNOTES(2): Screen shot attached','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/04/2008 09:59:40 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/03/08 Wii build.test\n',''),(3616,1222992000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,2,3,1,1222905600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Once - Scoring - Career Mode - NPPL Xtreme Paintball Beyond the Paint: The opposing team\'s score appeared incorrect at the end of the round.','Summary:\nOnce, during Career Mode gameplay, NPPL Xtreme Paintball Beyond the Paint, Preliminary rounds, the user\'s character was eliminated at the same time as the last opposing player was eliminated ending the round in a draw, but the HUD and Results gave the user 21 point and the opposing team 24 points, awarding the win to the opposing team.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu select Career Mode\n2) Select Play Tournament \n3) Select NPPL Xtreme Paintball Beyond the Paint\n4) Enter into gameplay\n5) The user eliminated the last opposing player while at the same time being eliminated ending the round\n6) The HUD and Results awarded the user 21 points and the opposing team 24 points\n\nExpected Results:\nThe points must be correctly calculated at all times for both the user and the opposing team.\n\nNote(1): In a 7v7 CTF NPPL tournament, a team is awarded 3 points for each elimination. Both teams should only be able to reach a maximum of 21 points when eliminating all the opposing players.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(3731,1222992000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,12,4,1,1222905600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - The text \'Menu\' is overlapping \'Pause\' in the in game pause menu.','Summary:\nThe text \'Menu\' is overlapping \'Pause\' in the in game pause menu.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Boot the game\n2) Enter into any form of gameplay \n3) Gameplay appears\n4) Press the 2 Button to pause the game\n5) Pause menu appears\n\nObserve the text \'Menu\' overlaps \'Pause\'\n\nExpected Results:\nAll menu text must be displayed correctly.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3809,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,3,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay: User presses their character against an object; this causes sporadic camera shaking and the user can see through the object.','Summary: User presses their character against an object; this causes sporadic camera shaking and the user can see through the object.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Quick Play.\n2) User selects any location.\n3) User begins gameplay.\n4) User positions their character facing an object.\n5) User presses \"up\" on the left-stick, in order to press against the object.\n6) User observes their camera shaking sporadically, and they can see through the object.\n\nExpected Results: User\'s camera must not shake or see through objects when pressing against them','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3811,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,5,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Comment - Multiplayer - Round Results: The Round Results and Final Results screens must appear easy for the User to read with clear indications of what all the stats and numbers relate to.','Summary:\nThe Round Results and Final Results screens must appear easy for the User to read with clear indications of what all the stats and numbers relate to.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer menu, Host creates a default multiplayer game,\n2) Client joins the Host\'s game,\n3) Users progress into gameplay,\n4) Users complete a round,\n5) The Round Results screen appears,\n6) Users observe that the stats and numbers are difficult to understand.\n\nExpected Result:\nThe Round Results and Final Results screens must appear easy for the User to read with clear indications of what all the stats and numbers relate to.\n\nNote(1): If the Users complete all rounds and arrive at the Final Results screen, the screen also has stats and numbers that are difficult to understand.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3823,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: In woodsball locations, the smaller pine trees change colors as the user approaches them from a distance.','Summary: In woodsball locations, the smaller pine trees change colors as the user approaches them from a distance. The trunks and leaves change colors as you approach the trees.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a multiplayer match.\n2) User 1 selects any Woodsball location.\n3) User 2 joins User 1\'s match lobby.\n4) Users begin gameplay.\n5) User 1 positions their camera, in order to view a small pine tree from a distance.\n6) User 1 presses forward on the left-stick to move toward the tree.\n7) User 1 observes the pine tree change colors as they approach it.\n\nExpected Results: Pine trees must not change colors when viewed from different distances.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3829,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,10,4,5,1219968000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Audio/Sound - Multiplayer: While standing next to an opponent, if User 1 prompts a voice over, User 2 hears a different character\'s voice.','Summary:\nWhile standing next to an opponent, if User 1 prompts a voice over, User 2 hears a different character\'s voice.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu, User 1 hosts a default multiplayer match,\n2) User 2 joins the Host\'s game lobby,\n3) Users enter into gameplay\n4) User 1 progresses toward the opponent\'s character,\n6) User 1 presses \"Up\" on the directional buttons to prompt a voice over,\n7) User 2 observes that the voice over is spoken by a different character than on User 1\'s console.\n\nExpected Results:\nVoice overs from must be spoken by the correct character when heard from any console.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3830,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: When a user goes prone, that user\'s hand clips through the ground.','Summary: When a user goes prone, that user\'s hand clips through the ground.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects quick play.\n2) User selects any location.\n3) User begins gameplay.\n4) User presses \"B\" twice to go prone.\n5) User observes their characters hand clips into the ground.\n\nExpected Results: Users must not clip into the ground when prone.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3833,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: Changing their character\'s Standing stances causes the Player\'s character to momentarilly float off the ground.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in a Multiplayer match, if the User switches their character\'s stance from Standing to Crouching and finally to Prone, other Players in the game are able to observe that the User\'s character momentarily floats off the ground while switching stances.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 hosts a Player Match game with any settings.\n2) At least one other User joins the game.\n3) User 1 launches the game.\n4) Gameplay appears.\n5) All Users navigate to the same location on the level.\n6) User 1 begins pressing the \"B\" button to make their character switch between the standing stances (Stand/Crouch/Prone).\n7) All other Users look at User 1\'s character, and are able to see that User 1\'s character momentarily floats off the ground when switching standing stances.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser\'s character must not appear to float off the ground when changing stand stances.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3836,1223078400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,12,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer - Round Results: The Round Results screen only appears for 3 seconds.','Summary:\nThe Round Results screen only appears for 3 seconds; shorter when/if all users press A to continue.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer menu, Host creates a default multiplayer game,\n2) Client joins the Host\'s game,\n3) Users progress into gameplay,\n4) Users complete a round,\n5) The Round Results screen appears,\n6) Users observe that the Round Results screen only appears for 3 seconds.\n\nExpected Result:\nThe Round Results screen must appear for at least 10 seconds.\n\nNote(1): If all Users press A on the Round Results screen, it will disappear in less than 3 seconds.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3841,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,12,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer - Pause Menu: On the Pause Menu, Users cannot scroll up to get to the bottom menu option and vice versa.','Summary:\nOn the Pause Menu, Users cannot scroll up to get to the bottom menu option and vice versa.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer menu, Host creates a default multiplayer game,\n2) Client joins the Host\'s game,\n3) Users progress into gameplay,\n4) Users press START to access the Pause Menu,\n5) Users observe that they cannot scroll up to get to the bottom menu option and vice versa.\n\nExpected Result:\nUsers must be able to scroll up to get to the bottom menu option and vice versa.','jhh\ntesting\n','[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/18/2008 02:39:04 AM]\nfixed in the 10/17/08 build\n\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/18/2008 02:41:00 AM]\nclicked the wrong bug. This is Verified open with the same steps in the 10/17 build\n\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/24/2008 01:53:28 AM]\nVerified in the 10/22 buildtest\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3843,1224288000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer - After the completion of one round in multiplayer, the Round Results screen appears with 2 square, black, transparent text boxes','Summary:\nAfter users complete one of the rounds in a multiplayer match, the Round Results screen appears. The Round Results screen appears with 2 square, black, transparent text boxes.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) 2 users load into any multiplayer match that is more than one round\n2) Users complete the round and the Round Results screen appears before the start of the next round\n3) Users will notice that Round Results screen appears with 2 black, square, transparent text boxes\n\nExpected Results:\nText boxes must appear stylized and visually stimulating','jhh\ntesting\n','[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/18/2008 02:43:32 AM]\nVerified open on the 10/17 build. Issue occurs with the same steps.test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3845,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,3,4,5,1219968000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay: When a user presses directly up against an object, the object pushes the user to the left or right.','Summary: When a user presses directly up against an object, the object pushes the user to the left or right. The user is holding forward, but instead moves to either side.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Quick Play.\n2) User selects any location.\n3) User begins gameplay.\n4) User positions their character facing an object.\n5) User presses up on the left-stick to run directly forward.\n6) User observes their character move to the left or the right, once it has collided with the object.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen the user navigates the character into an object the character must stop on the object when presses just forward.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3853,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: When the user changes their \"default marker hand\" to the left hand, the marker takes up more of the screen when compared to the right hand.','Summary: When the user changes their \"default marker hand\" to the left hand, the marker takes up more of the screen when compared to the right hand.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects quickplay.\n2) User selects any location.\n3) User begins gameplay.\n4) User presses the X button to change their default marker hand.\n5) User observes the marker takes up more screen space in the left hand than it does in the right hand.\n\nExpected Results: Marker must take up the same amount of screen space in both hands.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3858,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer - Multiple Members of the crowd float above the seating within the stands.','Summary:\nWithin multiplayer gameplay, multiple members of the crowd float above the seating within the stands in arena gameplay.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host creates a multiplayer match on an arena map\n2) A client joins the lobby\n3) The users load into gameplay\n4) The users observe multiple members of the crowd are floating above the seating within the stands\n\nExpected Results:\nThe crowd must appear normally within multiplayer gameplay.\n\nNote: Easiest to notice on the Magala, Spain level.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3859,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: While watching another Player performing the reload animation, the User observes there is no pod within that Player\'s hand.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay of a Play Online match, if the User navigates their character up to another Player, that Player performs the reload animation, and the User observes no pod appears within that Player\'s hand.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 hosts a Play Online match with any settings.\n2) User 2 joins the match.\n3) All Users READY up, and User 1 launches the game.\n4) Gameplay appears.\n5) From the starting position, User 1 navigates their character to User 2\'s character, and positions themself to the side of User 2\'s character.\n6) User 2 presses the \"RB\"/\"Right Trigger\" button to fire off a few paintball rounds at the ground.\n7) User 2 then clicks the \"Right Stick\" (RELOAD) button to perform the reload action.\n8) User 1 observes User 2\'s character perform the reload action.\n9) User 1 observes that User 2\'s character has no pod in their hand when performing the action.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe reload animation must appear correctly to other Players.\n\nNOTE: No paintballs appear as well.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(3863,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: On the filters list for a client, there is no \"Any\" option for a filter.','Summary: \nOn the filters list for a client, there is no \"Any\" option for a filter. The client has to choose specifically what game mode they want.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Xbox Live\n2) User selects Player Match\n3) User selects Join Game\n4) User observes no \"Any\" option is available\n\nExpected Results: \nThere must be an \"Any\"option available.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3874,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,5,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Comment - Gameplayer - Multiplayer: User should be able to control Bot difficulty level.','Summary:\nUser should be able to control Bot difficulty level before entering a match.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer menu, User hosts a default match,\n2) Adds a bot to the other team,\n3) Loads into gameplay,\n4) Observes that the bot is too easy.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser must be able to control the bot difficulty before starting the match.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3876,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,5,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: There are no vital game statistics/settings displayed in the Game Lobby prior to entering gameplay.','Summary:\nThere are no vital game statistics/settings displayed in the Game Lobby prior to entering gameplay.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Multiplayer,\n2) Select Play Online or Local Network,\n3) Create or Join a game,\n4) Observe in the Game Lobby that there are no vital game statistics/settings displayed.\n\nNote(1): Since there is a possible maximum number of 14 players, Users may have to wait in the Game Lobby an indeterminable length of time before entering gameplay and it would be very useful to have the Game Type, Time Limit, Rounds, whether or not Friendly Fire is turned on, and whether or not Cheating is allowed displayed in the Game Lobby before the match begins; Users may forget what the match settings are prior to entering gameplay.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3884,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: AI players start in different standing positions.','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer, the AI players start in different standing positions.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Host creates default Multiplayer match\n2) The Host adds the maximum number of bots to the Red Team and Yellow Team\n3) Host starts the game\n4) Gameplay appears\n5) The Host notices that some AI start standing straight up and some AI players are leaning forward in a crouching position.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll AI players must start in the same standing position.\n\nNOTE: Bug also occurs in Exhibition.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3886,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: If Client disconnects the network cable while the Game Lobby countdown begins, then plugs the network cable back in, the Client encounters a loading screen.','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer, if the Client disconnects the network cable while the Game Lobby countdown begins, then plugs the network cable back in, the Client encounters a loading screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Host creates default Multiplayer match\n2) Client joins the Host\'s game\n3) Host starts the Game Lobby timer\n4) During the Game Lobby countdown the Client disconnects the network cable from the system\n5) After the Client receives the disconnected message, the Client plugs the network cable back in the system\n6) The Client selects OK on the disconnected message\n7) The Client is brought back to the Main Menu\n8) Client waits a few seconds\n9) The Client encounters a Loading screen, then brought back to the Multiplayer Menu\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Client must not get a loading screen in the Main Menu, after disconnecting the network cable from the Game Lobby.\n\nNOTE: If the Client proceeds to single player or multiplayer gameplay after this bug occurs, the user crashes on the load screen.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3897,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania: The course appears without a Big Spike on the 50 yard line, which violates NPPL\'s official rules.','Summary:\nThe course appears without a Big Spike on the 50 yard-line, which violates NPPL\'s Official rules.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User enters into gameplay at Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania\n2) User observes no Big Spike on the 50 yard-line.\n\nExpected Results:\nA Big Spike must appear on either the right-50, left-50, or center-50.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3904,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223078400,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Multiplayer: User crashes after beginning gameplay on a Custom Houston, Texas with 13 bots.','Summary: User crashes after beginning gameplay on a Custom Houston, Texas with 13 bots. The custom map had 35 large round bunkers placed as close as possible to the middle of the map.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Field Editor.\n2) User selects Houston, Texas.\n3) User deletes all of the bunkers, and replaces them with 35 Large Round bunkers, placed as closely to the center as possible.\n4) User saves the map.\n5) User creates a multiplayer match, using the custom map.\n6) User adds 13 bots to the match.\n7) User begins gameplay.\n8) User observes crash.\n\nExpected Results: Users must not crash.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3908,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: While watching another person dive in multiplayer gameplay, User observes the other User\'s character clipping through environmental objects.','Summary:\nWhile watching another person dive in multiplayer gameplay, User observes the other User\'s character clipping through environmental objects.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 hosts a default multiplayer match\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s game\n3) User load into gameplay\n4) User 1 positions their character so they are looking at User 2\n5) User 2 runs at an object and performs the dive action\n6) User 1 observes User 2\'s character clipping through the object.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser\'s character must not clip through environmental objects while performing the dive action.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3909,1224288000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,2,3,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Scoring - Career Mode: Center Flag scoring is inconsistent, and incorrect.','Summary: Center Flag scoring is inconsistent, and incorrect. Depending on the number of players per match (1vs1, 2vs2, etc) the scoring changes for eliminations and survivors. For all center flag games the scoring for Flag Hangs and Flag Pulls is different, and incorrect. Ex. 7vs7 Hang = 40 points, Pull = 32 points. Ex. 1vs1 Hang = 32 points, Pull = 50 points. Ex. 5vs5 Hang = 55 points, Pull = 20 points.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Exhibition. \n2) User selects Any Teams.\n3) User selects 7vs7.\n4) User selects Center Flag.\n5) User begins gameplay at any location.\n6) User picks up the flag first, and observes 32 points.\n7) User hangs flag and observes 40 points.\n\nExpected Results: Scoring must work correctly.\n\nNOTE: Eliminations in 4vs4 and 5vs5 are worth 4 points instead of 3.','jhh\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/17/2008 05:10:23 AM]\nWe thought that the 100pts system is to be used with the Capture the Flag matches.\nNow we should have it also for Center Flag?\n\nRequesting producer input on this.\n\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/18/2008 01:47:12 AM]\nPlease review this issuestest\n',''),(3913,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: In a 7vs7 match, the user observes a drop in Frame Rate.','Summary: In single player gameplay, in a 7vs7 match, the user observes a lower frame rate. Example: XPSL Nevada (Career Mode)\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Career Mode.\n2) User selects Play Tournament.\n3) User selects XPSL Nevada.\n4) User begins gameplay.\n5) User observes a low frame rate during gameplay.\n\nExpected Results: Gameplay must function smoothly.\n\nNOTE: Some locations are less severe, but still noticeable.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3923,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: Host encounters moderate framerate drop during gameplay.','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer, the Host encounters moderate framerate drop during gameplay.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Host creates default Multiplayer match\n2) 13 Clients join the Host\'s game\n3) Host starts the game\n4) Gameplay appears\n5) During gameplay, the Host encounters moderate framerate drop during gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nHost must not encounter framerate drops.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(3938,1223164800,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,4,3,1,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Once - Video/Graphic - Exhibition - Speedball (Jacksonville, FL): The camera view during the victory animation appeared incorrectly','Summary: \nOnce, during Exhibition, in Speedball (Jacksonville, FL) Center Flag, the user grabbed the flag, eliminated the opponent, hung the flag at the opponent\'s flag station, the camera view appeared to display the user\'s character floating in the air\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Entered Exhibition, in Speedball (Jacksonville, FL) Center Flag\n2) Grabbed the flag\n3) Eliminated the opponent\n4) Hung the flag at the opponent\'s flag station\n5) The victory animation played\n6) Once, observed that the camera view appeared to display the user\'s character floating in the air\n\nExpected Results:\nThe camera view during the victory animation must appear properly\n\nNOTES(1): Video is available','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(3967,1223337600,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,3,1,1223078400,0,0,0,3,'(20%-29%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Career Mode: The user takes control of a eliminated teammate','Summary:\nOccasionally, during Career Mode, if the user\'s character gets eliminated, the user is automatically placed behind a player that will be taken over, the player is eliminated before the user takes control, the user takes control of the eliminated player and the player is not counted as eliminated\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Career Mode on the Main Menu\n2) Proceeds into gameplay\n3) User\'s character gets eliminated\n4) The user is automatically placed behind another player that will be taken over\n5) The player is hit by a paintball and is eliminated before being taken over\n6) Occasionally, the user takes control of the eliminated player and the player resumes with gameplay\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must not take control of eliminated players','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/06/2008 05:20:57 PM]\ncannot reproduce it\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/07/2008 04:56:30 AM]\nVerified Open in 10/06/08 Wii build.test\n',''),(3970,1223164800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,1,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The user\'s character does not remove the lid to the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity while reloading','Summary:\nDuring Gameplay, with the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity hopper equipped, if the user\'s character reloads, the user\'s character does not remove the lid to the hopper\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects any mode of gameplay on the Main Menu, with the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity hopper equipped\n2) Selects any location\n3) Proceeds into gameplay\n4) User\'s character fires at least one shot\n5) Reloads the hopper\n6) 