uring gameplay, Tournament 19b - Texas Invitational (Houston, Texas), if the User completes the third match in the bracket, the game crashes on the Post Match Results Screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n2) Select Play Tournament,\n3) Select Texas Invitational - Houston, Texas,\n4) Proceed through the Invitational until entering into the third match,\n5) Win the match,\n6) Observe that frequently, the game crashes on the Post Match Results Screen.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash on the post results screen.\n\nNOTE(1): Three Xbox Xenon Crash Dumps are located on the FTP in the following location:\n/Paintball/X360 Crash Dumps\n\n- PB_#4281.rar','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4282,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1223078400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Gameplay: Completing a tournament that had been already finished does not appear to award the appropriate amount of credits.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, if the User\'s Character replays a finished tournament, they do not appear to be awarded the full amount of credits.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter Career Mode, then select Tournament,\n2) Select any tournament,\n3) Complete the tournament,\n4) Replay and complete the finished tournament,\n5) Observe the User appears to earn 0 credits instead of what was stated to have been earned.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser must be able to replay tournaments to earn credits.\n\nNOTE(1): Previously played tournament games appear to not award the User with any of the credits that it informs the User they have earned.\nNOTE(2): As of the 10/22/08 build, if the user gets 2nd place in a tournament and then replays the tournament and earns 1st place, he will gain the full amount of 1st place credits. If, however, the user gets 1st place in a tournament and then replays the tournament and receives 1st place a second time, he will get no extra credits.\n\nThis design encourages users to purposefully finish all tournaments in 2nd place, and then go back and finish them all again in 1st place for extra credits.\n\nIf the user is given 2nd place in a tournament and he replays it again and gets 1st, he should only be given the credits he did not earn the first time around - OR - the user should be allowed to earn the full amount of credits per place every time he plays through, allowing him to accrue unlimited credits.','jhh\n','[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 05:42:47 PM]\nVerified on the 10/22/08 X360 Build.test\n',''),(4299,1223251200,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Gameplay - Speedball - San Bernardino, California: Opponent AI did not pick up center flag','Summary:\nOnce, during Quick play, in Speed-ball - San Bernardino, California, the opponent team did not pick up the center flag after the user\'s character was eliminated.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu user select Quick Play.\n2) Selected San Bernardino, California.\n3) Enemy team eliminates all team-mates on user\'s character\'s team but 1.\n4) user\'s character picked up center flag.\n5) User\'s character was eliminated.\n5) Observed that the opponent AI did not pick up the center flag and return it to the correct flag station.\n\nExpected Results:\nAfter the user\'s character loses a match, the opponent AI must grab the center flag and hang it in the correct flag station. \n\nNote(1):\nScreen-shot attached.\n\nNote(2):\nVideo-documentation available.\n\nNote(3):\nOnce, happened in Speedball - Orlando, FL','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4322,1223337600,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,3,1,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Gameplay - Speedball - Malaga, Spain: User\'s team-mates did not pick up center flag','Summary:\nOnce, during Quick play, in a Speed-ball exhibition in Malaga, Spain, the user\'s team-mates did not pick up the center flag after the user\'s character fully eliminated the opponent.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu user select Quick Play.\n2) Selected Malaga, Spain.\n3) User\'s character eliminated the opponent.\n5) Once, user observed that the user\'s team-mates did not pick up the center flag and return it to the correct flag station.\n\nExpected Results:\nAfter the user\'s character eliminates the opponent with more than one survivor, the user\'s character\'s team-mate(s) must grab the center flag and hang it in the correct flag station. \n\nNote(1):\nVideo-documentation available.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4336,1223337600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,1,1223251200,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally - Video/Graphic - Career Mode (NPPL Tournaments) - Results: The screen displays 9 Preliminary matches and the opponent\'s name for the Preliminary match does not show up','Summary: \nOccasionally, during Career Mode, in any NPPL Tournaments, during the final Match Results screen, 9 Preliminary matches are displayed and the opponent\'s name for the Preliminary match does not show up\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Entered Career Mode, in any NPPL Tournament\n2) Completed the whole tournament\n3) The final Match Results screen appeared\n4) Occasionally, observed that the screen displays 9 Preliminary matches, and the opponent\'s name for the Preliminary match does not show up\n\nExpected Results:\nResults must appear properly in gameplay\n\nNOTES(1): Screen shot attached\nNOTES(2): Bug happend in NPPL Houston, NPPL Huntington Beach, and NPPL Commander\'s Cup','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(4337,1223337600,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,17,3,1,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Options - Field Creator: Unnecessary options appear in the Options/Gameplay menu','Summary:\nIn Field Creator, if the user enters the the Pause Menu, selects Options, selects Gameplay, unnecessary options appear in the Gameplay menu\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Field Creator on the Main Menu\n2) Selects any map\n3) Proceeds into the field creator\n4) Pushes the 2 Button to enter the Pause Menu\n5) Selects Options\n6) Selects Gameplay\n7) The Cheatmeter and the Ramping option appears in the menu\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Gameplay Menu for Field Creator must only have the Autosave option\n\nNote: The \"Show Player Names\" option appears if the user enters the Field Creator after exiting out of a Career Mode match; and the \"Automatic Fire\" option appears if the user enters the Field Creator after exiting out of a Woodsball match.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4338,1223337600,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,17,3,1,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Options - Dynasty Training Drills: Unnecessary options appear in the Options/Gameplay menu','Summary:\nIn the Dynasty Training Drills, if the user enters the the Pause Menu, selects Options, selects Gameplay, unnecessary options appear in the Gameplay menu\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Field Creator on the Main Menu\n2) Selects any map\n3) Proceeds into the field creator\n4) Pushes the 2 Button to enter the Pause Menu\n5) Selects Options\n6) Selects Gameplay\n7) The Cheatmeter option appears in the menu\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Gameplay Menu for Field Creator must only have the Autosave option and the Ramping option\n\nNote: The \"Show Player Names\" option appears if the user enters the Field Creator after exiting out of a Career Mode match; and the \"Automatic Fire\" option appears if the user enters the Field Creator after exiting out of a Woodsball match.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4339,1223337600,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,6,2,1,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Exhibition: Loading into 2nd match on a custom field, the game crashed','Summary:\nOnce, during a 7 vs 7, 9 round, capture the flag exhibition on a custom map, the game crashed loading into the 2nd round.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu user selects exhibition.\n2) Set up a 7 vs 7, 9 round, capture the flag exhibition with the default teams.\n3) Selected a custom map from save slot 2.\n4) User\'s character lost match with 6 eliminations.\n5) Initiated 2nd match.\n6) Once,during the camera movement over the field, the game crashed.\n\nExpected Results:\nGame must not crash.\n\nNote():\nVideo-documentation available','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4340,1223337600,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223251200,0,0,0,3,'(10%-19%)','Occasionally - Gameplay: The opposing AI did not return the flag in a center flag match.','Summary:\nOccasionally, during Center Flag gameplay, when the user\'s character grabbed the flag and moved directly in front of their home flag station and then the user\'s character and all of their team was eliminated, the opposing AI player grabbed the flag that was directly in front of the flag station and remained still not hanging it.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Entered a Center Flag match\n2) The user\'s character gained possession of the flag\n3) The user\'s character moved directly in front of the user\'s home flag station\n4) The user\'s teammates were eliminated\n5) The user\'s character was eliminated\n6) An AI player grabbed the flag that laid directly in front of the flag station\n7) The AI player remained still with the flag, and never hung it\n\nExpected Results:\nThe AI players must hang the flag after gaining possession of it.\n\nNote(1): This bug has occured in Career Mode, Exhibition Mode, and Quick Play Center Flag matches.\nNote(2): In 10-8-08 build, occurred twice in Woodsball, Train Depot Field, but opponents did not retrieve the flag and remained idle.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4345,1223337600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: There is no indication of who is talking in the Match Lobby','Summary:\nThere is no indication of who is talking in the Match Lobby\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Match Lobby, with more than one Player with a headset.\n2) Any player talks, and there is no indication of who is talking.\n\nExpected Results:\nA graphical representation must appear when a Player talks, to indicate who is talking.\n\nNotes:\n1) This occurs in Ranked Match, Player Match, and System Link.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4346,1223337600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: There is no indication of who is talking during gameplay','Summary:\nThere is no indication of who is talking during gameplay.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Ranked Match, with more than one Player with a headset in the same team.\n2) Any player talks, and there is no indication of who is talking.\n\nExpected Results:\nA graphical representation must appear when a Player talks along with their Gamertag, to indicate who is talking.\n\nNotes:\n1) This occurs in Ranked Match, Player Match, and System Link.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4348,1223337600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Ranked Match Lobby: Player\'s are not properly listed on the Players List when in the same game lobby','Summary:\nPlayer\'s are not properly listed on the Players List when in the same game lobby\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Ranked Match Lobby, with the Player as the Host.\n2) A Client joins the match lobby that has not played with the Player before.\n3) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n4) The Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n5) The Player selects Players, and the Client\'s Gamertag does not appear on the Players List.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll players that have played with the Player must appear on the Players List.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4351,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,10,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Audio/Sound - Gameplay: Reloading audio appears to play quieter than other gameplay SFX.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, if the User reloads, the reload audio appears to play at a lessened volume level than other SFX.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Load into any area of gameplay,\n2) Reload after firing,\n3) Observe that the audio level of the reload appears to play quieter than all other SFX.\n\nExpected Results:\nReload audio must appear to play at a consistent level with other game SFX.','jhh\ntesting\n','[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/20/2008 08:45:31 AM]\nVerified on the 10/17/08 Build.test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(4353,1223337600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,2,'(90%-99%)','Frequently - Technical Check - Player Match Lobby: Player\'s are not properly listed on the Players List when in the same game lobby','Summary:\nPlayer\'s are not properly listed on the Players List when in the same game lobby\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Player Match Lobby, with the Player as the Host.\n2) A Client joins the match lobby that has not played with the Player before.\n3) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n4) The Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n5) The Player selects Players, and the Client\'s Gamertag does not appear on the Players List.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll players that have played with the Player must appear on the Players List.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4359,1223337600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,2,'(70%-79%)','Frequently - Technical Check - Player Match Games List: The game map does not display correctly','Summary:\nFrequently, in the Player Match Games List, the game map name does not display the correct map that has been selected.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Player Match Menu, with a hosted and joinable game that has any of the pre-made maps selected.\n2) The Player selects Join Game.\n3) The Player Match Filters Menu appears.\n4) The Player selects search with the filters set to the hosted game.\n3) The Games List appears, and the Map Name for the hosted game appears as:\n\n\"Custom created\"\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Map Name must correctly appear as the map the Host selected.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4370,1223337600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,2,'(50%-59%)','Frequently - TCR 088 - Multiplayer Player Match Games List: Gamertags are incorrectly displayed','Summary:\nFrequently, In Multiplayer Player Match Games List, Gamertags do not display correctly.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Player Match Menu, with a joinable Player Match game hosted.\n2) The Client selects Join Game.\n3) The Player Match Filters Menu appears.\n4) The Player presses the A (Search) button with the filters set to the hosted game.\n5) The Games List appears, and hosted games Game Name appears as \"SV_Paintball\".\n\nExpected Results:\nGamertags must be displayed properly.\n\nGames must correctly display all 15 characters of any gamertag. Gamertags consist of ASCII characters a-z, A-Z, 0-9, (, ), and \" \" (ASCII character 0×20). This is a violation of TCR 088.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4379,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Gameplay: Pausing the game when the Cheat Meter is on screen and returning to gameplay causes the User to fail the cheat.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, in any game utilizing the 3 for 1 cheat meter penalty, if the User\'s Character is hit, the User Pauses the game while the meter is in the yellow/red section of the meter, and selects Resume, the User is returned to gameplay and instantly fails the cheat.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter into any game utilizing the 1,2 or 3 for 1 cheat penalty,\n2) Get hit,\n3) While the meter is in the yellow/red, Pause the game,\n4) Select Resume using the A (continue) Button,\n5) Observe that the User instantly fails the cheat.\n\nExpected Results:\nButton confirmation from the Pause Menu must not effect the button confirmation required by the Cheat Meter.\n\nNOTE(1): This only occurs if the User presses the A Button to return to gameplay from the Pause Menu.\nNOTE(2): This only occurs with the 1,2 or 3 for 1 style Cheat Meter (noted in the attached screenshot).','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4384,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,6,2,1,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Team Manager: Game crashed when scrolling through the list of team mates.','Summary:\nOnce, during gameplay, at the Team Manager screen (in-game), User completing the Pacific Shootout Challenge tournament and unlocked a new team mate, User proceeded to the 2v2 XPSL NorCal tournament and was brought to the Team Manager screen. User scrolled through the list, and selected 5 team mates, then scrolled through the list and the game crashed to a black screen with looping audio.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Entered gameplay, Career Mode, Pacific Shootout Challenge.\n2) Completed the event.\n3) User unlocked a new team mate.\n4) User proceeded to the next event.\n5) User was brought to the Team Manager screen to recruit more team mates.\n6) User selected 5 additional team mates.\n7) User scrolled through the list of team mates towards the second slot.\n8) Observed that game crashed to a black screen with looping audio while highlighting team mates.\n\nExpected Results:\nGame must not crash when selecting team mates.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4398,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Crash - Multiplayer System Link: Disconnecting the Ethernet cable from the back of the Xbox 360 console during the loading screen','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer System Link, disconnecting the Ethernet cable from the back of the Xbox 360 console during the loading screen into gameplay causes the game to hard crash.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu, with an Ethernet cable connected to the back of the Xbox 360 console.0\n2) The Player selects System Link.\n3) The Player creates a Game.\n4) The Match Lobby appears.\n5) The Player presses RB (add bot) button. to add a bot.\n6) The Player presses A (start game) button.\n7) The loading screen appears, and the Player disconnects the Ethernet cable from the back of the Xbox 360 console.\n8) The game hard locks and is unrecoverable.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must properly handle network disconnects.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4421,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 006 - Multiplayer: Users observe a static screen that varies in length (dependant on the number of games hosted) after pressing \"A\" on the Join Game screen.','Summary: Users observe a static screen that varies in length (dependant on the number of games hosted) after pressing \"A\" on the Join Game screen. The screen is static for about 2 seconds per game that is hosted. With 4 games hosted on the list, the static screen lasts about 8 seconds.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Users 1-4 each host a default Capture the Flag - Player Match.\n2) User 5 selects Multiplayer.\n3) User 5 selects Xbox LIVE\n4) User 5 selects Player Match.\n5) User 5 selects Join Game.\n6) User 5 presses \"A\" on the Join Game screen.\n7) User 5 observes an eight second static screen before the games list appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe screen must not be static.\n\nGames must not pause without game-representative on-screen graphics. When the pause time is greater than five seconds, the game must indicate the reason and provide on-screen animation. This is a violation of TCR 006.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4434,1223596800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: If the user enters the Ranked Match menu, backs out, then creates a Player Match game, a Ranked match is created.','Summary: \nIf the user enters the Ranked Match menu, backs out, then creates a Player Match game, a Ranked match is created.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 selects Multiplayer.\n2) User 1 selects Xbox LIVE.\n3) User 1 selects Ranked Match.\n4) User 1 presses \"B\" to back up.\n5) User 1 selects Player Match.\n6) User 1 creates a default game.\n7) User 2 selects Player Match.\n8) User 2 selects join game, and default searches.\n9) User 2 observes User 1\'s game is not on the list.\n10) User 2 repeats the search under Ranked Match.\n11) User 2 observes User 1\'s game is on the list.\n\nExpected Results: Menu flow must not interfere with multiplayer match creation\n.\nNOTE(1): The game also appears on the System Link Games List.','jhh\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/10/2008 03:54:42 AM]test\n',''),(4436,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Crash - Multiplayer: When the Host leaves a multiplayer match before the Client, the Client is returned to the main menu and crashes.','Summary: Host leaves a multiplayer match before the client, the client is returned to the main menu and crashes.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default multiplayer match\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s game\n3) Users begin gameplay\n4) User 2 presses Start to pause their game\n5) User 1 manually quits from the game via the pause menu\n6) User 2 receives a disconnection message\n7) User 2 observes the game crash on the main menu after pressing \"A\" on the message.\n\nExpected Results: \nClient must not crash when disconnected form the Host.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4437,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Multiplayer: The default marker hand option does not function correctly in multiplayer. All users default marker hand is based off of the host\'s choice.','Summary: The default marker hand option does not function correctly in multiplayer. All users default marker hand is based off of the host\'s choice. If the host\'s default hand is \"left,\" then all clients who join the match start with their marker in their left hand.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 selects options.\n2) User 1 selects movement.\n3) User 1 changes the default marker hand to \"left.\"\n4) User 1 creates a default multiplayer match.\n5) User 2 joins User 1\'s match.\n6) Users begin gameplay.\n7) User 2 observes their marker is placed in the left hand.\n\nExpected Results: Default marker hand must function correctly.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4443,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: Users are returned to the multiplayer menu after accepting any game invites while in a multiplayer game lobby.','Summary: Users are returned to the multiplayer menu after accepting any game invites while in a multiplayer game lobby.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default player match.\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s match.\n3) User 3 creates a default player match.\n4) User 3 presses \"Y\" to open the invite menu.\n5) User 3 highlights User 2\'s gamertag and presses \"A\" to invite.\n6) User 2 accepts User 3\'s invite.\n7) User 2 is brought back to the multiplayer menu.\n\nExpected Results: Multiplayer invites must function correctly.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4446,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Crash - Multiplayer: User crashes after accepting an invite during multiplayer gameplay and joining the new lobby, and then the host backs out of the lobby.','Summary: User crashes after accepting an invite during multiplayer gameplay and joining the new lobby, and then the host backs out of the lobby. The client crashes on a black screen after pressing \"A\" on the disconnection message.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default Player Match.\n2) User 2 creates a default Player Match.\n3) User 2 presses \"LB\" to add a bot to the game.\n4) User 2 presses \"A\" to begin the game.\n5) User 2 begins gameplay.\n6) User 1 presses \"Y\" to open the Invite menu.\n7) User 1 presses \"A\" while highlighting User 2\'s name to invite.\n8) User 2 accepts the invite.\n9) User 2 enters User 1\'s game lobby.\n10) User 1 manually backs out of the lobby.\n11) User 2 observes a disconnection message, and presses \"A\".\n12) User 2 observes a crash on a black screen.\n\nExpected Results: Users must not crash.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4454,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: Lobby team lists do not update correctly when 13 users simultaneously join a match hosted by a user with 200 ms or less round trip latency between consoles.','Summary: Lobby team lists do not update correctly when 13 users simultaneously join a match hosted by a user with 200 ms or less round trip latency between consoles. The red team fills up all 7 slots, while the yellow team appears to have 0-1 users on the team.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default player match, using 200 ms or less round trip latency.\n2) Users 2-14 simultaneously join User 1\'s match.\n3) Users observe the Yellow team does not update correctly, and displays either 0 users, or 1 user on the team.\n\nExpected Results: Teams must update correctly.\n\nNOTE(1): This also occurs without simultaneous joins, just not as frequently.\nNOTE(2): Occasionally the teams are only missing a few users.\nNOTE(3): This also occurs in Ranked matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4464,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Multiplayer - When the host was a on throttled connection, a client crashed loading into gameplay.','Summary:\nOnce, when the host was on a throttled connection running at 200ms or less round trip latency between consoles, when 13 clients joined the game lobby and the host started the match, a client crashed on the pre-game fly by camera.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host creates a default multiplayer match while running on a connection at 200ms or less round trip latency between consoles\n2) 13 clients join the game lobby and \"ready up\"\n3) The host starts the game\n4) On the pre-game fly by camera one client crashed\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash loading into gameplay when the host is running on a throttled connection.\n\nNote: Watson Crash dump attached.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4465,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: Lobby team lists do not update correctly when 13 users simultaneously join a match hosted by a user with a connection that has ten percent or less packet loss in a ten second interval.','Summary: Lobby team lists do not update correctly when 13 users simultaneously join a match hosted by a user with a connection that has ten percent or less packet loss in a ten second interval.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default player match, with ten percent or less packet loss in a ten second interval.\n2) Users 2-14 simultaneously join User 1\'s match.\n3) At least 1 client observes Users missing from the Yellow team list.\n\nExpected Results: Teams must update correctly.\n\nNOTE(1): This also occurs without simultaneous joins, just not as frequently.\nNOTE(2): This also occurs in Ranked matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4468,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 096 - Multiplayer: Xbox LIVE player match gameplay does not function when the host has an internet connection with limited bandwidth of 64kbps/64kbps.','Summary: When the host of an Xbox LIVE multiplayer player match has an internet connection with limited bandwidth at 64kbps/64kbps, Xbox LIVE gameplay does not function.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) With an internet connection limited to 64kbps/64kbps, user 1 creates a default Xbox LIVE player match.\n2) User 2 attempts to join user 1\'s game.\n3) User 2 observes when user 1 attempts to start the game, they are disconnected from the game.\n\nExpected Results: The title must support Xbox LIVE gameplay when the host has an internet connection with limited bandwidth of 64kbps/64kbps.\n\nPeer-to-peer gameplay between two different Xbox consoles must not be disconnected as long as the following performance conditions are maintained:\n• Each console has an upstream and downstream bandwidth of 64 kilobits/sec (64,000 bits/sec) or higher.\n• 200 ms or less round-trip latency between consoles.\n• Ten percent or less packet loss in a ten-second interval.\n• Two percent or less packet loss, in general.\n\nThis is a violation of TCR 096.\n\nNote: \n1) If multiple clients attempt to join the host\'s game lobby, they will be disconnected from the lobby.\n2) This is PreCert TCR 096 Issue 1 of 1.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4472,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,3,'(40%-49%)','Occasionally (40%-49%) - Technical Check - Multiplayer: Lobby team lists do not update correctly when 13 users simultaneously join a match hosted by a user with a connection that has two percent packet loss.','Summary: Lobby team lists do not update correctly when 13 users simultaneously join a match hosted by a user with a connection that has two percent packet loss.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default player match, with two percent packet loss.\n2) Users 2-14 simultaneously join User 1\'s match.\n3) At least 1 client observes Users missing from the Yellow team list.\n\nExpected Results: Teams must update correctly.\n\nNOTE(1): This also occurs without simultaneous joins, just not as frequently.\nNOTE(2): This also occurs in Ranked matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4475,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,2,'(50%-59%)','Frequently (50%-59%) - Technical Check - Multiplayer: Lobby team lists do not update correctly when 13 users simultaneously join a ranked match.','Summary: Lobby team lists do not update correctly when 13 users simultaneously join a ranked match.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default ranked match.\n2) Users 2-14 simultaneously join User 1\'s match.\n3) At least 1 client observes Users missing from the Yellow team list.\n\nExpected Results: Teams must update correctly.\n\nNOTE(1): This also occurs without simultaneous joins, just not as frequently.\nNOTE(2): This also occurs in System Link.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4477,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,3,'(20%-29%)','Occasionally - Technical Check - Multiplayer - The client receives the \"Could not join game\" message when loading into a game lobby.','Summary:\nOccasionally, when loading into a default multiplayer game lobby with 13 clients (one by one or simultaneously), one client will receive the \"Could not join game\" message.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host creates a default multiplayer match\n2) 13 clients join the game lobby\n3) Occasionally, one client will receive the \"Could not join game\" message.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must always be able to join a game lobby that is not full.\n\nNote: This occurs more frequently when the host is on a throttled internet connection.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4481,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Crash - Multiplayer - When the host disconnects during the game lobby countdown, multiple clients crash on the loading screen into gameplay.','Summary:\nWhen the host disconnects during the game lobby countdown, multiple clients crash on the loading screen into multiplayer gameplay with 14 players.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host creates a default multiplayer match\n2) 13 clients join the game lobby and \"ready up\"\n3) The host presses the A button to start the match\n4) Disconnects in any manner (power down, sign out, network cable, or WAN) as soon as the countdown appears\n5) When the loading screen appear, multiple clients crash.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash when the host disconnects from the game lobby during the countdown to gameplay.\n\nNote: This occurs when the host disconnects on the loading screen or on the Waiting for Players screen before gameplay as well.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4483,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Crash - Multiplayer - When the host of a match is connected to a WAN router, multiple clients crash loading into gameplay.','Summary:\nWhen loading into multiplayer gameplay with 14 players when the host is connected to a WAN router, multiple clients crash on the loading screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host creates a default multiplayer match while connected to a WAN router\n2) 13 clients joins the game lobby and \"Ready up\"\n3) The host presses A to start the match and the loading screen appears\n4) Multiple clients crash loading into gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash when loading into multiplayer gameplay when the host is connected to a router.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4485,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223337600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Exhibition (Custom Map): AI characters do not react properly to a bunker layout','Summary:\nWith a Custom Map created that has numerous bunkers lined up across the 20 yard line, the AI characters (friendly and enemy alike) that are assigned to grab or hang the flag cease to move to the flag or flag station to finish the match. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu select Field Creator\n2) Select any Pre-Made field\n3) Proceed to delete all of the existing bunkers on the field by holding the B Button and pressing the A Button repeatedly\n4) Selects a bunker to block the flag station (snake bunker works 100%)\n5) Proceed to place the bunkers in a line that runs parallel to the ends of the field (there should be 5 bunkers placed on each of the team\'s sides of the field (there should be a \'wall of bunkers\' created that forces the players to use the \'safe corridor\'. See the attached topdown screenshot for reference.)\n6) Proceed to save and exit the Field Creator\n7) Return to the Main Menu and select Exhibition\n8) With 7v7 Capture the Flag (or Center Flag) settings selected, continue to the field selection\n9) Press the 2 (Custom) Button\n10) Select the recently saved Custom Map\n11) Press the A Button to Continue into the match\n12) Allow the user\'s team to be eliminated\n13) Observe that the opponent (or the user\'s character\'s team in the opposite scenario) gets stuck along the bunkers and will never retrieve the flag.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll NPCs must react properly to game events.\n\nNote: Video capture available.\n\nNote: Multiple screenshots of bunker setup attached.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4487,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223337600,0,0,0,4,'','Twice - Gameplay - Exhibition: In a custom map, oppponent did not pick up & return flag','Summary:\nTwice, while playing in a 7 vs. 7, seven round, capture the flag exhibition in a custom Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania map and a custom Malaga, Spain map, the opponent failed to pick up and return the flag after the user\'s character was eliminated. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main menu user selected Exhibtion.\n2) Set up a 7vs. 7, 7 round, capture the flag exhibition with the default teams.\n3) Selected a previously created custom map in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.\n4) Gameplay initiated.\n5) Won 3 matches and lost 1.\n6) User\'s character was fully eliminated during the 5th round.\n7) Twice, Observed that the opponent did not grab and return the flag resulting in the user being unable to complete stage.\n\nExpected Results:\nDuring capture the Flag and Center Flag matches, after the user\'s character has been eliminated, the enemy must return the flag to the correct location.\n\nNote(1):\nScreen-shot of custom map attached.\n\nNote(2):\nVideo-documentation available.\n\nNote(3) :\nIn both instances of the issue, many 8ft tetrahedron bunkers were placed in the custom map.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4488,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: When the user signs back into Xbox Live before loading back to the Press Start screen, the user signs in, then is stuck signing back out.','Summary:\nWhen the user signs out of Xbox LIVE from within multiplayer gameplay, when the user signs back in before loading out to the Press start screen, the user signs in and then is stuck signing out.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host creates a default multiplayer match\n2) A client joins the match\n3) Gameplay begins\n4) Either user signs out of Xbox LIVE\n5) The user signs back into Xbox LIVE before returning to the Press Start screen\n6) The user signs back in and then is stuck signing out on the Xbox Guide Blade\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must be signed back into Xbox LIVE when selecting to do so.\n\nNote: \n1) The user is able to close the Blade, and then attempt to sign in again.\n2) This also occurs in the Menu System, but with a lower frequency.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4489,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,8,3,1,1223337600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Exhibition - Woodsball - Match Summary: Additional scorings for 7v7 Center Flag match must be removed','Summary: \nDuring Exhibition, in any Woodsball (Center Flag; 7v7 match), additional scorings must be removed\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter Exhibition\n2) Select Center Flag as the gametype\n3) Select the 7v7 player match\n4) Press the 2 Button to select Woodsball\n5) Enter to the Match Summary Screen\n6) The following texts appear:\n\n\"Scoring:\nRound win: 1 point\n\n7 Points for each elimination,\n3 points for each survivor\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Scoring:\nRound win: 1 point\"\n\nBy removing the points for elimination and survivor\n\nNOTES(1): The scoring for elimination and survivor must also be removed for any 3v3 and 5v5 Center Flag Matches in all Speedball and Woodsball level','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4490,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,3,1,1223337600,0,0,0,3,'(30%-39%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Dynasty Training Drills: The user completes the objective to dive into a snake bunker without sliding behind the bunker','Summary:\nOccasionally, during Dynasty Training Drills, in Fitness Drills, in Stage 2, if the user\'s character dives but does not reach the snake bunker, the bunker is still counted as completed\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Dynasty Training Drills on the Main Menu\n2) Progresses to the Fitness Drills\n3) Proceeds into Stage 2 of the Fitness Drills\n4) Dives towards the designated snake bunker\n5) Immediately dives towards the next bunker, but does not reach it\n6) Occasionally, the user\'s character still completes the bunker\n\nExpected Results:\nThe objectives for each stage must not be completed until the user\'s character does the proper actions','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4491,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223337600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Exhibition - Woodsball - Train Depot Field (Center Flag): Opponents are unable to retrieve the flag nearby trains','Summary: \nDuring Exhibition, in Woodsball - Train Depot Field (Center Flag), if the user captures the center flag and gets eliminated nearby a train, the flag drops/clips inside the train and the opponents are unable to retrieve the flag\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter Exhibition\n2) Select the Center Flag gametype\n3) Select and enter Woodsball, in Train Depot Field\n4) Capture the center flag\n5) Get eliminated next to a train\n6) The flag drops/ or clips inside the nearby train\n7) Continue gameplay and lose all of the user\'s teammates\n8) Observe that the opponents cannot retrieve the flag\n\nExpected Results:\nOpponent\'s must be able to capture the flag\n\nNOTES(1): Video is available; (Part 1: User grabs the flag and gets eliminated near a train; Part 2: The opponents eliminate the user\'s team and cannot retrieve the flag)','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4493,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,9,3,1,1223424000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Collision Detection - Gameplay: The user\'s character clips into the snake bunkers','Summary:\nDuring Gameplay, if the user\'s character jumps on top of the snake bunkers, goes into prone stance, crouches or stands from the prone stance, the user\'s character clips into the snake bunker\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects any mode of gameplay\n2) Proceeds into any level with snake bunkers\n3) User\'s character enters prone stance\n4) Crouches or stands from prone stance\n5) The user\'s character clips into the snake bunker and frequently becomes stuck inside the snake bunker\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user\'s character must not clip into the snake bunkers\n\nNote: The user\'s character is able to get out of the bunker by entering prone stance and crawling off the bunker\\\nNote: Video capture is available','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4495,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: Games that are not full, do not disappear from the Games list, after entering gameplay.','Summary:\nGames that are not full, do not disappear from the Games list, after entering gameplay. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates default player match game.\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s game.\n3) Users progress to gameplay.\n4) From the main menu, User 3 selects multiplayer.\n5) User 3 selects Xbox LIVE.\n6) User 3 selects Player Match.\n7) User 3 selects Join Game.\n8) User 3 presses the A button to Search, with default filters.\n9) User 3 observes User 1\'s game appear on the games list until the observed game is terminated in any way.\n\nExpected Results:\nGames must no longer appear on the games list after they have entered gameplay. \n\nNotes:\n1) This game remains on the Games List for at least 5 minutes after entering gameplay, it only disappeared when the game was completed.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4496,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 006 - Multiplayer: Users observe a static screen that varies in length (dependant on the number of games hosted) after pressing \"Y\" to Refresh the Games List.','Summary: \nUsers observe a static screen that varies in length (dependant on the number of games hosted) after pressing \"Y\" to Refresh the Games List.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Users 1-4 each host a default Capture the Flag - Player Match.\n2) User 5 selects Multiplayer.\n3) User 5 selects Xbox LIVE\n4) User 5 selects Player Match.\n5) User 5 selects Join Game.\n6) User 5 presses \"A\" on the Join Game screen.\n7) The Games List appears.\n8) User 5 presses the Y (Refresh) button, and a ~8 second static screen before the games list appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe screen must not be static.\n\nGames must not pause without game-representative on-screen graphics. When the pause time is greater than five seconds, the game must indicate the reason and provide on-screen animation. This is a violation of TCR 006.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4497,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 006 - Multiplayer: A ~3 second black screen appears after dismissing the \"Disconnected from Xbox LIVE\" error','Summary:\n~3 second black screen appears after dismissing the \"Disconnected from Xbox LIVE\" error\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match or Ranked Match.\n2) The Player pulls the network cable from their Xbox 360 console.\n3) The \"Disconnected from Xbox LIVE\" message appears.\n4) The Player selects Ok, and the a ~3 second black screen appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nGames must not pause without game-representative on-screen graphics. When the pause time is greater than five seconds, the game must indicate the reason and provide on-screen animation. This is a violation of TCR 006.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4506,1224288000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer Player Match Lobby: Invite Menu is incorrectly implemented','Summary:\nIn the Multiplayer Player Match Lobby, the Invite Menu is incorrectly implemented.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From The Multiplayer Player Match Lobby,\n2) The following navigational prompt appears:\n\n\"[Y button Graphic] Invite\"\n\nExpected Results:\nRemove this prompt and its functionality.\n\nNotes:\n1) Invites can be done through the Xbox Guide Blade, the current implementation does not work and must be removed.','jhh\n','[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/18/2008 02:43:32 AM]\nVerified open on the 10/17 build. Issue occurs with the same steps.test\n',''),(4508,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: In game GUI appears vertically stretched in 4:3 video resolution','Summary:\nIn 4:3 video resolution, the in game GUI appears vertically stretched.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, with the Xbox 360 console Video Resolution set to 4:3,.\n2) The GUI appears vertically stretched.\n\nExpected Results:\nIn game GUI must appear properly for all video resolutions.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(4512,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Woodsball - Tippmann Field (Center Flag) - Flag can become stuck when dropped near the set of three wooden spools.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Woodsball map type, in Tippmann Field (Center Flag), the flag becomes stuck after a player retrieves the flag, proceeds towards the set of three wooden spools and then gets eliminated while positioned between the spools.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter gameplay, Exhibition.\n2) Change game type to Woodsball, Center Flag.\n3) Select Tippmann Field.\n4) Capture the center flag.\n5) Proceed out of the flag building to the right.\n6) Proceed up to the set of three wooden spools.\n7) Position User\'s Character in between two of them.\n8) Allow User\'s Character to become eliminated.\n9) Observe that the flag drops inside object.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe flag must be retrievable at all times.\n\nNote:\nVideo attached showing location and occurrence of opponent unable to retrieve flag.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4514,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Woodsball - San Diego Field(Center Flag) - Flag can become stuck when dropped near the middle oil platform.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Woodsball map type, in San Diego Field (Center Flag), the flag becomes stuck after a player retrieves the flag, proceeds towards the middle oil platform near the flag spawn point, and then gets eliminated while positioned against the oil platform.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter gameplay, Exhibition.\n2) Change game type to Woodsball, Center Flag.\n3) Select San Diego Field.\n4) Capture the center flag.\n5) Position User\'s Character against the middle oil platform nearby.\n6) Allow User\'s Character to become eliminated.\n7) Observe that the flag drops inside object.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe flag must be retrievable at all times.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4517,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Crash - Multiplayer: When exiting a match after the Controller was initially disconnected upon entering gameplay','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer, when the Client exits a match after initially entering gameplay with a disconnected Controller, the game will hard crash on the Multiplayer Menu.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Lobby, any mode,\n2) Clients join.\n3) A Client disconnects the Controller.\n4) The Host starts the match.\n5) Gameplay begins.\n6) The Client reconnects the Controller during gameplay.\n7) The Host presses START (pause) button.\n8) The Host selects Quit Match.\n9) The Client recieves the Host Disconnected message.\n10) The Client is returned to the Multiplayer Menu crashed with a hard lock.\n\nExpected Results:\nPlayers must not crash when controller disconnects have occurred.\n\nNotes:\n1) This occurs in all Multiplayer Game Types: System Link, Ranked Match, Player Match.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4518,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Multiplayer Player Match Lobby: The Player disconnected the Controller and the game hard crashed','Summary:\nOnce, in the Multiplayer Player Match lobby, the Player disconnected the Controller, and the game hard crashed.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Main Menu, with an Player Match created.\n2) The Client selected Join Game.\n3) The Client entered the Player Match Lobby.\n4) The Player disconnected the Controller.\n5) A hard crash occurred.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must properly handle Controller disconnects.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4519,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Woodsball - Gold Mine Field (Center Flag) - Flag can become stuck when dropped at the large tree near friendly spawn point.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Woodsball map type, in Gold Mine Field (Center Flag), the flag becomes stuck after a player retrieves the flag, proceeds towards the large tree left of the friendly spawn point, and then gets eliminated while positioned against the side closest to the friendly spawn point.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter gameplay, Exhibition.\n2) Change game type to Woodsball, Center Flag.\n3) Select Gold Mine Field.\n4) Capture the center flag.\n5) Proceed to the largest tree positioned near the edge of the field, directly left from the friendly spawn point.\n6) Position User\'s Character on the side closest to the friendly spawn point.\n7) Allow User\'s Character to become eliminated.\n8) Observe that the flag drops inside object.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe flag must be retrievable at all times.\n\nNote(1):Video attached showing location of tree. \nNote(2): Bug occurs within the map at other locations with the same tree model.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4550,1223424000,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Woodsball - Train Field (Center Flag) - Flag can become stuck when dropped at the large building near the flag spawn point.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Woodsball map type, in Train Field (Center Flag), the flag becomes stuck after a player retrieves the flag, proceeds towards the building near the flag spawn point, positions on the wall facing the AI\'s spawn point, and gets eliminated while positioned against the wall.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter gameplay, Exhibition.\n2) Change game type to Woodsball, Center Flag.\n3) Select Train Field.\n4) Capture the center flag.\n5) Proceed to the building near the flag spawn point.\n6) Position User\'s Character on the wall facing the AI\'s spawn point.\n7) Allow User\'s Character to become eliminated.\n8) Observe that the flag drops inside object.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe flag must be retrievable at all times.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4561,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Multiplayer: The game crashed when the Host disconnected their Xbox 360 Controller after disconnected their ethernet cable','Summary:\nThe game crashed when the Host disconnected their Xbox 360 Controller after disconnected their ethernet cable\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match, with the Player as the host.\n2) The Player removed their ethernet cable.\n3) The \"Disconnected from Xbox LIVE\" message appeared.\n4) The Player disconnceted their Xbox 360 Controller.\n5) The Player reconnected their Xbox 360 Controller.\n6) The Player selects Ok.\n7) A Loading Screen appeared.\n8) The \"No clients left, returning to menus\" message appeared.\n9) The Player selected OK, and the game become unresponsive to any Controller input.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash after a Player disconnects their Xbox 360 Controller.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4589,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: Xbwatson reports a Rich Presence error when the Host exits the Match Lobby','Summary:\nXbwatson reports a Rich Presence error when the Host exits the Match Lobby\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Match Lobby, Ranked Match or Player Match, with XbWatson monitoring the Xbox 360 console.\n2) The Player presses the B (Back) button.\n3) The Player selects Yes, and XbWatson reports the following error:\n\n\"WARNING: XSessionDelete called for a presence enabled session\n(XSESSION_CREATE_USES_PRESENCE) that was never started. Please ensure that\nXSessionStart and XSessionEnd are always called on a presence enabled session\nwhen a Live multiplayer game takes place to ensure accurate reporting of\nmultiplayer usage data.\"\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not call XSessionDelete() before a call to XSESSION_CREATE_USES_PRESENCE().','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4593,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Gameplay: Xbwatson reports errors for idle Controllers when in Xbox LIVE Gameplay','Summary:\nXbwatson reports errors for idle Controllers when in Xbox LIVE Gameplay\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Ranked Match or Player Match, with XbWatson Montoring the Xbox 360 console and the Player using Controller 1.\n2) The following text appears in the XbWatson output:\n\n\"WRN[XGI]: Non-signed-in index passed to XUserGetANID. (dwUserIndex=1\nWRN[XGI]: Non-signed-in index passed to XUserGetANID. (dwUserIndex=2\nWRN[XGI]: Non-signed-in index passed to XUserGetANID. (dwUserIndex=3\n\"\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not pass indexes to non-signed in Users.\n\nNotes:\n1) This also occurs in career mode.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4598,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Gameplay - Career Mode - Tournament: When the User is not signed in to a Gamer Profile and eliminates an opponent, \"John Doe\" appears onscreen.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, while signed out of a Gamer Profile for Player 1 and signed in to a Gamer Profile with Player 2, when Player 1 eliminates an opponent the text \"John Doe\" appears on the bottom left of the screen instead of the Player Character\'s name.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Sign in to a Gamer Profile with Controller 2,\n2) With Controller 1 signed out of a Gamer Profile, press START on the Press Start screen,\n3) Press the \"B\" button on the controller,\n4) Select \"Continue Without Saving\",\n5) Start a New Game,\n6) Select any character from Character Selection (make a mental note of the selected character\'s name),\n7) Select any team,\n8) Select any difficulty,\n9) Select Career Mode,\n10) Select Play Tournament,\n11) Select any map,\n12) Observe that when an opponent is shot, the text \"John Doe eliminated an opponent\" appears on the bottom left of the screen instead of the name of the Player Character that was previously selected.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe text \"John Doe\" must not appear when the User is signed out of a Gamer Profile and shoots an opponent during gameplay. The name of the selected Player Character should appear.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4599,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Gameplay - Career Mode - Tournament: When the User is signed in as a Guest, no text appears when an opponent is eliminated.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Career Mode, Tournament with the User signed in with a Guest Profile, when the Guest User eliminates an opponent, no text appears onscreen to indicate that the Guest User has done so.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Sign in as a Guest with Controller 1,\n2) Press START on the Press Start screen,\n3) Select \"Continue Without Saving\",\n4) Begin a New Game,\n5) Select a character on the Character Selection screen,\n6) Select any team,\n7) Select any difficulty,\n8) Select Career Mode,\n9) Select Play Tournament,\n10) Select any map,\n11) Observe that when the Guest User eliminates an opponent, no text appears to indicate that the Guest User has done so.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Guest User\'s name must appear and the Guest User must be informed when an opponent is successfully eliminated.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4609,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Multiplayer Ranked Match: The Player crashed loading into a match','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer Ranked Match, the Player crashed upon loading into the match.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Ranked Match Multiplayer Lobby, with a Woodsball game hosted,\n2) 3 Clients joined.\n3) The host selected Start Game.\n4) Upon loading into the game, the Client crashed.\n\nExpected Results:\nClients must not crash loading into Multiplayer Matches.\n\nNotes:\n1) The Crash dump is available on the FTP.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4612,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video Graphic - Gameplay: The Right Bumper and the Right Trigger, cause the User\'s character to shoot with the incorrect finger.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, the controls to shoot, the (Right Bumper) causes the User\'s character to shoot with his bottom finger and the (Right Trigger) causes the User\'s character to shoot with his top finger.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter any match,\n2) Press the (Right Bumper), \n3) Press the (Right Trigger),\n4) Observe that the User\'s character will move the wrong finger to shoot the marker.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe controls must trigger the correct graphical reaction on the User\'s character.\n\nNOTE(1): The bumper should function the top finger, and the trigger should function the lower finger.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(4614,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Menu System: The Rich Presence for the Menu System is incorrect','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence for the Menu System is incorrect\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in and a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence.\n2) The Player Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"Browsing the menu\nProfile menus\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Browsing the menu\"\n\nby removing the text \"Profile menus\".\n\nIn active gameplay, games must update presence information. Presence information must accurately reflect the player’s state. This is a violation of TCR 070.\n\nNotes:\n1) This is PreCert TCR 070 Issue 1 of 2.','jhh\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/19/2008 11:29:59 AM]\nThis issue still occurs in the 10.17.08 X360 build. The issue has been updated.test\n',''),(4621,1223424000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: Bunkers appear on the wrong side of the fence on the ending flyby.','Summary: \nDuring gameplay, when the camera is outside of the playing field at the end of the match during the ending flyby, the User observes the bunkers appear to be sitting in front of the fence and the fence appears to be in the background instead of the foreground.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) from the Main Menu, enter any Speedball event,\n2) Win the event,\n3) Observe the bunkers appear to be in the foreground and the fence appears to be in the background on the ending flyby when the camera is out side of the playing area.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll environmental objects must appear properly.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(4635,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Menu System: The Post-earned text for the Achievement \"Woodsball Chief\" is incorrectly displayed','Summary:\nThe Post-earned text for the Achievement “Woodsball Chief” is incorrectly displayed.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Gamer Profile signed in that has earned the \"Woodsball Chief\" Achievement.\n2) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n3) The Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n4) The Player selects the Gamer Profile.\n5) The Player selects View Games.\n6) The Player selects Paintball 2009.\n7) The Player selects the Achievement Woodsball Chief, and the following Post-earned text appears: \n\n“Won at least 50 Woodsball matches over Xbox LIVE”\n\nChange to:\n\n“Won at least 50 Woodsball Ranked Matches over Xbox LIVE”\n\nBy changing the text \"matches\" to the text \"Ranked Matches\".','jhh\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/24/2008 09:01:15 PM]\nThis issue still occurs in the 10.22.08 X360 build. The issue has been updated.test\n',''),(4642,1223510400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,3,'(40%-49%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Exhibition - Custom Field - Center Flag Match: Flag becomes stuck inside of large cone bunkers out of reach for NPCs.','Summary:\nOccasionally, during gameplay in a Custom Field in a Center Flag Match, when the user\'s teams flag carrier is eliminated near a large cone bunker the flag clips inside of the bunker and is out of reach for NPCs.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Created a custom Field with many large cone bunkers,\n2) Entered gameplay in the Custom Field in a Center Flag Match,\n3) Moved user\'s character to the flag\n4) Took the flag\n5) Moved near a large cone bunker,\n6) User\'s character was eliminated,\n7) Observed that the flag was clipping the large cone bunker and that the Enemy NPC was unable to reach the flag.\n\nExpected Results:\nEnemy NPCs must be able to reach the flag and return it to score.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4650,1223510400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,2,'(80%-89%)','Frequently - Gameplay - Exhibition - Custom Match - Center Flag Match: Enemy NPCs become stuck on 8ft Tetrahedron bunkers.','Summary:\nFrequently, during gameplay in a custom field with 25 8ft tetrahedron bunkers, if the user\'s character picks up the flag, moves into a highly bunker populated area, get shot, drops the flag, has the rest of the user\'s team become eliminated, user observes that the enemy NPC frequently could not retrieve the flag because the NPC was stuck on a bunker.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter the Field Creator,\n2) Make a field with all 8ft tetrahedron bunkers,\n3) Save the field,\n4) Enter the newly created level in an exhibition 7vs7, Center Flag Match, match,\n5) After the round begins move the user\'s character to the flag,\n6) Take the flag and move to an area with many bunkers,\n7) Become eliminated,\n8) Have the rest of the user\'s team become eliminated,\n9) Observe that frequently the enemy NPCs will be stuck on bunkers and unable to return the flag.\n\nExpected Results:\nEnemy NPCs must not become stuck on bunkers, and must be able to return the flag.\n\nNote(1) \nVideo availible.\n\nNote(2)\nField layout image attached.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4651,1223510400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,17,3,1,1223424000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Options - Exhibition - Woodsball: The Automatic Fire option does not save properly','Summary: \nDuring Exhibition, in any Woodsball, in gameplay, if the user enters the options menu, turns on the Automatic Fire, returns to gameplay and exits out of the game, returns to main menu, saves the profile, resets the console, loads the same profile, enters into a Woodsball match again, the Automatic Fire option is turned off\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter Exhibition, in any Woodsball\n2) Press the 2 Button to enter the Pause Menu\n3) Select Options\n4) Select Gameplay\n5) Turn on Automatic Fire\n6) Return to gameplay\n7) Press and hold the Z Button to confirm Automatic Fire\n8) Exit out of the game\n9) Return to the main menu and perform a save\n10) After saving is completed, reset the Wii system\n11) Load from the save\n12) Enter into any Woodsball match again\n13) Return to the gameplay options\n14) Observed that the Automatic Fire is now turned off\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Automatic Fire must save properly','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4652,1223510400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,2,'(50%-59%)','Frequently - Gameplay - Exhibition - Custom Match - Center Flag Match: Enemy NPCs become stuck on 6ft Tetrahedron bunkers.','Summary:\nFrequently, during gameplay in a custom field with 25 6ft tetrahedron bunkers, if the user\'s character picks up the flag, moves into a highly bunker populated area, get shot, drops the flag, has the rest of the user\'s team become eliminated, user observes that the enemy NPC frequently could not retrieve the flag because the NPC was stuck on a bunker.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter the Field Creator,\n2) Make a field with all 6ft tetrahedron bunkers,\n3) Save the field,\n4) Enter the newly created level in an exhibition 7vs7, Center Flag Match, match,\n5) After the round begins move the user\'s character to the flag,\n6) Take the flag and move to an area with many bunkers,\n7) Become eliminated,\n8) Have the rest of the user\'s team become eliminated,\n9) Observe that frequently the enemy NPCs will be stuck on bunkers and unable to return the flag.\n\nExpected Results:\nEnemy NPCs must not become stuck on bunkers, and must be able to return the flag.\n\nNote(1) \nVideo availible.\n\nNote(2)\nField layout image attached.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4656,1223510400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,3,'(10%-19%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Exhibition - Custom Field - Center Flag Match: Flag becomes stuck inside of a wide cylinder-shaped bunkers out of reach for NPCs.','Summary:\nOccasionally, during gameplay in a Custom Field in a Center Flag Match, when the user\'s teams flag carrier is eliminated near a wide cylinder-shaped bunker the flag clips inside of the bunker and is out of reach for NPCs.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Created a custom Field with 25 Gravitron bunkers,\n2) Entered gameplay in the Custom Field in a Center Flag Match,\n3) Moved user\'s character to the flag\n4) Took the flag\n5) Moved near a bunch of wide cylinder-shaped bunkers,\n6) User\'s character was eliminated,\n7) Observed that the flag clipped into a Gravitron bunker and that the enemy NPC was unable to reach the flag.\n\nExpected Results:\nEnemy NPCs must be able to reach the flag and return it to score.\n\nNote(1) \nNPCs seem to have a hard time navigating the field with out the flag clipping into the bunker.\n\nNote(2)\nVideo available and Picture of the field layout attached.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4664,1223510400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,8,3,1,1223424000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Gear Store: Change the Bob Long Rapper barrel length stat from \"12in\" to \"14in\".','Summary:\nIn the Gear Store, the length stats for the Bob Long Rapper barrel appear as \"12in\".\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu select Career Mode\n2) Select Gear Store\n3) Highlight the Bob Long Rapper barrel\n4) The Length stat appears as:\n\n\"12in\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"14in\"\n\nBy changing \"12in\" to \"14in\".','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4665,1223510400,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Gameplay - Woodsball - Gold Mine Field: Opponent became stuck picking up center flag, near mine-cart','Summary:\nOnce, during a woodsball exhibition, in the Gold Mine Field, the opponent became stuck with the center flag, after the user\'s character was eliminated with the flag in-between the central barn and the opponent\'s flag station, near a mine cart.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, user selected Exhibition.\n2) Set up a 7 vs. 7, seven round, center-flag exhibition between The Coalition and Dynasty.\n3) Selected Gold Mine Field.\n4) User\'s character navigated immediately towards the central barn.\n5) Picked Up central flag.\n6) Navigated towards opponents flag station .\n7) User\'s character was eliminated close to the the opponent\'s bunker near a mine-cart, just past the barn.\n8) Remainder of user\'s characters were eliminated.\n9) Opponent picks up center flag.\n10) Once, user observed that the opponent was stuck and could not return the center flag to the correct location to complete the match.\n\nExpected Results:\nOpponent(s) must not get stuck picking up or carrying the center flag.\n\nNote():\nVideo-documentation available.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4677,1223510400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Multiplayer Ranked Match: Host crashed upon returning to the Multiplayer Main Menu','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer Ranked Match, the Host crashed upon returning to the Multiplayer Main Menu after all Clients had exited the match.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in a Multiplayer Ranked Match, with 4 Clients.\n2) The Host eliminated all of the opponents.\n3) The Results screen appeared.\n4) All Clients selected Continue\n5) The Host selected Continue.\n6) The Multiplayer Menu appeared.\n7) The Host crashed with a hard lock\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Host must not crashed upon returning to the Multiplayer Main Menu.\n\nNotes:\n1) No Crash Dump is available as none was generated.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4678,1223510400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The User\'s Characters shadow does not disappear if the User is eliminated at the end of the round.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, any Game Mode, any level, if the User\'s Character is shot and the game ends before the User\'s Character disappears as the User\'s Character disappears the character\'s shadow remains. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Game Mode,\n2) Select any any level, \n3) During gameplay allow the character to be eliminated at the end of the round,\n4) Observe the characters shadow remains on the ending flyby even though the character has disappeared\n\nExpected Results:\nThe shadows must be accurate to the environmental objects during gameplay.\n\nNOTE(1): This is a timing specific bug but it happens very often during gameplay if the User is an aggressive player.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(4682,1223510400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 085 - Multiplayer Ranked Match: The Player is unable to submit Player Reviews and view detailed Player stats at the end of a Match','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer Ranked Match, the Player is unable to submit Player Reviews and view detailed Player Stats at the end match Results Screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in a Ranked Multiplayer Match.\n2) The Players complete the match.\n3) The Results screen appears.\n4) The Player is unable to view detailed Player stats and submit Player Reviews.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must be allowed to view their own detailed Player stats regarding the Match, and submit Player Reviews.\n\nGames that support post-game lobbies must provide the player the ability to directly submit a player review at the end of the game session for the 100 most recent players. This is a violation of TCR 085.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4683,1223510400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 085 - Multiplayer Player Match: The Player is unable to submit Player Reviews and view detailed Player stats at the Results screen','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer Player Match, the Player is unable to submit Player Reviews and view detailed Player Stats at the end match Results Screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in a Multiplayer Player Match.\n2) The Players complete the match.\n3) The Results screen appears.\n4) The Player is unable to view detailed Player stats and submit Player Reviews.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must be allowed to view their own detailed Player stats regarding the Match, and submit Player Reviews.\n\nGames that support post-game lobbies must provide the player the ability to directly submit a player review at the end of the game session for the 100 most recent players. This is a violation of TCR 085.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4685,1223510400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer System Link: The results screen does not contain detailed Player stats','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer System Link, the Player is unable to view detailed Player stats on the Results screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in a System Link Match, any mode,\n2) The Player complete the match.\n3) The Results screen appears.\n4) The Players are unable to view detailed Player stats regarding the Match.\n\nExpected Results:\nIndividual Players must be allowed to view their Player stats regarding matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4714,1223510400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Field Creator: The Rich Presence for the Field Creator does not appear properly','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence for the Field Creator does not appear properly.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Field Creator, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in and a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence.\n2) The Player\'s Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"LAN - Speedball\nLocation 1/20\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"In the Field Creator\"\n\nby replacing the first set of text with the second set of text.\n\nIn active gameplay, games must update presence information. Presence information must accurately reflect the player’s state. This is a violation of TCR 070.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4731,1223510400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,14,5,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Comment - Gear Store: The user should be able to compare the stats of gear in the gear store compared to the gear they have equipped','Suggestion:\nWhile in the gear store, the user should be able to compare the stats of the gear available in the gear store compared to the gear they currently have equipped. The way it is set up now, the user has no way of comparing these stats.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4739,1223510400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,2,'(80%-89%)','Frequently (80% - 89%) - Crash - Tournament 6 - XPSL Victorville: If the user presses the [A button] after losing a match in Tournament 6 - XPSL Victorville, the game will crash','Summary:\nFrequently, if the user presses the [A button] (to skip the flag-running cutscene) after losing a match in Tournament 6 - XPSL Victorville, the game will crash.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n2) Choose Play Tournament,\n3) Choose the XPSL tournament in San Bernadino, California,\n4) Play through a match and allow the enemy team to win,\n5) When the option \"Press A to Skip\" appears on the bottom of the screen, press the [A button],\n6) Observe that the game crashes.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash.\n\nNOTE(1): An Xbox Xenon Crash Dump is available on the FTP in the following location:\n/Paintball/X360 Crash Dumps\n\n- PB_#4739.rar','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4743,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Dynasty Training Drills: The Rich Presence for the Dynasty Training Drills does not appear properly','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence for the Dynasty Training Drills does not appear properly\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Dynasty Training Drills, any level, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in and a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence.\n2) The Player\'s Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"LAN - Speedball\nHouston, Texas\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Dynasty Training Drills\n<X> Stage <N>\"\n\nby replacing the first set of text with the second set of text.\n\nIn active gameplay, games must update presence information. Presence information must accurately reflect the player’s state. This is a violation of TCR 070. \n\nNotes:\n1) \"<X>\" denotes the kind of stage, \"Accuracy\", \"Fitness\", or \"Leaning and Snapping\". (I would simplify \"Leaning and Snapping\" to \"L. and S.\"\n2) \"<N>\" denotes the number of the stage, 1, 2, 3, 4, or 5.','jhh\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/19/2008 05:30:40 PM]\nThis issue still occurs in the 10.17.08 X360 build. The issue has been updated.test\n',''),(4745,1223510400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,2,'(90%-99%)','Frequently - Video/Graphic - Career Mode - Charlotte, North Carolina: Frequently, in the 3v3 match, the friendly AI\'s marker barrels clip through the bunkers','Summary:\nFrequently, during gameplay in Career Mode, in the Division 2 3v3 match in Charlotte, North Carolina, the friendly AI\'s marker barrel clips through the bunkers.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Career Mode.\n2) Select Play Tournament, select Charlotte, North Carolina (the first map).\n3) Dismiss the Instructions Screen to begin gameplay.\n4) When gameplay begins, follow the friendly AI that appears on the user\'s left to the bunker, and observe that frequently, his marker barrel clips through the bunker.\n\nExpected Results:\nMarker barrels must not clip through the bunkers.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(4830,1223596800,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,2,1,1223424000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Field Creator: The user is able to place more bunkers then what is specified causing the game to crash.','Summary:\nIn the Field Creator, if the user places the maximum amount of single bunkers (25), and then highlights a bunker and selects the splitter tool, changing the single bunker into 4 bunkers, and then repeats this to all the single bunkers, they are able to place 100 bunkers onto the field which results in a infinite loading screen when trying to play the map from Exhibition Mode.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu select Field Creator\n2) Select any map\n3) Delete all the preset bunkers by repeatedly pressing the Square button\n4) Place single bunkers down 35 times (Smaller bunkers of the same type make the following steps easier)\n5) Use the left stick to navigate to any single bunker\n6) Use the directional pad to highlight and change the splitter tool to 4 bunkers instead of 1\n7) Move the 4 bunkers with the right stick to a placeable location on the map\n8) Navigate to another single bunker with the left stick\n9) Repeat steps 6 - 8 until all the single bunkers have been replaced with 4 bunkers\n10) Press the Start button\n11) Select Store Custom Field\n12) Select any Slot\n13) Name the map and select Done\n14) Select Exit and return back to the Main Menu\n15) Select Exhibition \n16) Press the A button to continue with any of the match settings and teams\n17) Press 2 to change to Custom maps\n18) Select the newly created map\n19) The game crashes in an infinite loading screen\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must not be able to place more then the designated amount of bunkers on a field.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(4903,1223596800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 061 - Multiplayer: A Player with their Player-created content flag set to Blocked can join games with Custom Maps','Summary:\nA Player with their Player-created content flag set to Blocked can join games with Custom Maps\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Player Match Games List, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in with their Player-created Content flag set to blocked and a hosted, joinable game on a Custom Map.\n2) The Player highlights the game.\n3) The Player presses the A (Join) button, and the Match Lobby appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen the Player has their player-created content flag set to blocked and they attempt to join a game on a Custom Map, the following message must appear:\n\n\"You cannot join the selected game. You cannot view Custom Created content.\"\n\nGames must not receive any player-created content if the player-created content viewing flag is turned off. This is a violation of TCR 061.\n\nNotes:\n1) This PreCert TCR 061 Issue 1 of 1.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(4928,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','1st Party Standards - Tournament Bracket: The User is unable to unlock all Gear Store Content.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Tournament Bracket, if the User\'s Character plays through all career mode tournaments getting 1st on each tournament played, due to gear being unlocked from specific tournaments in the multi tournaments that become locked the User appears unable to unlock all content for the Gear Store.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Career Mode, select Tournament,\n2) Complete all tournaments in 1st place.\n3) Observe that due to the the non selected tournament for the multi tournaments becoming locked the User appears unable to unlock all content for the Gear Store.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser must be able to complete previously locked tournaments upon completing the final tournament.','jhh\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/12/2008 06:19:22 PM]\nThere was never intended to unlock all the gear from the 1st pass thoughout the game. For replayability reasons, if the player wants to get all items in the game he must play career again\n\n[George Batog (AMP Production) -- 10/12/2008 06:30:06 PM]\nThis is not what we discussed. The final unlock of the double tournaments should have been implemented. This should have been forwarded as WNF because of insufficient time.\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/17/2008 07:41:02 PM]\nok\n\n[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/19/2008 09:02:08 AM]\nWe need an unlock list - if the Player cannot get all the Markers to unlock the Achievement, this causes a violation of TCR 073.\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/20/2008 06:34:45 AM]\nThe final unlock of the double tournaments was not the initial design but a last-minute patch.\nSee FTP folder /Paintball/AMP QA Bug Captures and Dumps/4928 - xls/ for the unlock gear file that has been provided to us.\n\n[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/20/2008 08:41:02 AM]\nIs file accurate to the current implementation, or is your implementation different?\n\nIn any case, unlocked markers (and gear) DO NOT CARRY OVER between careers, and should not.\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/20/2008 11:04:22 AM]\nThe file is for current implementation.\nIt\'s the same file we\'ve sent you over a month ago.\nUnlocked markers do not carry over, that\'s true. However, this does not mean that you ca not play with all the markers in the game because you simply have to buy the markers you did not buy in the previous Career. You can even play the Career ten times, each marker you\'ve bought and used over the ten Careers are tracked and recorded as such.\n\n[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/20/2008 01:36:58 PM]\nWhere is this information tracked? In the saved game? In the Gamer Profile?test\n',''),(5008,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,4,1223596800,0,0,0,2,'(60%-69%)','Frequently - Gameplay: The AI players do not move from the spawn point on a custom field','Summary:\nFrequently, during Exhibition, on a Custom Field full with bunkers, some of the AI players do not move from the spawn point\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Field Creator on the Main Menu\n2) Proceeds into the Field Creator\n3) Fills the map with 35 bunkers\n4) Saves the custom field\n5) Returns to the Main Menu\n6) Selects Exhibition\n7) Selects Capture the Flag or Center Flag\n8) Selects the saved Custom Field \n9) Proceeds into gameplay\n10) Frequently, the 2 to 3 of the AI players on each side to not move from the spawn point\n\nExpected Results:\nAI players must function properly at all times\n\nNote: Screen shots of custom fields attached\n\nNote: Save Data is attached.','jhh\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/13/2008 01:17:22 AM]\nplease send saves with the map you create and have problems\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/14/2008 09:10:43 PM]\nClose - Fixed with 10/13/08 PS3 build.\n\n[Thanuvong Yang (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/19/2008 07:29:31 PM]\nCNV due to bug 5934\n\n[Thanuvong Yang (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/24/2008 07:52:43 PM]\nUnable to reproduce in build 10/23/08\n\n[Thanuvong Yang (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 04:17:50 PM]\nVerified open build 10/28/08test\n',''),(5056,1223683200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Game Lobby: The bots are not clearly identifiable as bots','Summary:\nThe bots are not clearly identifiable as bots.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Match Lobby, any game mode, with at least one bot present.\n2) The bots names appears like any other name.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe bot\'s names must be clearly identifiable as being not human controlled, but adding the text \"Bot\" to their names.\n\nImplementation notes:\n1) The names can be changed to Red Bot 1, Yellow Bot 1, to clearly identify both that they are bots, and what team they are on when playing.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5132,1223769600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 119 - Menu System - Multiplayer: There is no Ranked leaderboard for Ranked Capture the Flag','Summary:\nIn the Ranked Leaderboards Menu, there is no Ranked Leaderboard for Capture the Flag.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu,\n2) The Player selects Xbox LIVE.\n3) The Player selects Leaderboards.\n4) There is no Leaderboard for Ranked Capture the Flag.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Ranked Leaderboard for Capture the Flag must be displayed as :\n\n\"Ranked Capture the Flag\"\n\nGames that support ranked sessions must support a minimum of one arbitrated leaderboard per each ranked game mode. Games must allow the player access to the leaderboards from within the game’s UI. This is a violation of TCR 119.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5133,1223769600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 119 - Menu System - Multiplayer: There is no Ranked Leaderboard for Ranked Center Flag.','Summary:\nIn the Ranked Leaderboards Menu, there is no Ranked Leaderboard for Center Flag.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu,\n2) The Player selects Xbox LIVE.\n3) The Player selects Leaderboards.\n4) There is no Leaderboard for Ranked Center Flag.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Ranked Leaderboard for Center Flag must be displayed as :\n\n\"Ranked Center Flag\"\n\nGames that support ranked sessions must support a minimum of one arbitrated leaderboard per each ranked game mode. Games must allow the player access to the leaderboards from within the game’s UI. This is a violation of TCR 119.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5151,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 093 - Multiplayer: Voice Chat continues when a Voice Communication Blocked Gamer Profile is signed in as an idle Gamer Profile','Summary:\nVoice Chat continues when a Voice Communication Blocked Gamer Profile is signed in as an idle Gamer Profile \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in a Player Match or Ranked Match, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in as the active Gamer Profile and an idle Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in with their voice communication set to blocked.\n2) The Player is able to send and recieve voice chat.\n\nGames must not transmit text chat, voice chat, or video chat when the communication privilege is turned off. In cases in which multiple players are signed in on one console, games must respect the most restrictive communications settings among all users. This includes situations in which the most restrictive settings are set for a gamer that is \"idle\" in a session (that is, signed in to the console but not actively participating in the session). This is a violation of TCR 093.\n\nNotes:\n1) This occurs for both Player and Ranked Matches. \n2) This is PreCert TCR 093 Issue 1 of 1.','jhh\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/19/2008 02:07:52 PM]\nThis issue still occurs in the 10.17.08 X360 build. No change.test\n',''),(5152,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 094 - Multiplayer: Voice Chat continues when a Voice Communication Friends Only Gamer Profile is signed in as an idle Gamer Profile','Summary:\nVoice Chat continues when a Voice Communication Friends Only Gamer Profile is signed in as an idle Gamer Profile\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in a Player Match or Ranked Match, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in as the active Gamer Profile and an idle Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in with their voice communication set to Friends Only.\n2) The Player is able to send and recieve voice chat.\n\nGames must only allow communication between friends when the friends-only communication privilege is on. In cases in which multiple players are signed in on one console, games must respect the most restrictive communications settings among all users. This includes situations in which the most restrictive settings are set for a gamer that is \"idle\" in a session (that is, signed in to the console but not actively participating in the session). This is a violation of TCR 094.\n\nNotes:\n1) This occurs for both Player and Ranked Matches. \n2) This is PreCert TCR 094 Issue 1 of 1.','jhh\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/19/2008 02:16:22 PM]\nThis issue still occurs in the 10.17.08 X360 build. No change.test\n',''),(5159,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Ranked Matchs: The Rich Presence is incorrect for Ranked Matches','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence is incorrect for Ranked Matches \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, any Ranked Match, with a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence.\n2) The Player\'s Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"Online - Speedball\nLocation 1/20\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Ranked Match - <X>\n<N>\n\nby replacing the first set of text with the second set of text.\n\nNotes:\n1) \"<X>\" refers to the gametype - CTF, CF, or Elim.\n2) \"<N>\" refers to the name of the level.','jhh\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/17/2008 04:51:26 AM]\nRich presence cannot have texts longer than 22 characters.\nThe proposed implementation won\'t work; text is longer than 22 characters.\n\n[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/17/2008 09:33:02 AM]\nShortened the gametypes to fit the text restriction.test\n',''),(5160,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Player Matchs: The Rich Presence is incorrect for Player Matches','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence is incorrect for Player Matches \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, any Player Match, with a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence.\n2) The Player\'s Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"Online - Speedball\nLocation 1/20\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Player Match - <X>\n<N>\n\nby replacing the first set of text with the second set of text.\n\nNotes:\n1) \"<X>\" refers to the gametype - CTF, CF, or Elim.\n2) \"<N>\" refers to the name of the level.','jhh\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/17/2008 04:48:18 AM]\nRich presence cannot have texts longer than 22 characters.\nThe proposed implementation won\'t work due to the fact that is longer than 22 characters.\n\n[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/17/2008 09:34:36 AM]\nShortened the gametypes to fit the text restriction.test\n',''),(5161,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - System Link: The Rich Presence is incorrect for System Link games','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence is incorrect for System Link games\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, any System Link game, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in and a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence.\n2) The Player\'s Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"LAN - Speedball\nLocation 1/20\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"System Link - <X>\n<N>\n\nby replacing the first set of text with the second set of text.\n\nNotes:\n1) \"<X>\" refers to the gametype - CTF, CF, or Elim.\n2) \"<N>\" refers to the name of the level.','jhh\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/17/2008 04:46:35 AM]\nRich presence cannot have texts longer than 22 characters.\nThe proposed implementation won\'t work; both are longer than 22 characters.\n\n[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/17/2008 09:35:04 AM]\nShortened the gametypes to fit the text restriction.test\n',''),(5183,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,4,1223596800,0,0,0,3,'(20%-29%)','Occasionally - Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: One Client was initially unable to see the flag in a Center Flag or Capture The Flag game, all the large flag-indicator arrows appeared inanimate, and the Client\'s teammate(s) had no Player Names or indicators.','Summary:\nOccasionally, in Multiplayer, one Client was initially unable to see the flag in a Center Flag or Capture The Flag game, all the large flag-indicator arrows appeared inanimate, and the Client\'s teammate(s) had no Player Names or indicators.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, selected Multiplayer,\n2) User 1 (Host) created any game,\n3) Users 2-4 joined User 1\'s game,\n4) Users entered gameplay,\n5) From each of their respective starting positions, Users navigated their Avatars to the flag located in the middle of the level (Center Flag) or on the opposite side of the field (Capture The Flag),\n6) One of the Clients observed no visible flag, the large flag-indicator arrows located at the flag and at each of the bases were not animated, and the User\'s teammates had no Player Names or indicator arrows.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe flag must appear for all Users, the large flag-indicator arrows must appear animated for all Users, and Users must be able to see Player Names and indicators above teammates.\n\nNOTE(1): The 1st Client on the Yellow-team side is usually the Client for which this bug occurs.\nNOTE(2): When this bug occurs, it only occurs for the beginning round and for that Client only. Also, once the flag is picked up, the Client will then see the flag if it is subsequently dropped.\nNOTE(3): This bug occurs with fewer Players, but the frequency is lower.\nNOTE(4): This issue occurs in all game modes.\nNOTE(5): More easily reproduced at San Diego Field - Woodsball, in a Center Flag match.\nNOTE(6): May be related to issue 5568.','jhh\n','[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/24/2008 06:03:56 PM]\nVerified on 10.23.08 build.\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/27/2008 01:45:07 PM]\nIssue Verified on 10.26.08 build.\n\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 04:19:02 AM]\nVerified in the 10/28 buildtest\n',''),(5241,1223856000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 050 - New Game Menu: The game doesn\'t use the XUI to handle low storage conditions','Summary:\nThe game doesn\'t use the XUI to handle low storage conditions \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the New Game/Load Game Menu, with a Gamer Profile signed in and a Storage Device present that is full.\n2) The Player selects New Game.\n3) The Character Selection Menu appears.\n4) The Player selects a character.\n5) The Difficulty Selection Menu appears.\n6) The Player selects a difficulty.\n7) The No Storage Device selected message appears.\n8) The Player selects Select Storage Device.\n9) The Select a Device Blade appears.\n10) The Player selets the full Storage Device, and the Save Game Menu appears.\n\nWhen selecting a Storage Device to save to, the XUI must properly detect the Low Storage Space condition, and return the expected error using the Blades.\n\nGames must provide an option that allows the player to select any available storage device for saving game data. If no device is selected, the game must notify the player that no game data will be saved. The notification must occur before any potential data loss. This is a violation of TCR 050.\n\nNotes:\n1) When loading, the game does not need to detect for Low Storage Space, as the save has already been created.\n2) This also occurs when selecting Save from the Main Menu.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5243,1223856000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The user\'s character does not remove the lid to the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity while reloading','Summary:\nDuring Gameplay, with the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity hopper equipped, if the user\'s character reloads, the user\'s character does not remove the lid to the hopper\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects any mode of gameplay on the Main Menu, with the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity hopper equipped\n2) Selects any location\n3) Proceeds into gameplay\n4) User\'s character fires at least one shot\n5) Reloads the hopper\n6) The user\'s character does not remove the lid to the hopper before reloading\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user\'s character must reload the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity properly, removing the lid before reloading the hopper and then replace the lid after reloading','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5244,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Team Manager (Menu System): The text description under any character\'s Communication bar contains errors','Summary:\nDuring the Team Manager menu, while any player\'s Communication bar is highlighted, the phrase \"Command reaches __ closest team mates\" (the blank spot has a number from 2-6 depending on the character\'s level) appears. This phrase contains text errors.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n2) Choose Team Manager,\n3) Select any character,\n4) Press the [X button] to adjust the character\'s points,\n5) Scroll down to the Communication bar,\n6) Observe that the following phrase appears,\n\n\"Command reaches __ closest team mates\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Commands reach __ closest teammates\"\n\nby adding an \"s\" on the end of \"command,\" removing the \"es\" from the end of \"reach,\" and combining the words \"team\" and \"mates\" into one word.','jhh\n','[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 05:42:47 PM]\nVerified on the 10/22/08 X360 Build.test\n',''),(5245,1223856000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 006/TCR 095 - New Game Menu: Selecting Continue causes a static screen for ~41 seconds after pulling the uplink cable','Summary:\nSelecting Continue causes a static screen for ~41 seconds after pulling the uplink cable\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the New Game/Load Game/Continue Menu, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in and a Storage Device that contains a saved game.\n2) The Player removes the uplink cable.\n2) The Player quickly selects Continue, and a static screen appears for ~41 seconds before the Main Menu appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nGames must not pause without game-representative on-screen graphics. When the pause time is greater than five seconds, the game must indicate the reason and provide on-screen animation. This is a violation of TCR 006.\n\nNotes:\n1) The \"uplink cable\" is the cable that connects the router to the internet, not the \"ethernet cable\", that connects the Xbox 360 console to the router.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5246,1223856000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 006/TCR 095 - Load Game Menu: Loading a game causes a static screen for ~23 seconds after pulling the uplink cable','Summary:\nLoading a game causes a static screen for ~23 seconds after pulling the uplink cable\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Load Game Menu, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in and a Storage Device that contains a saved game.\n2) The Player removes the uplink cable.\n3) The Player quickly selects any saved game.\n4) The Player selects Yes, and a static screen appears for ~23 seconds before the Load Successful message appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nGames must not pause without game-representative on-screen graphics. When the pause time is greater than five seconds, the game must indicate the reason and provide on-screen animation. This is a violation of TCR 006.\n\nNotes:\n1) The \"uplink cable\" is the cable that connects the router to the internet, not the \"ethernet cable\", that connects the Xbox 360 console to the router. \n2) This is PreCert TCR 095 Issue 1 of 2.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5247,1223856000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,3,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,2,'(60%-69%)','Frequently (60% - 69%) - Gameplay - Gameplay: NPC characters face the wrong direction on the course just before the user\'s character takes control','Summary:\nFrequently, during gameplay, on any 7 vs. 7 match, if the user\'s character is eliminated and forced to take control of a crouching NPC player, the NPC will turn around and face the wrong way on the course just before the user takes over.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode, Quick Play, or Exhibition,\n2) Choose any 7 vs. 7 match,\n3) During gameplay, attempt to get eliminated as soon as possible,\n4) When the user is about to take control of a crouching NPC player, observe that the NPC turns and faces the wrong direction.\n\nExpected Results:\nNPC characters will behave properly at all times.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5248,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Career: Opposing team AI always has a set direction of attack','Summary:\nIn Career Gameplay, the opposing team AI always uses the same directional attacks of attacking left for Semi-Finals and attacking right for Finals.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in a Career Semi-final match.\n2) The Player observes the AI always attacking from the left.\n3) During a Finals match, the AI always is attacking from the right.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe paths at which the AI attacks should be random as to not create repetition.','jhh\n','[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 05:42:47 PM]\nVerified on the 10/22/08 X360 Build.test\n',''),(5254,1223942400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Team Manager: The Left Trigger icon appears too close to the edge of the text boundary box','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in the Team Manager Menu, on the left side of the screen, the Left Trigger icon appears too close to the right edge of the text boundary box, and the placement is inconsistent compared to the positioning of the Right Trigger icon on the right side of the screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Career Mode.\n2) Select Team Manager.\n3) When the Team Manager Menu appears, observe that on the left side of the screen, the Left Trigger icon and the \"Field\" text appears too close to the right edge of the text boundary box, and the placement is inconsistent compared to the positioning of the Right Trigger icon and \"Help\" text on the right side of the screen.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Left Trigger icon and \"Field\" text must be moved to the right so that the placement is consistent compared to the positioning of the Right Trigger icon and \"Help\" text that appears on the right side of the screen.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5263,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: At the Load Map Screen, the Left Bumper icon appears larger than the Right Bumper, and is off center from the text boundary box','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Field Creator, on the Load Map Screen, the Left Bumper icon appears larger than the Right Bumper, and is off center from the text boundary box.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Field Creator.\n2) When the Load Map Screen appears, observe the bottom center of the screen; the Left Bumper icon appears larger than the Right Bumper, and is off center from the text boundary box.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Left Bumper icon must be scaled down so that it is the same size as the Right Bumper icon, and moved to the left so that the curve on the bumper lines up with the curved line on the boundary area.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached. New screenshot attached for 10/22 build.','jhh\n','[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/20/2008 08:25:04 AM]\nVerified on the 10/17/08 build.\n\n[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 05:42:47 PM]\nVerified on the 10/22/08 X360 Build.test\n',''),(5269,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Match Description: Upon disconnecting the active controller the message to reconnect the controller appears corrupted.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Match Description, if the User has one or more controllers connected to the Xbox 360, then goes to Career Mode, then Tournament Play, then selects any tournament, then proceeds through the screens until reaching the Match Description screen, and then disconnects the active controller the message to reconnect the controller appears corrupted.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Attach one or more controllers to the Xbox 360,\n2) Boot the game and set any controller to be the active controller at the initial interactive,\n3) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n4) Select Tournament Play,\n5) Select any tournament,\n6) Proceed through the screens that appear until reaching the Match Description screen,\n7) Disconnect the active controller,\n8) Observe that the message to reconnect the controller appears to be corrupted.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe message to reconnect the controller must appear properly.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\n','[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 05:44:34 PM]\nVerified on the 10/22/08 X360 Build.test\n',''),(5272,1223856000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,17,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Options - Movement Options: The Vibration on/off option appears in the Movement Options Menu','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in the Options Menu, under the Movement Options, the Vibration on/off option appears, when it should appear in the Gameplay Options Menu.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Options.\n2) Select Movement.\n3) Observe that the Vibration on/off option appears, but has nothing to do with movement.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Vibration on/off option must be removed from the Movement Options Menu, and placed in the Gameplay Options Menu.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5291,1223856000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The User\'s Character\'s finger repeatedly moves when holding the RT button.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, any game mode, any level, if the user holds the RT button, the User observes the User\'s Character\'s finger repeatedly moves.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the the main Menu, select any game mode,\n2) Select any level,\n3) Hold down on the RT button,\n4) Observe the User\'s Character\'s finger repeatedly moves.\n\nExpected Results:\nTrigger must appear to be properly pulled.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5360,1223942400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 015 - Gameplay: Idle Gamer Profile sign In or out causes the Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile to be returned to the Multiplayer Menu','Summary:\nIdle Gamer Profile sign In or out causes the Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile to be returned to the Multiplayer Menu\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match or Ranked Match, with an Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile signed into Xbox LIVE on Controller 1,\n2) The Player signs into an Idle Gamer Profile with Controller 2.\n3) The Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile is returned to the Multiplayer Menu.\n\nExpected Results:\nSign ins and sign outs with idle Gamer Profiles must not affect the active Gamer Profile.\n\nGames must properly detect and handle player profiles signing in or out in all areas of the game. This is a violation of TCR 015.\n\nNotes:\n1) This is PreCert TCR 015 Issue 1 of 1.\n2) This also occurs for sign outs.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5363,1223942400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 022 - Menu System: The Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed for 4 seconds when entering gameplay before the loading screen appears','Summary:\nThe Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed for 4 seconds when entering gameplay before the loading screen appears\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu.\n2) The Player selects Quick Player.\n3) The Quick Play Menu appears.\n4) The Player selects any map.\n5) The Player quickly presses the Xbox Guide button, and the Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed for ~2 seconds to ~4 seconds.\n\nExpected Results:\nGames must ensure that system UI can be rendered at least every 66 milliseconds in all areas of the game for any display mode. This is a violation of TCR 022.\n\nNotes:\n1) This is PreCert TCR 022 Issue 1 of 1.\n2) This occurs for all transitions to the loading screen prior to entering gameplay.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5368,1223942400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 115 - Front End: The game does not accurately handle accepted Game Invites or Joins from outside of the game','Summary:\nThe game does not accurately handle accepted Game Invites or Joins from outside of the game\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Xbox Dashboard, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in and a hosted Xbox LIVE Player Match and the Paintball 2009 disc present.\n2) The Host sends a Game Invite to the Player.\n3) The Player accepts the Game Invite.\n4) The Game begins, and the Player is not moved to the Match Lobby.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must correctly handle invites and move the Player to the Match Lobby.\n\nGames must allow players to send game invites for player match game sessions. Games must also allow players to join player match sessions. This is a violation of TCR 115.\n\nNotes:\n1) This is PreCert TCR 115 Issue 2 of 2.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5369,1223942400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 115 - Menu System: The game does not correctly handle Game Invites to idle Players','Summary:\nThe game does not correctly handle Game Invites to idle Players\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in on an idle Xbox 360 Conttoller, and a hosted Xbox LIVE Player Match.\n2) The Host sends a Game Invite to the idle Player.\n3) The idle Player accepts the Game Invite, and nothing occurs.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must display a confirmation message accessible by the active Gamer Profile to confirm that the invite can be accepted, and then change the active Gamer Profile to the Idle Gamer Profile, join the Player Match, without carrying over the current game state from the previous active Gamer Profile.\n\nGames must allow players to send game invites for player match game sessions. Games must also allow players to join player match sessions. This is a violation of TCR 115.\n\nNotes:\n1) This is PreCert TCR 115 Issue 1 of 2. \n2) This also occurs in Gameplay.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5371,1223942400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 095 - Multiplayer: The game enters an unresponsive state for ~80 seconds when the uplink cable has been disconnected for the Host','Summary:\nThe game enters an unresponsive state for ~80 seconds when the uplink cable has been disconnected for the Host\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match or Ranked Match, with the Player as the Host.\n2) The Player removes the uplink cable, and the game becomes unresponsive for ~80 seconds before a message appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must correctly handle network disconnections and display an appropriate message.\n\nGames must properly detect and handle loss of network connectivity in all areas of the game. This is a violation of TCR 095.\n\nNotes:\n1) This is PreCert TCR 095 Issue 2 of 2.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5372,1223942400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 095 - Multiplayer: The game enters an unresponsive state for ~20 seconds when the uplink cable has been disconnected for the Client','Summary:\nThe game enters an unresponsive state for ~20 seconds when the uplink cable has been disconnected for the Client\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match or Ranked Match, with the Player as the Client.\n2) The Player removes the uplink cable, and the game becomes unresponsive for ~20 seconds before a message appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must correctly handle network disconnections and display an appropriate message.\n\nGames must properly detect and handle loss of network connectivity in all areas of the game. This is a violation of TCR 095.\n\nNotes:\n1) This is PreCert TCR 095 Issue 2 of 2.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5390,1223942400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,8,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Tournament 22a - Millennium MAXS CPL European Masters: On the Results Screen following the tournament, the tournament title overlaps a white line near the top of the screen','Summary:\nOn the Results Screen following the Millennium MAXS CPL European Masters tournament, the tournament title text slightly overlaps a white line near the top of the screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n2) Choose Play Tournament,\n3) Choose Tournament 22a - Millennium MAXS CPL European Masters,\n4) Play through the tournament normally,\n5) After the tournament ends, look at the final Results Screen,\n6) Observe that the tournament title appears to be slightly too high on the screen.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll elements of the Results Screen must appear properly aligned.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5418,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,4,1223856000,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally (1%-9%) - Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: The user experienced a rapidly flashing HUD while in Spectator Mode after being eliminated','Summary:\nOccasionally (1%-9%), the user experienced a rapidly flashing HUD while in Spectator Mode after being eliminated.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 Created a Multiplayer, Online, Player Match with default settings,\n2) 13 Clients joined User 1\'s game,\n3) Proceeded to Gameplay,\n4) Users eliminated each other,\n5) At least 1 user observed a rapidly flashing HUD during spectator mode after being eliminated.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must not experience a Flashing HUD in spectator mode after being eliminated during a match.\n\nNOTE(1): Once, the user experienced a Crash while the HUD was flashing during spectator mode after being eliminated.\n\nNOTE(2): Full crash dump uploaded to FTP','jhh\n','[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/25/2008 07:44:40 AM]\nVerified on 10.23.08 build. Issue only occurred while a DSL/Cable was hosting on a at-home connection. Crash did not occur.\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/27/2008 01:45:07 PM]\nIssue Verified on 10.26.08 build.test\n',''),(5423,1224028800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Gameplay - Jacksonville, Florida: The bottom right Massive Ad does not appear properly','Summary:\nIn Jacksonville, Florida gameplay, the bottom right Massive Ad does not appear properly.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Jacksonville, Florida, with the Player connected to Xbox LIVE and the Massive Ad server,\n2) The Player proceeds to the bottom right Massive ad billboard.\n3) The Massive Ad does not appear properly.\n\nExpected Results:\nMassive Ads must appear properly during gameplay.\n\nNotes:\n1) The screenshots attached highlight this issue.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5424,1224028800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Gameplay - Jacksonville, Florida: The bottom left Massive Ad does not appear properly','Summary:\nIn Jacksonville, Florida gameplay, the bottom left Massive Ad does not appear properly.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Jacksonville, Florida, with the Player connected to Xbox LIVE and the Massive Ad server,\n2) The Player proceeds to the bottom left Massive Ad billboard.\n3) The Massive Ad does not appear properly.\n\nExpected Results:\nMassive Ads must appear properly during gameplay.\n\nNotes:\n1) The screenshots attached highlight this issue.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5494,1224028800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Gameplay - Miami, Florida: The bottom left Massive Ad does not appear properly','Summary:\nIn Miami, Florida gameplay, the bottom left Massive Ad does not appear properly.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Miami, Florida, with the Player connected to Xbox LIVE and the Massive Ad server,\n2) The Player proceeds to the bottom left Massive Ad billboard, and a static billboard appears instead of a Massive Ad.\n\n\nExpected Results:\nMassive Ads must appear properly during gameplay.\n\nNotes:\n1) The screenshots attached highlight this issue.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5495,1224028800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Gameplay - Miami, Florida: The Massive Ad next to the crane does not appear properly','Summary:\nIn Miami, Florida gameplay, the Massive Ad next to the crane does not appear properly.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Miami, Florida, with the Player connected to Xbox LIVE and the Massive Ad server,\n2) The Player proceeds to the crane with the Massive Ad billboard, and a static billboard appears instead of a Massive Ad.\n\n\nExpected Results:\nMassive Ads must appear properly during gameplay.\n\nNotes:\n1) The screenshots attached highlight this issue.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5496,1224028800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Gameplay - Miami, Florida: The bottom right Massive Ad does not appear properly','Summary:\nIn Miami, Florida gameplay, the bottom right Massive Ad does not appear properly.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Jacksonville, Florida, with the Player connected to Xbox LIVE and the Massive Ad server,\n2) The Player proceeds to the bottom right Massive Ad billboard, and a static billboard appears instead of a Massive Ad.\n\nExpected Results:\nMassive Ads must appear properly during gameplay.\n\nNotes:\n1) The screenshots attached highlight this issue.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5498,1224028800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,9,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Collision Detection - Gameplay: User\'s Character appears to be able to partially clip into the large cone bunkers.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, if the User\'s selects a field with at least one Large Cone Bunkers, then moves their character to the side of the bunker while crouched, then while facing the the bunker moves towards it part of the character appears to clip into and see through the Large Cone Bunker.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n2) Select Tournament Play,\n3) Select Tournament 1 - East Coast Invitational,\n4) Eliminate all opponents and take flag,\n5) Walk next to the Large Cone Bunker,\n6) Position character to face the bunker,\n7) Place character into a crouching position,\n8) Move character towards the bunker,\n9) Observe that the User\'s Character appears to clip into the bunker.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe User\'s Character must not clip into the bunkers.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshots attached,\nNOTE(2): Eliminating the opponents and capturing the flag is not necessary, but it does make checking this bug easier.\nNOTE(3): Field chosen does not matter so long as it has a Large Cone Bunker.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5520,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Team Manager: The Player can field 10 players','Summary:\nThe Player can field 10 players\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Team Manager Menu, with 10 players unlocked.\n2) The Player can field all ten players at the same time.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must only be able to field 7 players at a time.','jhh\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/17/2008 04:43:57 AM]\nSome tournament types allows fielding more than 7 players which are then sheffled around in between rounds.\nThere are at no time more than 7 players in the field.\n\n[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/17/2008 09:38:08 AM]\nThe Player is told they cannot enter a Tournament with more than 7 Players fielded.\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/18/2008 12:44:32 PM]\nwe do not understand what is the issue.\nthere are tournament formats allowing the player to shuffle players between rounds and these allow to begin the game with 10 players.\n\n[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/19/2008 09:03:28 AM]\nThere are tournaments that allow you to select any of your unlocked teammates inbetween rounds. However, there are no tournaments in the game that allow you to enter with all of your teammates fielded.\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/20/2008 06:29:35 AM]\nSure, that\'s true.\nThere are not tournamentsin the game that allow you to play with more than 7 players. You do however have the hole team pool to choose from inbetween rounds. The 7 fielded players in the begining define the players that begin the game on the field.\nDo you think that we should have a better wording that using \"Field\" and \"Bench\" terms?\nThanks.\n\n[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/20/2008 08:43:25 AM]\nThere is nothing wrong with the terminology. The Player must not be allowed to Field more Players than he can ever take into a tournament (seven), as it causes unneccessary navigation to the Team Manager.test\n',''),(5531,1224028800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Quick Play - Speedball - Las Vegas, Nevada: Once, game crashed after recieving a disconnected from host message','Summary:\nOnce, during gameplay in Quick Play, in the Las Vegas, Nevada tournament, after the 3rd round, the user received a disconnected from host message, and the game became unresponsive.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, selected Quick Play.\n2) Selected the Las Vegas, Nevada tournament.\n3) Dismissed the Instructions Screen to begin gameplay.\n4) The user won the 1st round, lost the 2nd round, and won the 3rd round.\n5) After the Results Screen appeared in the 3rd round, the user received a \"Disconnected from host\" message.\n6) User pressed the XBox Guide button to dismiss the message.\n7) User observed the Main Menu appeared, but the game was unresponsive when the user attempted to navigate the Main Menu.\n\nExpected Results:\nIn Quick Play, the user must not receive a disconnected from host message, and the game must not crash after receiving the message.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot of message attached.\nNOTE(2): No crash dump was available as the game hard locked.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5568,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,4,1223856000,0,0,0,3,'(30%-39%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Multiplayer: At least one player in a Ranked Match did not see Player Names over their teammates.','Summary:\nOccasionally, at least one player in a Ranked Match did not see Player Names over their teammates.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer, Play Online menu, User 1 hosted a default Ranked Match,\n2) Users 2-4 joined User 1\'s Ranked Match lobby,\n3) Users progressed into gameplay,\n4) Occasionally, at least one User did not observe a Player Name over their teammate.\n\nExpected Results:\nUsers must be able to identify their teammates by their Player Names.\n\nNote(1): Issue also occurs with more than four players.\nNote(2): The flag does not appear and the large pulsing flag indicator arrow is stationary when this issue occurs (may be related to issue 5183).','jhh\n','[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/24/2008 06:03:56 PM]\nVerified on 10.23.08 build.\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/27/2008 01:45:07 PM]\nIssue Verified on 10.26.08 build.\n\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 04:19:02 AM]\nVerified in the 10/28 buildtest\n',''),(5596,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Gameplay: Massive Ads do not properly update when the Player connects to Xbox LIVE after the game starts.','Summary:\nMassive Ads do not properly update when the Player connects to Xbox LIVE after the game starts.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in but not connected to Xbox LIVE.\n2) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n3) The Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n4) The Player selects Connect to Xbox LIVE.\n5) The Player is connected to Xbox LIVE.\n6) The Player closes the Xbox Guide Blade.\n7) The Player enters gameplay, any level, and static ads appear where the Massive Ads normally appear.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe in game Massive Ads must update properly when the Player is connected to Xbox LIVE and the Massive Ad server.\n\nNotes:\n1) This issue also occurs if the Player selects an alternate map or gametype.\n2) This also appears if the Player reconnects during gameplay.','jhh\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/23/2008 06:46:23 PM]\nThis issue still occurs in the 10.22.08 X360 build. No Change.test\n',''),(5623,1224115200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Leaderboards: Scrolling through pages does not function properly in the Leaderboards','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer Leaderboards, when the Player scrolls up from Rank 26, it defaults the Player highlighting to Rank 1.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu, with 26 Ranks filled in the Ranked Multiplayer Speedball Elimiinations Leaderboards.\n2) The Player selects Ranked.\n3) The Player selects Leaderboards.\n4) The Player selects Multiplayer Speedball Eliminations.\n5) The Player scrolls down to rank 26.\n6) The Player scrolls up one position.\n7) The Player is defaulted to highlighting Rank 1.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen the Player scrolls up from Rank 26, it should highlight Rank 25.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5625,1224115200,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator - SC Village: Drink bottles appear highly visible through the mesh fence','Summary:\nIn Field Creator SC Village, the drink bottles appear highly visible through the mesh fence.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Field Creator SC Village.\n2) The Player presses Y (fly through) button.\n3) The Player proceeds to the edge of the mesh fence, and the drink bottles appear highly visible through it.\n\nExpected Results:\nDrink bottles must appear properly behind the mesh fence.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5626,1224115200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,2,'(90%-99%)','Frequently - Crash - Multiplayer: During a 4 player Center Flag match, on the Round Results screen the Host will crash.','Summary:\nFrequently, during gameplay, System Link, if the User creates 2 player Center Flag match on the Round Results screen, the Host crashes.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer menu, User 1 hosts a default Center Flag System Link match.\n2) Users 2-14 join Host\'s game,\n3) One team completes the round by bringing the Center Flag to their opponent\'s base,\n4) Observe the host appears to crash on the Round Results screen.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash during a System Link match.\n\nNOTE(1): There are crash dumps uploaded to this bug.\nNOTE(2): The client also appears to crash, but at a lower frequency.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5632,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator - SC Village: The Player is able to see outside of the level while in fly through mode','Summary:\nIn Field Creator SC Village, the Player is able to see outside of the level in the bottom right corner of the level.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Field Creator SC Village, \n2) The Player presses Y (Flythrough) button.\n3) The Player proceeds to the corner with the yellow tent and bleachers.\n4) The Player flies upwards and is able to see outside of the level.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must not be allowed to see outside of the level.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.\n2) This issue will also occur in Multiplayer, when a Player is eliminated and enters Fly through mode.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5683,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,3,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally (1%-9%) - Gameplay - Multiplayer: With Gamertags enabled, friendly AI characters\' names stayed on screen after the character was eliminated','Summary:\nOccasionally, during Multiplayer gameplay with bots and Gamertags enabled, friendly bots\' names stayed on screen after they were eliminated.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, the host and clients selected Multiplayer,\n2) The host selected any map,\n3) The host chose Capture the Flag,\n4) He then enabled Gamertags,\n5) He added the maximum amount of bots,\n6) During gameplay, the users eliminated all the bots,\n7) The users then observed that friendly bots\' names occasionally stayed on screen and were listed on the HUD as still being active.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll bots must properly disappear when eliminated.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5685,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator - SC Village: Objects outside of the field pop in and out when the Player is on the opposite end of the field','Summary:\nIn Field Creator SC Village, the objects outside of the field pop in and out when the Player is on the opposite end of the field.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in SC Village,\n2) The Player observes that objects outside of the field pop in and out when the Player is on the opposite end of the field.\n\nExpected Results:\nObjects must not pop in and out while the Players are on the field.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5686,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - SC Village: A banner pole is clipping through the benches','Summary:\nIn SC Village, a banner pole appears clipping through the benches on the right side of the map.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in SC Village,\n2) The Player proceeds to the right of the map.\n3) The Player proceeds to the middle banner.\n4) The pole appears clipping through the bench.\n\nExpected Results:\nPoles must not clip through benches.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5689,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - San Jose California: pizza and drink bottles appear floating','Summary:\nIn San Jose California, a pizza box and drink bottles appear floating.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in San Jose California,\n2) From the Yellow Team spawn, the Player proceeds left to the mesh fence.\n3) A pizza box and drink bottles appear floating.\n\nExpected Results:\nA table must be added for the pizza box and drink bottles to sit on.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5690,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - San Jose California: Banner poles clip through the top of a tent','Summary:\nIn San Jose California, the poles of a banner clip through the top of a tent, in the area with all of the tents lined up.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in San Jose California,\n2) The Player proceeds to the mesh fence where all the tents are located.\n3) The Poles of a banner are clipping through the top of the tent.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe poles must be moved as to not clip through the top of tents.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5694,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - San Jose California: Floating pizza boxes appear inside tents','Summary:\nIn San Jose California, floating pizza boxes appear inside of the large brown tents.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in San Jose California,\n2) The Player proceeds to the large brown tents by the stands.\n3) Pizza boxes appear floating inside of the tents.\n\nExpected Results:\nPizza boxes must not appear floating.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5713,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - Paris France: A building in the background appears off the level','Summary:\nIn Paris France, a building in the background appears off the level edge.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Paris France,\n2) The Player navigates to where the large house is located.\n3) The smaller building to the left of it appears off the edge of the level.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe level must not appear to abruptly end to the Players view.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\ntesting\n','[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 05:44:34 PM]\nVerified on the 10/22/08 X360 Build.test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5718,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Gameplay: AI characters are unable to jump over beam bunkers','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in any Speedball match, the AI characters are unable to jump over the beam bunkers.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select any mode of play.\n2) Select any Speedball match.\n3) Dismiss the Instructions Screen to begin gameplay.\n4) During gameplay, observe that the AI characters do not jump over beam bunkers, and run around them instead.\n\nExpected Results:\nAI characters must be able to jump over beam bunkers.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5722,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator - Malaga Spain: The Player is able to see the edge of the level','Summary:\nIn Field Creator Malaga Spain, the Player is able to see the edges of the level.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) In Field Creator, Malaga Spain,\n2) The Player presses Y (fly through) button.\n3) The Player proceeds to the area with the ocean.\n4) The Player looks towards the corners and is able to see the edges of the level.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe level must appear naturally to the Player, and the edges must be conceled.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5732,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: When the Player flies upward, the Player is able to view the edges of levels','Summary:\nIn Field Creator, when the Player is in Fly Through mode, and proceeds upwards, the Player is able to view the edges of the levels.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During fly through mode in Field Creator, any level,\n2) The Player proceeds upwards with the camera.\n3) The Player is able to view the edges of levels.\n\nExpected Results:\nLevels must be designed in such a manner to not allow the Player to view the edges of levels.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5733,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1223251200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - San Diego California: Palm trees in the background partially appear','Summary:\nIn San Diego California, palm trees in the background partially appear.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in San Diego California,\n2) The Player views the palm trees towards the buildings, and they appear only partially depending on where the Player is on the field.\n\nExpected Results:\nPalm trees must appear properly during gameplay.\n\nNotes:\n1) The image attached highlights this issue.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5734,1224201600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1223251200,0,0,0,4,'','Twice - Crash - XPSL Nevada - Preliminary Match 3: After all teammates are eliminated by opposing team and pressing the \"A\" button to skip the scene, the game crashed.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, in XPSL Nevada, after all members of the Player Team are eliminated, the Player pressed the \"A\" button to skip the scene of the opponent capturing the Player\'s flag when the text \"Press A to skip\" was displayed. After pressing \"A\" on the controller, the game crashed with a fatal system error.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Begin the XPSL Nevada Tournament,\n2) Allow all teammates to be eliminated by the opposing team,\n3) When the text \"Press A to skip\" appears on screen, press the \"A\" button on the controller,\n4) Observe that the game crashes with a fatal system error.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash when the Player presses \"A\" to skip the scene of the opposing team capturing the Player Team\'s flag.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5737,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,2,4,1224028800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer : The users experience extreme amounts of lag during gameplay when the host is connected via a cable/dsl connection.','Summary:\nThe users experience extreme amounts of lag during gameplay when the host is connected via a cable connection.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host, connected via a cable connection, creates a default multiplayer match\n2) 13 clients joins the game lobby\n3) Gameplay appears\n4) The users experience extreme amounts of lag during gameplay\n\nExpected Results:\nThe users must not experience large amounts of lag during multiplayer gameplay when the host is connected via a cable connection.\n\nNote: Because of the lag multiple issues occur including:\n-Cheat meters do not appear until user\'s are already in spectator mode.\n-Delay when attempting to pick up opponent flag.\n\nNote: The following was the connection type used:\nRouter: D-Link 802.11g/2.4ghz\nm/n: DL 524\nModem: Terayon \nM/N: TJ715X','jhh\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/23/2008 09:46:39 PM]\nChanges have been made to prevent this to happening again. Please check on the latest build to see if this issue has beend fixed. Thanks\n\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 04:57:46 PM]\nThe lag still occurs when a DSL/Cable connection hosts a game. Mainly the characters moved at such a choppy pace that it made the game unplayable. However we did not run into the marker dissapearing or the loading screen coming in going white and blue.\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/24/2008 06:03:56 PM]\nVerified on 10.23.08 build.\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 04:46:56 PM]\nSpeedball lag has improved greatly. However woods ball seems to have a few lag issue depending on who is hosting, and how their connection is. See below:\n\nWoods ball Field Lag – 1 to 5 (5 being 10.26 lag)\nBrent: 15740 kb/s down, 2819 kb/s up (Comcast Cable)\nDoua: 6194 down, 753 up (Qwest DSL)\n\nTippman Field\nBrent Host: 1\nDoua Host 4\nLag drops to a 1 rating when 9-10 people remain in gameplay.\n\nJungle Park\nBrent host: 1\nDoua Host: 2\n\nSan Diego Field\nBrent host: 1\nDoua Host: 2\n\nTrain Depot –\nBrent Host: 1\nDoua Host: 4\nLag drops to a 1 rating when 9-10 people remain in gameplay.\n\nGold Mine Field\nBrent Host: 1\nDoua Host: 3test\n',''),(5767,1224288000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic: Multiplayer - Woodsball, San Diego Field, power lines above the level appear with corrupt graphics.','Summary: During gameplay of a multiplayer match on Woodsball, San Diego Field, power lines above the level appear with corrupt graphics.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates an Xbox LIVE player match on Woodsball, San Diego Field.\n2) User 2 joins user 1\'s game.\n3) User 1 starts the game, gameplay begins for all users.\n4) Users observe the power lines that cross the center of the level.\n5) Users observe the power lines appear with corrupt graphics.\n\nExpected Results: The power lines on this level must appear correctly.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5768,1224288000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic: Multiplayer - San Diego Field, users observe the house near the yellow team flag base is partially sunk into the ground.','Summary: During gameplay of a multiplayer match on San Diego Field, users observe the house near the yellow team flag base is partially sunk into the ground.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates an Xbox LIVE player match on the San Diego Field woodsball level.\n2) User 2 joins user 1\'s game.\n3) User 1 starts the game, gameplay begins for all users.\n4) User 2(yellow team) observes the house in front of and to the left of their flag base.\n5) User 2 observes the house is partially sunk into the ground.\n\nExpected Results: The specified house must not be partially sunk into the ground.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5793,1224288000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic: Multiplayer - Woodsball, Jungle Park, the small wooden shack appears partially sunk into the ground.','Summary: During gameplay of a multiplayer match on Woodsball, Jungle Park, the small wooden shack appears partially sunk into the ground.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates any multiplayer match on Woodsball, Jungle Park.\n2) User 2 joins user 1\'s game.\n3) User 1 starts the game, gameplay appears for all users.\n4) Users navigate their characters to the small wooden shack.\n5) Users observe the shack is sunk partially into the ground.\n\nExpected Results: The wooden shack must appear correctly.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5794,1224288000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic: Multiplayer - Woodsball, Gold Mine Field, the small wooden shack appears partially sunk into the ground.','Summary: During gameplay of a multiplayer match on Woodsball, Gold Mine Field, the small wooden shack appears partially sunk into the ground.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates any multiplayer match on Woodsball, Gold Mine Field.\n2) User 2 joins user 1\'s game.\n3) User 1 starts the game, gameplay appears for all users.\n4) Users navigate their characters to the small wooden shack.\n5) Users observe the shack is sunk partially into the ground.\n\nExpected Results: The wooden shack must appear correctly.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5814,1224288000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Woodsball - San Diego Field: All powerlines on the map are graphically corrupt','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, on San Diego Field, all the power lines strung above the map are graphically corrupt.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Exhibition,\n2) Select any game type,\n3) Choose Woodsball,\n4) Select San Diego Field,\n5) When gameplay begins, look up at the sky near the middle of the map,\n6) Observe that the power lines in this area are graphically corrupt.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll areas of the environment must appear properly.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5819,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,4,'','Twice - TCR 015 - Gameplay - Exhibition: Signing in an non-Xbox LIVE idle Gamer Profile caused a Profile change for the Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile','Summary:\nTwice, In Exhibition gameplay, the Player signed into a non-Xbox LIVE idle Gamer Profile which caused a Profile change for the Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During Exhibition gameplay, with an Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile signed in to Controller 2.\n2) The Player signed in an non-Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile in to Controller 1.\n3) A Profile change occurred for the Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile, returning the Player to the START screen. \n\nExpected Results:\nIdle Profile sign ins must not affect the Active Gamer Profile during gameplay.\n\nGames must properly detect and handle player profiles signing in or out in all areas of the game. This is a violation of TCR 015.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5822,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,5,'','Once - TCR 015 - Menu System: Signing in to an Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer profile that was not connected to Xbox LIVE caused a Profile change','Summary:\nOnce, on the Main Menu, a Player signed into a Xbox LIVE enabled idle Gamer Profile which caused a Profile change for the Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with an Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile not connected to Xbox LIVE signed in to Controller 2.\n2) The Player signed in to a Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile not connected to Xbox LIVE with Controller 1.\n3) A Profile change occurred for the Active Xbox LIVE Gamer Profile, returning the Player to the START screen. \n\nExpected Results:\nIdle Profile sign ins must not affect the Active Gamer Profile during gameplay.\n\nGames must properly detect and handle player profiles signing in or out in all areas of the game. This is a violation of TCR 015.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5827,1224288000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: With the black and blue color scheme selected, the black color on the 4ft Cylinder bunkers appears gray','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Field Creator, with the black and blue color scheme selected, if the user selects the 4ft Cylinder bunkers, the black color on the bunker appears gray.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Field Editor.\n2) Select any pre-made map.\n3) When the Field Creator appears, press the X button until all of the pre-existing bunkers have been deleted.\n4) Press left on the Directional Pad, set the color scheme to black and blue (the black square should be in front of the blue square), then press the B button to apply the color scheme.\n5) Press right on the Directional Pad, and select the 4ft Cylinder bunkers.\n6) Observe that the area that is supposed to be black in color appears gray in color.\n\nExpected Results:\nWith the black and blue color scheme selected, the black color must appear black and not gray.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5841,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Multiplayer System Link: The Rich Presence for Speedball Miami, Florida is incorrect','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer System Link, the Rich Presence for Speedball Miami, Florida is incorrect.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu, with a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence,\n2) The Player selects System Link.\n3) The Host selects Create Game.\n4) The host selects Speedball Miami, Florida.\n5) Clients join.\n6) Gameplay begins.\n7) The Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"LAN - Speedball \nHouston, Texas\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"System Link - <X>\nMiami, Florida\"\n\nBy replacing the first set of text with the second set of text.\n\nIn active gameplay, games must update presence information. Presence information must accurately reflect the player’s state. This is a violation of TCR 070.\n\nNotes:\n1) \"<X>\" refers to the gametype - CTF, CF, or Elim.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5853,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: The Host is unable to start a Player Match after creating it through the Quick Match option.','Summary:\nThe Host is unable to start a Player Match after creating it through the Quick Match option.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 selects Player Match from the Xbox Live menu\n2) User 1 selects Quick Match\n3) User 2 joins User 1\'s game\n4) With both Users \"readied up\" and on opposite teams, User 1 presses the A button to start the game\n5) User 1 observes they are unable to start the game.\n\nExpected Results:\nPlayer Matches must be able start when there is a minimum of two players in the lobby on opposing teams.\n\nNote: The host can start the game if there are 4 players in the game lobby.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5854,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: The Host is unable to start a Player Match after creating it through the Quick Match option when the teams are not even.','Summary:\nThe Host is unable to start a Player Match after creating it through the Quick Match option when the teams are not even.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 selects Player Match from the Xbox Live menu\n2) User 1 selects Quick Match\n3) Users 2 and 3 join User 1\'s game\n4) With all Users \"readied up\" and at least one User on each team, User 1 presses the A button to start the game\n5) User 1 observes they are unable to start the game.\n\nExpected Results:\nPlayer Matches must be able to start when there is a minimum of two players in the lobby on opposing teams, even teams must not be turned on.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5866,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Multiplayer: If the Host disconnects the controller, and the Client manually quits from the game, the Host stays in the game with no opposing team.','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer, if the Host disconnects the controller, and the Client manually quits from the game, the Host stays in the game with no opposing team\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Host creates a default Player Match.\n2) Client joins the Host\'s game\n3) Host presses \"LB\" to add a bot to their team.\n3) Host starts the game\n4) Gameplay appears\n5) Host disconnects the controller\n6) Client exits the game via the Pause Menu\n7) The Host reconnects the controller and selects \"OK\" on the disconnected message\n8) The Host notices he remains in gameplay with no clients/bots on the yellow team.\n\nExpected Results:\nHost must get disconnected when there are no Clients left in the game.','jhh\n','[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/24/2008 01:58:55 AM]\nVerified in the 10/22 buildtest\n',''),(5871,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Multiplayer - Ranked Match: If a Client disconnects in any way during the Game Lobby countdown, the Host is unable to start the game, and other Clients are unable to join.','Summary:\nIn a Ranked Match, if a Client disconnects in any way during the Game Lobby countdown, the Host is unable to start the game, and other Clients are unable to join the game.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Host creates default Ranked Match\n2) 3 Clients join the Host\'s game\n3) The Host starts the Game Lobby countdown\n4) As soon as the countdown begins 1 Client disconnects (signs out of Xbox LIVE, power down, pulling the network cable, etc.)\n5) The timer counts down and dissapears\n6) The Host notices the button prompts on the screen disappear and the screen only displays \"Waiting For 1 More Client.\"\n7) The Host is unable to start the game and no clients are able to rejoin the Host\'s game\n\nExpected Results:\nThe title must not hang, malfunction or become unplayable due to communication, errors, or another Clients actions.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5872,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: From the Audio Options screen in the Pause menu, User cannot choose the playlist \"Menu Music.\"','Summary:\nFrom the Audio Options screen in the Pause menu, User cannot choose the playlist \"Menu Music.\"\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main menu, User loads into any type of gameplay,\n2) Presses START button to access the Pause Menu,\n3) Selects Options,\n4) Selects Audio,\n5) Highlights Playlist,\n6) Scrolls cursor left and right to view playlists,\n7) Observes there is no option to choose \"Menu Music\" as a playlist.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser must be able to select any playlist.\n\nNote(1): If User highlights Playlist and presses the \"X\" button to View Playlists, they see that \"Menu Music\" is supposed to be an available playlist.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5880,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Gameplay: User observes a slight frame rate drop when jumping over small bunkers.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, if the User character attempts to jump over a small bunker, the User observes a slight frame rate drop when performing that jump.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User enters gameplay in any Speedball map.\n2) User approaches a small bunker their character is able to jump.\n3) User observes the text, \"Press A to jump\" appears on screen.\n4) User presses the \"A\" button to have their character execute a jump.\n5) User observes the a slight drop in frame rate while jumping.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe frame rate must not drop, when the User\'s character is jumping over obstacles.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5881,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,3,'(30%-39%)','Occasionally - Technical Check - Multiplayer - When 5 clients simultaneously join a game lobby, the game lobby between clients does not properly reflect what team multiple clients are on.','Summary:\nWithin a game lobby of a default multiplayer match, when 5 clients simultaneously join the match, the game lobby between clients does not properly reflect what team multiple clients are on.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host creates a default multiplayer match\n2) 5 clients simultaneously join the lobby\n3) Multiple clients observe the teams displayed on screen do not reflect what the teams actually are\n\nExpected Results:\nThe teams listed within the game lobby must always appear properly before loading into multiplayer gameplay between all users.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5895,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Multiplayer: Gamertags and Player Icons overlap the User\'s paintball mask graphic, on the Users HUD.','Summary:\nOnline ID\'s overlap the User\'s paintball mask graphic, on the Users HUD.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a multiplayer game lobby with \"Visible Player Name\" set to Yes.\n2) User 2 and 3 join User 1\'s game lobby, with User 2 on User 1\'s team.\n3) Users progress to gameplay.\n4) Gameplay begins, User 1 observes User 2.\n5) User 1 observes User 2\'s Player Icon and Gamertag, overlapping with their Paintball Mask graphic, on their HUD.\n\nExpected Results:\nPlayer Icons and Gamertag must not overlap a User\'s Paintball mask graphic, on the Users HUD.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5909,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer - Train Depot Field: While in spectator view, the user is able to see under the world after colliding with a spool.','Summary: While in spectator view, the user is able to see under the world after colliding with a spool. The user attempts to move in between the top and bottom of the spool, and ends up seeing outside the world.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a Capture the Flag, Player match at Train Depot Field.\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s match.\n3) Users begin gameplay.\n4) User 2 eliminates User 1.\n5) User 1 navigates to any spool that is flipped over onto it\'s side.\n6) User 1 attempts to position their camera in between the spool.\n7) User 1 observes their camera clip through the ground, and can see outside the world.\n\nExpected Results: Users must not be able to see outside the world.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5916,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: The text indicating that the User has the flag overlaps the Sprint Meter when the resolution is set to 480i.','Summary:\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 or 2 has there resolution set to 480i\n2) User 1 hosts a default Player Match\n3) User 2 joins User 1\'s game\n4) Users load into gameplay\n5) The User with 480i resolution picks up the flag\n6) User observes the text that appears overlaps the Sprint Meter.\n\nExpected Results:\nText must not overlap the Sprint Meter.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5922,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: The Client is returned to the Main menu after being disconnected from the Host while on the Exit Confirmation screen.','Summary:\nThe Client is returned to the Main menu after being disconnected from the Host while on the Exit Confirmation screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 Creates a Player Match with default settings,\n2) User 2 joins user 1\'s game,\n3) Game Lobby appears,\n4) User 2 presses B button to Back out,\n5) Exit Confirmation screen appears,\n6) User 1 presses the B button to Back out,\n7) Selects YES to confirm,\n8) \"Disconnected from the host.\" message appears for User 2,\n9) Selects OK,\n10) Observes being returned to the Main menu.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Client must be returned to the Xbox LIVE menu after they have lost connection with the Host.\n\nNOTE(1): This occurs from Player Match, Ranked Match, and System Link game lobbies.\nNOTE(2): Also occurs while a Client is on the Your Gear screen.','jhh\n','[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/24/2008 01:58:55 AM]\nVerified in the 10/22 buildtest\n',''),(5923,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Multiplayer: The elimination text in the corner of the screen dissapears too quickly.','Summary:\nThe elimination text in the corner of the screen dissapears too quickly.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 hosts a Ranked or Player Match\n2) Users 2-4 join User 1\'s game\n3) Users enter into gameplay\n4) User 1 eliminates User 2\n5) Right after the elimination User 3 eliminates User 4\n6) Users observe the text in the corner of the screen disappear for the first elimination before they can read it.\n\nExpected Results:\nElimination text must stay on-screen for a resonable amount of time. Text must scroll when Users are eliminated at the same time.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5926,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,14,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Statistics: Scoreboards - Ranked match, statistics from partially completed ranked matches do not post to the scoreboards.','Summary: \nWhen viewing the ranked match scoreboards, users observe that statistics from partially completed ranked games (host leaves early) do not post to the scoreboard. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default ranked match.\n2) Users 2-4 join user 1\'s game.\n3) User 1 starts the game, gameplay begins for all users.\n4) User 2(yellow team) eliminates users from the red team, then captures the flag to complete the round.\n5) User 1 exits the match via the in-game menu.\n6) User 2 enters the ranked match scoreboards.\n7) User 2 observes they are not credited for their eliminations in the previous partially completed match.\n\nExpected Results: \nRanked match statistics must be tracked on a per-round basis to the scoreboards.\n\nNote(1)\nCurrently, users could exploit the ranked scoreboard by choosing whether or not to complete a match. If the user is having a poor game, they can quit without being penalized.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5960,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Exhibition - Woodsball Maps: There is no paint splatter when paintballs hit anything except the ground.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Exhibition Mode, on any woodsball level, when a paintball hits any object other than the ground (trees, shacks, barrels, and boxes), no paint splatter appears where the paintball landed.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Exhibition,\n2) Select any gameplay settings, and any woodsball map,\n3) Hit A to start the game,\n4) When the match starts, walk up to any object such as a tree or box and shoot it,\n5) Observe, there is no paint splatter left where the paintball hit the object.\n\nExpected Results:\nThere must be a paint splatter whenever a paintball hits an object.\n\nNOTE(1):\nThe paint splatters do not appear on anything except the ground.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5961,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,2,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - System Link: A Client that quits out of a System Link game is brought to the incorrect Menu','Summary:\nA Client that quits out of a System Link game is brought to the incorrect Menu\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, System Link, with the Player as a client.\n2) The Player presses the START (Pause) button.\n3) The Player selects Quit Match.\n4) The Player selects Yes.\n5) A loading screen appears, and a System Link Menu appears with the options \"Quick Match\", \"Custom Match\", and \"Create Game\".\n\nExpected Results:\nAnyone exiting from a Multiplayer game must be brought to the System Link Menu.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5962,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,2,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - System Link: A Host that quits out of a System Link game is brought to an incorrect menu','Summary:\nA Host that quits out of a System Link game is brought to an incorrect menu\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, System Link, with the Player as the Host.\n2) The Player presses the START (Pause) button.\n3) The Player selects Quit Match.\n4) The Player selects Yes.\n5) A loading screen appears, and a System Link Menu appears with the options \"Quick Match\", \"Custom Match\", and \"Create Game\".\n\nExpected Results:\nAnyone exiting from a Multiplayer game must be brought to the System Link Menu.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5963,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,2,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: Players are moved to the Main Menu if a System Link game ends in an error','Summary:\nPlayers are moved to the Main Menu if a System Link game ends in an error\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, System Link.\n2) The host quits the game.\n3) The clients recieve the message \"Lost connection with the Host\".\n4) The clients select Ok, and the Main Menu appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe System Link must appear after exiting a System Link game.\n\nNotes:\n1) This also occurs for the Host, if all the Clients leave.','jhh\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/21/2008 09:18:49 PM]\nMoved back to Dev ownershiptest\n',''),(5976,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1224201600,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - System Link Lobby: After pressing the Guide Button, the Blade came up full screen and the game crashed.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, on the System Link Lobby screen with default game-type settings and no Clients in the match, after the Host pressed the Guide Button, the Guide Blade appeared full screen and the game crashed with a fatal system error.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, selected Multiplayer,\n2) Selected System Link,\n3) Selected Create Match,\n4) Used the defaulted game types,\n5) In the Lobby, pressed the Guide button,\n6) Observed that the Guide Blade appeared full screen and the game crashed.\n\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash when the Guide Blade is brought up in the Lobby.\n\nNotes:\n1) There is no crash dump available for this crash.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5977,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Quick Play: The Rich Presence for Quick Play - Miami is incorrect','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence for Quick Play - Miami is incorrect\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Quick Play, Miami, with a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence,\n2) The Player\'s Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"Quick Play\nHouston, Texas\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Quick Play\nMiami, Florida\"\n\nBy replacing the text \"Houston, Texas\" with the text \"Miami, Florida\".\n\nIn active gameplay, games must update presence information. Presence information must accurately reflect the player’s state. This is a violation of TCR 070.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5978,1224374400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Exhibition: The Rich Presence for Exhibition - Miami is incorrect','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence for Exhibition - Miami is incorrect\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Exhibition, any mode, Miami, with a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence,\n2) The Player\'s Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"Exhibition - Speedball\nHouston, Texas\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Exhibition - Speedball\nMiami, Florida\"\n\nBy replacing the text \"Houston, Texas\" with the text \"Miami, Florida\".\n\nIn active gameplay, games must update presence information. Presence information must accurately reflect the player’s state. This is a violation of TCR 070.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(5987,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: The turning animation does not occur during sliding, if the User immediately begins turning when starting the slide.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in a Multiplayer match, if the User presses the \"A\" button to perform the slide action, then immediately begins turning, other Players in the game will observe that the User\'s character stays facing the original direction of the slide, when in fact the User has already turned nearly 180 degrees in the opposite direction.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a multiplayer match with any settings.\n2) User 2 joins the game.\n3) Both Users READY up, and User 1 launches the game.\n4) During gameplay, both Users navigate to the same bunker that is slide-able.\n5) User 1 performs the slide action by pressing the \"A\" button while moving towards the bunker.\n6) Immediately after pressing the \"X\" button, User 1 turns their camera and character by moving the Right Stick to the left/right to face User 2.\n7) User 2 observes that during the slide animation, User 1\'s character is always facing the original direction of the slide action, when in fact, User 1 has turned in mid-slide and has User 2 in their sight.\n8) The slide action completes, and User 2 observes that User 1\'s character has suddenly turned towards them.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe slide animation must properly reflect the actions of the User.\n\nNOTE: If User 1 is firing while performing this bug, User 2 wll observe that User 1 appears to be firing at their paintballs at weird angles.\nNOTE: This bug is timing specific.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5989,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,8,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Career Mode: With a new Career, the Canadian Invitational text will appear on-screen for a split second when Play Tournament is selected from the Career Mode menu.','Summary:\nFrom the Main menu, with a new Career, the User selects Career Mode, selects Play Tournament, the Tournament menu appears, and the User observes the text below the Charlotte, North Carolina level briefly appears as \"Canadian Invitational, Locked, 5 vs 5.\"\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User creates a new Career.\n2) From the Main menu, User selects Career Mode.\n3) User selects Play Tournament.\n4) The Tournament menu appears, and the User observes the text below the Charlotte, North Carolina level briefly appears as \"Canadian Invitational, Locked, 5 vs. 5\", before switching to the correct text.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe correct text must always appear underneath Tournament level pictures.\n\nNOTE: This also happens on other levels within the Tournament menu, but the User must progress through the tournaments and reach those levels.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5990,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Speedball - London, England: Spectators standing behind the mesh net on the left side of the field (Red Team\'s perspective) float approximately 1-foot off the ground and clip through 4 short cylindrical cement pillars.','Summary:\nDuring Speedball gameplay, London, England, the spectators standing behind the mesh netting on the left side of the field from the Red Team\'s starting point are floating approximately one foot off the ground and clip through four short cylindrical cement pillars along the length of the field.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Multiplayer,\n2) Select Xbox LIVE,\n3) Select Player Match,\n4) Create a game at London, England,\n5) Enter gameplay,\n6) From the Red Team\'s starting point, navigate the User\'s Avatar to the left side of the field,\n7) Observe that the spectators standing behind the mesh net along the length of the field float approximately one-foot off the ground and clip through four short cylindrical cement pillars.\n\nExpected Results:\nSpectators must not appear to be floating or clip through objects.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5991,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Train Depot Field: User is able to see through wheel mounts on the brown train cars.','Summary:\nOn Train Depot Field, the user is able to see through the wheel mounts on all the brown train cars.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User enters gameplay on Train Depot Field\n2) The user navigates to any of the brown train cars\n3) The user looks down the at the wheels from the front of the cars and the user is able to see through the wheel mounts\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must not be to see through the wheel mounts.\n\nNOTE: Screenshots attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/21/2008 09:19:05 PM]\nMoved back to Dev ownershiptest\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5992,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic: Multiplayer - San Jose, users observe a table graphic is missing just outside the boundary fence.','Summary: During gameplay of a multiplayer match on San Jose, users observe a table graphic is missing just outside the boundary fence.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates an Xbox LIVE player match game on the San Jose level.\n2) User 2 joins user 1\'s game.\n3) User 1 starts the game, gameplay appears for all users.\n4) The user on the yellow team navigates their character to the left corner closest to their flag station.\n5) The user on the yellow team looks just outside the boundary fence and observes a table graphic is missing.\n\nExpected Results: The table graphic must appear at the specified location.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5993,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer - Jacksonville, Florida: The crowd that is standing on the yellow lift appears to be floating.','Summary: The crowd that is standing on the yellow lift appears to be floating.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates an Xbox LIVE player match at the location Jacksonville, Florida.\n2) User 1 begins gameplay.\n3) User 1 navigates their character to the yellow lift with the crowd standing on it.\n4) User 1 observes the crowd appears to be floating over the lift.\n\nExpected Results: Crowd must not be floating.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5998,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,12,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: The black menu box with the icons for gear types is not centered on the screen, under Your Gear and Server Gear.','Summary: The black menu box with the icons for gear types is not centered on the screen, under Your Gear and Server Gear. The box is positioned farther to the left of the screen, leaving a larger gap on the right.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default Xbox LIVE Player match.\n2) User 1 presses the Left Stick to select gear.\n3) User 1 observes the menu box for gear types is position further to the left. (Not centered on the screen)\n\nExpected Results: The menu box for gear types must be centered.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(5999,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer - Train Depot Field: While in spectator view, the user is able to see under the world after colliding with a spool.','Summary: While in spectator view, the user is able to see under the world after colliding with a spool. The user attempts to move in between the top and bottom of the spool, and ends up seeing outside the world.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates an Xbox LIVE Capture the Flag, Player match at Train Depot Field.\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s match.\n3) Users begin gameplay.\n4) User 2 eliminates User 1.\n5) User 1 navigates to any spool that is flipped over onto it\'s side.\n6) User 1 attempts to position their camera in between the spool.\n7) User 1 observes their camera clip through the ground, and can see outside the world.\n\nExpected Results: Users must not be able to see outside the world.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6000,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: While watching another Player performing the reload animation, the User observes there is no hopper within that Player\'s hand.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay of an Xbox LIVE player match, if the User navigates their character up to another Player, that Player performs the reload animation, and the User observes no Hopper appears within that Player\'s hand.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 hosts an Xbox LIVE player match with any settings.\n2) User 2 joins the match.\n3) All Users READY up, and User 1 launches the game.\n4) Gameplay appears.\n5) From the starting position, User 1 navigates their character to User 2\'s character, and positions themself to the side of User 2\'s character.\n6) User 2 presses the \"LT\"/\"RT\" button to fire off a few paintball rounds at the ground.\n7) User 2 then presses the Right Stick (RELOAD) button to perform the reload action.\n8) User 1 observes User 2\'s character perform the reload action.\n9) User 1 observes that User 2\'s character has no Hopper in their hand when performing the action.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe reload animation must appear correctly to other Players.\n\nNOTE: No paintballs appear as well.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6001,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Speed ball - SC Village: On SC Village, the is no graphical environment past the trees outside of the field.','Summary:\nOn SC Village, the is no graphical environment past the trees outside of the field.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu, User 1 hosts a Speed ball Player Match on SC Village,\n2) User 2 joins Host\'s game,\n3) Users progress into gameplay,\n4) One of the Users shoots and eliminates the other User,\n5) When eliminated User is in Spectator Mode, they move to the corner of the field that has trees outside the fence,\n6) User observes that there is no graphical environment past the trees.\n\nExpected Results:\nA graphical environment must exist as far as the User can see.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6002,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer - When users are too close to each other, the user\'s paintball markers will clip and disappear','Summary:\nWhen 2 users are in a game and are close to each other, the user\'s markers will start to disappear.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) 2 users load into multiplayer gameplay (same team or not)\n2) Users stand as close a possible facing each other\n3) Users will see the other user\'s marker disappear\n\nExpected Results:\nUsers must not see other user\'s markers disappear, markers must remain visible at all times.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6010,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,4,1224374400,0,0,0,3,'(30%-39%)','Occasionally - Crash - Mutliplayer : The host is stuck on an indefinite black screen when they select Quit Game from the XMB while loading into gameplay.','Summary:\nWhen loading into a multiplayer match with 2 players, the host with the 2.50 system software update presses the PS Button and selects Quit Game from the XMB, the host observes a black screen appear and must manually power down the console using the power switch on the back of the PS3.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host with the 2.50 system software update creates a default multiplayer match\n2) A client joins the player lobby and the host starts the game\n3) While on the loading screen the host presses the PS Button to bring up the XMB\n4) The host selects Quit Game\n5) Selects \'YES\' to confirm\n6) Black screen appears,\n7) System beeps 3 times,\n8) Observes being crashed on the black screen.\n5) The host will be stuck on a black screen until manually re-booting the system.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe host must be brought back to system software screen menu when quitting the game via the XMB anywhere within multiplayer. \n\nNOTE(1): When rebooting via the power button on front of the system, the button has to be held down longer than normal before the system reboots.\nNOTE(2): Bug occured when the Host or Client quit via XMB on the countdown into gameplay. A TTY is attached for this reproduction.\nNOTE(3): Bug occured when the Client quit via XMB while on the Stats Menu. A TTY is attached for this reproduction.\nNOTE(4): Bug occured when the Host or Client quit via XMB while on the Controls Menu. A TTY is attached for this reproduction','jhh\n','[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/21/2008 02:54:52 PM]\nA TTY has been attached. This specific issue does not create a crash dump because the console remains on the loading screen indefinetly.\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/28/2008 01:01:04 PM]\ncould not reproduce it\n\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/28/2008 01:48:27 PM]\nNew TTY attached. Video uploaded to the FTP in the following location:/Paintball/AMP QA Bug Captures and Dumps/Video Capture/PS3/Paintball_PS3_#6010test\n',''),(6011,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,3,1224374400,0,0,0,2,'(80%-89%)','Frequently - Video/Graphic - Exhibition - Woodsball - Gold Mine Field: The tin building appears with stretched graphics','Summary: \nFrequently, during Woodsball, in Gold Mine Field, when nearing the tin building (or the center flag building) from the user\'s initial spawn point, the building appears with black stretched graphics\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter Exhibition, in Woodsball, Gold Mine Field\n2) Run towards the tin foil building\n3) Frequently, observe that the building appears with black stretched graphics\n\nExpected Results:\nBuildings must not appear with stretched graphics\n\nNote (1): Video is available','jhh\ntesting\n','[Bob Paterson (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/21/2008 06:22:10 PM]\nVerified open in 10/21/08 buildtest\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6036,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,3,1224374400,0,0,0,3,'(10%-19%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Quick Play: In Huntington Beach, CA, opponents move unrealistically.','Summary:\nOccasionally, during Quick Play, Huntington Beach CA, opponents move unrealistically and appear to be stuck crouching in a movement loop.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu user selected Quick Play.\n2) Selected Huntington Beach, California.\n3) All of the user\'s character\'s team-mates were eliminated except for 2, one opponent remained.\n4) User\'s character navigated to the far-right corner of the map where the remain opponent was positioned behind a bunker.\n5) Occasionally, observed that while the opponent was positioned at a bunker near the opponent, the opponent appeared to appeared to be stuck crouching in an unrealistic movement loop.\n\nExpected Results:\nOpponents must not get stuck in a movement loop.\n\nNote():\nVideo-documentation available.','jhh\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 10:20:26 PM]\nStill occurs in 10/22/08 PS2 build. \n\n-- The issue has been updated.test\n',''),(6044,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Exhibition: The Rich Presence for Exhibition - Custom Map is incorrect','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence for Exhibition - Custom Map is incorrect\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Exhibition, any mode, Custom Map, with a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence,\n2) The Player\'s Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"Quick Play\n<X>\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Exhibition - Speedball\n<X>\"\n\nBy replacing the text \"Quick Play\" with the text \"Exhibition - Speedball\".\n\nIn active gameplay, games must update presence information. Presence information must accurately reflect the player’s state. This is a violation of TCR 070. \n\nNotes:\n1) \"<X>\" refers to the Custom map\'s location.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6045,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Match Results: The Match Results screen does not appear after finishing the final match of any tournament.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Match Results, if the User finishes a tournament, at the end of the tournament the User observes the Match Results screen does not appear, the game appears to move straight to the Tournament Results screen without showing individual stats first.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career,\n2) Select Play Tournament,\n3) Select any Tournament,\n4) Finish the tournament in first place,\n5) Observe the Match Results screen does not appear after the tournament is finished.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Match Results screen must appear after every round in Tournament Mode.','jhh\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/21/2008 09:19:18 PM]\nMoved back to Dev ownership\n\n[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 05:42:47 PM]\nVerified on the 10/22/08 X360 Build.test\n',''),(6050,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 096 - Multiplayer: If the Host of an Xbox LIVE Ranked Multiplayer Match has an internet connection limited to bandwidth 64kbps/64kbps, when every Client after the first joins the Game Lobby, only one Client remains and all others are ejected.','Summary:\nIf the Host of an Xbox LIVE Ranked Multiplayer Match has an internet connection limited to bandwidth 64kbps/64kbps, when every Client after the first joins the game, only one Client remains and all others are ejected from the Game Lobby.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1\'s internet connection is limited to 64kbps/64kbps,\n2) User 1 creates an Xbox LIVE Ranked Match,\n3) User 2 joins User 1\'s game,\n4) User 3 joins User 1\'s game,\n5) Observe, when User 3 joins User 1\'s game, either User 2 or User 3 is ejected from the Game Lobby.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe title must support Xbox LIVE gameplay when the host has an internet connection with limited bandwidth of 64kbps/64kbps.\n\nPeer-to-peer gameplay between two different Xbox consoles must not be disconnected as long as the following performance conditions are maintained:\n• Each console has an upstream and downstream bandwidth of 64 kilobits/sec (64,000 bits/sec) or higher.\n• 200 ms or less round-trip latency between consoles.\n• Ten percent or less packet loss in a ten-second interval.\n• Two percent or less packet loss, in general.\n\nThis is a violation of TCR 096.\n\nNote(1): This is PreCert TCR 096 Issue 1 of 1.\nNote(2): Occasionally, four Users are supported in the Ranked Match Game Lobby for a short period of time before they are ejected from the Game Lobby due to being disconnected from the host.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6054,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,2,3,4,1224374400,0,0,0,2,'(70%-79%)','Frequently - Scoring - Results: Scoring after a 9 round match is incorrect.','Summary:\nFrequently the results screen will display incorrect scoring. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Select Exhibition, \n2) Select 7 vs 7, 9 round, capture the flag, speedball, select any map,\n3) Proceed through the rounds until the results screen,\n4) Frequently observed the numbers for survivors and eliminations did not match the actual totals or the displayed totals from individual rounds.\n\nExpected Results:\nScoring must be totaled accurately.\n\nNOTE(1):Occurred twice on Bakersfield, CA. May be potentially caused by a player being eliminated after the flag is hung. During at least one match the User had 4 team members displayed, after hanging the flag a teammate was eliminated displaying 3 remaining team members. The Results screen displayed that the User\'s team had 3 survivors. The Results screen after the completion of the entire match displayed results that the User\'s team had one extra survivor then were recorded. The end results seem to be counting the remaining players before the flag is hung and not counting the elimination after the flag is hung.\n\nNOTE(2): Match summary for the attached picture,\n\nRound 1: My team eliminated 4 opponents and 3 teammates survived. The opponents eliminated 4 of my teammates and 3 opponents survived. Displayed results were accurate.\n\nRound 2: My team eliminated 3 opponents and 2 teammates survived. The opponents eliminated 5 of my teammates and 4 opponents survived. Displayed results were accurate.\n\nRound 3: My team eliminated 4 opponents and 3 teammates survived. The opponents eliminated 4 of my teammates and 3 opponents survived. Displayed results were accurate.\n\nRound 4: My team eliminated 7 opponents and 1 teammates survived. The opponents eliminated 6 of my teammates and 0 opponents survived. Displayed results were accurate.\n\nRound 5: My team eliminated 5 opponents and 3 teammates survived. The opponents eliminated 4 of my teammates and 2 opponents survived. Displayed results were accurate.\n\nFinal Results: My team eliminated 23 opponents and 12 teammates survived. The opponents eliminated 23 of my teammates and 12 opponents survived. The displayed results showed that my team eliminated 21 opponents and 12 teammates survived, the opponents eliminated 23 of my teammates and 14 opponents survived.','jhh\n','[Thanuvong Yang (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 07:57:38 PM]\nverified open in build 10/21/08\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 07:11:03 AM]\nStill occurs in the 10/28/08 PS3 build.test\n',''),(6055,1224460800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,5,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Comment - Menu/GUI - Field Creator: There is no blank map option.','In the Field Creator, when selecting a map to begin editing, the User does not have a blank map option available.\n\nExpected Results:\nA Blank Map must be added to the Pre-made Maps Category.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6091,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 071 - Player Match Lobby: The navigational prompt for viewing a Gamer Card does not appear for the clients in Player Match','Summary:\nThe navigational prompt for viewing a Gamer Card does not appear for the clients in Player Match\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Match Lobby, Player Match, with the Player as a client.\n2) No navigational prompt for veiwing Gamer Cards appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe following navigational prompt must appear on all Player\'s screens:\n\n\"[X button Graphic] Gamer Card\"\n\nGames must provide the player the option to access another player’s gamer card wherever gamertags are enumerated. This is a violation of TCR 071.\n\nNotes:\n1) This prompt appears correct on the Host\'s screen.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6093,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,2,'(50%-59%)','Frequently (50%-59%) - Video/Graphic - Gameplay: When a match starts, the user\'s character\'s paintball marker is in the middle of the screen','Summary:\nFrequently, during gameplay, when any match starts, the user\'s character\'s paintball marker is in the middle of the screen instead of along the right or left sides. When the user\'s character fires the marker, paintballs come out of the barrel sideways.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select any game type,\n2) Select any location,\n3) When gameplay begins, observe that the marker is in the middle of the screen rather than on the sides, blocking the user\'s view.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user\'s character must hold his marker correctly.\n\nNOTE(1): If the user switches the marker between his left and right hands several times, the marker will return to a normal position on the screen.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6094,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 115 - Multiplayer: Game Invites do not function','Summary:\nGame Invites do not function\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in and a Game Invite to a hosted Player Match.\n2) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n3) The Player selects Message.\n4) The Player selects the Game Invite.\n5) The Player accepts the Game Invite, and nothing occurs.\n\nExpected Results:\nGame invites, when accepted, must move the Player to the accepted game\'s Match Lobby.\n\nGames must allow players to send game invites for player match game sessions. Games must also allow players to join player match sessions. This is a violation of TCR 115. \n\nNotes:\n1) The Host sees the Client\'s Gamertag appears in the Match Lobby.\n2) All locations in the game have yet to be tested, but none so far has worked properly.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6117,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Speedball - Nürburgring, Germany: A building on the far right corner of the course appears and disappears','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, in Nürburgring, Germany, a gray-and-white building on the far right corner of the course disappears as the user moves closer and reappears as the user moves further away.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Exhibition,\n2) Select any game type,\n3) Choose Speedball,\n4) Select Nürburgring, Germany,\n5) When gameplay begins, run over to the far right corner of the course,\n6) Note that there is a gray-and-white building with a scoreboard in this area,\n7) Observe that chunks of this building disappear as the user\'s character moves closer, and re-appear as the character moves further away.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll areas of the environment must appear properly.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshots attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6121,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 073 - Gameplay: The Achievement \"Marker Geek\" does not unlock after using all markers','Summary:\nThe Achievement \"Marker Geek\" does not unlock when the Player uses all markers during gameplay at least once.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, with a Gamer Profile signed in.\n2) The Player fires each marker once, and the Achievement \"Marker Geek\" does not unlock.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen the Player uses all markers, the Achievement \"Marker Geek\" must unlock.\n\nGames must provide a way for a player to earn all game-defined achievements and update the player’s profile. This is a violation of TCR 073. \n\nNOTE(1): \nSpeedball Markers Used: \nDye M8 \nJT Excellerator 5 \nJT Excellerator 6 \nJT Tetra \nBob Long Closer \nInvert Mini \nBob Long Protege \nBob Long Vice \nWGP Autococker SR \nBob Long Empire Intimadator \nSpyder Electra \nBob Long Ripper 2\nSmart Parts Vibe\nSmart Parts EOS\nSpyder MR2\nDLX Luxe\nSpyder Pilot\nSmartparts Ion XE\nBob Long Russian Legion\nSmarts Parts Shocker NXT\nBob Long Ripper 3\nBob Long Rapper\nEclipse Ego Etek\nEclipse Ego SL8R\nContract Killer Bob Long Marq\nContract Killer Smart Parts Shocker\n\nWoodsball Combos Used:\nTippmann X7 MP5SD\nTippmann X7 MP5\nTippmann X7 AK47\nTippmann X7 X36\nAlpha Black - Manufactured by Tippmann\nTippmann A-5 Black\nTippmann 98 Custom Digi Camo\nTippmann X7 M16\nTippmann 98 Custom Black\nTippmann A-5 Digi Camo\nTippmann X7','jhh\n','[Steve Myers (AMP TRG Lead) -- 10/25/2008 04:37:12 PM]\nThis issue still occurs in the 10.22.08 X360 build. No change.test\n',''),(6137,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Gear Store: The markers Spyder Pilot and Spyder MR2 have the same stats but the Spyder Pilot appears to cost more.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Gear Store, if the User accesses the Gear Store menu, then cycles to the marker Spyder Pilot, then cycles to the marker Spyder MR2, the stats for the two markers appear to be the same but the Spyder Pilot costs more.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n2) Select the Gear Store,\n3) Cycle to the marker Spyder MR2 and take note of its stats and cost,\n4) Cycle to the marker Spyder Pilot and take note it its stats and cost,\n5) Observe that the two markers have the same stats but different purchase prices.\n\nExpected Results:\nPurchasable items in the Gear Store that have the same stats must have the same prices.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6138,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Ranked - Woodsball - Elimination - Results screen: When the Host removes the controller battery on the Results screen, the menu disappears after the controller is reconnected.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in a Ranked Woodsball Elimination match, after the match is completed and the Host disconnects the battery from the controller on the Results screen, then reinserts the battery and reconnects the controller, then presses the \"A\" button, the Results screen disappears and returns to the game. The Host must then press the START button to bring the Results screen back up again to exit from the game.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Multiplayer,\n2) Select Xbox LIVE,\n3) Select Ranked Match,\n4) Select Custom Match,\n5) Change the Game Mode to Woodsball,\n6) Change the Game Type to Elimination,\n7) Enter gameplay,\n8) Have the Host eliminate the opponents for all three rounds,\n9) After completing the third round, disconnect the battery from the Host\'s controller when the Results screen appears,\n10) Reinsert the battery and reconnect the controller,\n11) Press the \"A\" button to continue,\n12) Observe that the Results screen will disappear and the Host must press the START button to bring the Results screen up again to exit the match.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen the controller is disconnected on the Results screen and then reconnected, pressing \"A\" must exit the Player from the game.\n\nNote:\nThis will also occur if the battery is removed BEFORE the results screen is displayed.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6140,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Gear Store: The Pod Harnesses NXE Elevation and Custom Products Pod Pack have the same stats but the Custom Products Pod Pack appears to cost more.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Gear Store, if the User accesses the Gear Store menu, then cycles to the harness NXE Elevation, then cycles to the harness Custom Products Pod Pack, the stats for the two harnesses appear to be the same but the Custom Products Pod Pack costs more.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n2) Select the Gear Store,\n3) Cycle to the harness NXE Elevation and take note of its stats and cost,\n4) Cycle to the harness Custom Products Pod Pack and take note it its stats and cost,\n5) Observe that the two harnesses have the same stats but different purchase prices.\n\nExpected Results:\nPurchasable items in the Gear Store that have the same stats must have the same prices.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6141,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Player Match: During Player Match Gameplay, the match still appears joinable','Summary:\nDuring Player Match Gameplay, the match still appears joinable\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match, any level.\n2) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n3) The Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n4) The Player selects Messages.\n5) The Player selects Create New, and the option to create a Game Invite appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must only be able to send Game Invites in the Match Lobby.\n\nNotes:\n1) The Player\'s game also appears Joinable to Friends or Players that attempt to Join Session in Progress. The Join does not succeed (the game is not joinable once gameplay begins)\n2) This is related to TCR 115.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6144,1224547200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 070 - Multiplayer: The Rich Presence for the Match Lobby is incorrect','Summary:\nThe Rich Presence for the Match Lobby is incorrect\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Match Lobby, any Multiplayer mode, any level, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in and a Friend monitoring the Player\'s Rich Presence.\n2) The Player\'s Rich Presence appears as:\n\n\"Browsing the menu\nProfile menus\"\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Rich Presence for the Match Lobby must appear as:\n\n\"<X> - <Y>\nMatch Lobby\"\n\nNotes:\n1) <X> refers to the multiplayer mode, Ranked Match, Player Match, or System Link.\n2) <Y> refers to the game type, CTF, CF, or Elim.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6150,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,3,1224547200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Exhibition - Nurburgring, Germany: Opponent got stuck in M bunker after eliminating the user\'s character.','Summary:\nWhen the user picks up the flag and takes cover behind the bunkers on the far right middle of the field the opponents will get stuck on the M bunker after eliminating the user\'s character.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the main menu enter Exhibition mode,\n2) Set up a 1vs1 center flag match in Nurnburgring, Germany,\n3) Grab the flag and take cover behind the bunkers on the right side of the map (see video for exact location)\n4) Let the enemy eliminate the user\'s character when he gets close,\n5) Observe the opponent getting stuck.\n\nExpected Results:\nOpponents must not get stuck.\n\nNote(1): Video capture available.\n\nNote(2): Occurs in the same location as bug #6158','jhh\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/22/2008 08:08:50 AM]\nFixed in 10/21/08 PS2 v3\n\n[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 10:48:00 PM]\nAccidentally closed. This issue occurs in 10/21/08 PS2 v3.\n\n\n--- Verified Open in 10/22/08 PS2 build.\n\n\n\n\nThe issue still occurs as written in the 10/23/08 PS2 build.test\n',''),(6151,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,3,1224547200,0,0,0,3,'(10%-19%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Exhibition - Custom map: The opposing AI does not grab the flag.','Summary:\nOccasionally, during Exhibition gameplay, Custom map, after the user\'s character and teammates have all been eliminated, the opposing AI players do not move to the user\'s flag station to grab the flag.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu select Exhibition \n2) Change the settings to CTF, 7v7, 9 rounds, with defaults teams\n3) Select a Custom field made from Houston Texas Pre-Made map (screenshot attached of layout)\n4) Enter into gameplay\n5) Allow the user\'s character and teammates to be eliminated \n6) Occasionally, the camera is fixed upon an unresponsive opposing player that does not move to get the flag\n\nExpected Results:\nThe opposing players must grab the flag.\n\nNote(1): Screenshot of bunker layout attached.\n\nNote(2): Screenshot attached of additional custom map where bug occurred. \n\nNote(3): Once when enemy NPC was stuck the game crashed after 20 seconds after eliminating the last of the user\'s team.\n\nNote(4): Occurs most often, when the opponent players are behind a bunker as the user\'s last player is eliminated','jhh\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 03:46:44 AM]\nStill occurs on the 10/22/08 PS2 build.test\n',''),(6158,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,3,1224547200,0,0,0,2,'(60%-69%)','Frequently - Gameplay: Opponents come up to user\'s character and start shaking rather than shooting whent he character is holding the flag in a Center Flag match.','Summary:\nFrequently, while playing Center Flag after the user has picked up the Center Flag if the user\'s character takes cover in a way that forces opponents to get very close (i.e., hiding behind a snake bunker that is separated by tombstone bunkers), the opposing characters will not shoot the user\'s character, but instead run up to the user\'s character and start moving erratically. This can also be caused by wiping all incoming hits while an opposing character is approaching the user\'s character.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the main menu enter Exhibition mode,\n2) Create a 1vs1 Center Flag match in Nurburgring, Germany,\n3) Pick up the flag,\n4) Run to the far right side of the field and take cover in the corner between the two tombstone bunkers located within the snake bunker\n5) Observe that frequently, the opponent will come up to the user\'s character and start shaking rather than shooting.\n\nExpected Results:\nOpponents must react realistically to the user\'s character at all times.\n\nNote(1) Video Capture available.\n\nNote(2) This bug can still occur if the opponent shoots a few times but the user manages to wipe while sitting in the corner.\n\nNote(3) A second Video Capture available.','jhh\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/22/2008 11:48:12 PM]\nStill occurs in 10/22/08 PS2 build.test\n',''),(6166,1224633600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,3,1224547200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Breakout Planner: The user is unable to select all players on the team','Summary:\nDuring Exhibition, on the Breakout Planner, if the user loads a custom field with tall cubes in two rows from the user\'s flag station to the opponent\'s flag station, with the bunkers in each row placed so that there is no space in between the bunkers, the user is unable to select all players\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Field Creator on the Main Menu\n2) Selects Malaga, Spain as the base map\n3) Creates a field with tall cube bunkers placed in two rows from one flag station to the other, but with no space in between the bunkers for each row\n4) Stores the custom field\n5) Backs out to the Main Menu\n6) Selects Exhibition\n7) Selects a 7 vs. 7 match\n8) Proceeds to the Breakout Planner\n9) Notice that not all players have a breakout destination and the user is unable to select all players\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must be able to select all the players on the user\'s team and give breakout destinations\n\nNote: Screenshot of layout attached\nNote: Save available','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6167,1224633600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,3,1224547200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: If reloading while ramping, paintballs appear floating on screen','Summary:\nAfter the user\'s character upgrades Reload, floating paintballs appear on screen when reloading while ramping.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main menu user selects Career Mode.\n2) selects Team manager.\n3) Fully upgrades main character\'s Reload stats.\n4) enters any mode of gameplay.\n5) User\'s character reloads hopper while ramping.\n6) Observe that paintballs appear floating near the bottom of the screen.\n\nExpected Results:\nPaintballs must not appear floating on the screen.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6171,1224633600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Menu System: The Post-Earned text for the \"World Tour\" Achievement contains a capitalization error','Summary:\nThe Post-Earned text for the \"World Tour\" Achievement contains a capitalization error\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Gamer Profile signed in that has earned the \"World Tour\" Achievement.\n2) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n3) The Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n4) The Player selects the Gamer Profile.\n5) The Player selects View Games.\n6) The Player selects Paintball 2009.\n7) The Player selects World Tour, and the following text appears:\n\n\"Played a game of paintball in all the career and woodsball locations\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Played a game of paintball in all the Career and Woodsball locations\"\n\nby changing the text \"career and woodsball\" to the text \"Career and Woodsball\".','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6175,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Tournament Selection Screen: Text appears outside of the text box.','Summary:\nOn the Tournament Selection Screen, when the Player selects Malaga, Spain \"Millennium Iberian Cup\", a text box appears with the text \"These tournaments take place at the same time. Playing this tournament will lock the other one in the slate. Are you sure you want to continue?\" The letter \"P\" in \"Playing\" appears outside of the text box.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Play Tournament\n2) On the Tournament Selection Screen, select Malaga, Spain \"Millennium Iberian Cup\",\n3) A text box will appear displaying the text \"These tournaments take place at the same time. Playing this tournament will lock the other one in the slate. Are you sure you want to continue?\",\n4) Observe that the letter \"P\" in \"Playing\" appears outside of the text box.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll text must appear inside of the text box.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6176,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1224201600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer Ranked: The level Miami does not appear in the map rotations','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer Ranked matches, the level Miami does not appear in the map rotations, preventing the Player from playing in Miami.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu,\n2) The Player selects Ranked Match.\n3) The Player selects any game type.\n4) 3 clients join.\n5) The Player starts the match.\n6) The level Miami is never playable.\n\nExpected Results:\nMiami must be playable in Ranked Matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6181,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,3,1224633600,0,0,0,2,'(60%-69%)','Frequently - Gameplay - Exhibition: On a specific custom map, the opponent AI do not return center flag.','Summary:\nDuring Exhibition, on a specifically designed Custom Map (See attached layout), in Huntington Beach, CA, the opponent AI frequently do not return the flag from the far right corner.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu user selects Field creator.\n2) Selects Huntington Beach, CA.\n3) Removes all pre-existing bunkers.\n4) Places 24 brick bunkers on the map using the horizontal-mirror tool (See attached image.).\n5) Saves map and exit field creator.\n6) Selects Exhibition.\n7) Sets up a 7 vs. 7, capture the flag speedball-exhibition.\n8) Selects Huntington beach.\n9) Match initiates.\n10) Both teams are fully eliminated with the exception of 2 opponent team-mates and the user\'s character.\n11) Leads the remaining opponents into the far right corner.\n12) User\'s character is eliminated.\n13) Observe that both remaining opponent teammates are stuck along the right-side row of unkers.\n\nExpected Results:\nOpponent team-mates must not get stuck on bunker.\n\nNote (1) Map image attached.\n\nNote (2) Video-documentation available.\n\nNote (3) Save Data is attached with the custom map created.\n\nNote (4) Issue has lower frequency with only 1 opponent team-mate survival\n\nNote (5) Twice, the opponent grabbed the center flag but stopped right before the flag station, and the match didn\'t end.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6184,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,3,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Dynasty Training Drills (Pause Menu): The TRIANGLE button displays the Help screen','Summary:\nIn any Dynasty Training Drill, on the Pause Menu, the TRIANGLE button displays the Help screen after exiting Help.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Select Dynasty Training Drills from the Main Menu\n2) Select any of the Drills\n3) Enter into gameplay\n4) Press the START button to bring up the Pause Menu\n5) Select Help\n6) Press the X (Continue) button\n7) Press the TRIANGLE button\n8) Observe that the Help screen is displayed.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe TRIANGLE button must not display the Help screen.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6191,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,3,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: A static screen with button prompts appears after the results screen in multi-round matches.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, in any multi-round match (i.e., best 2 of 3, etc.), if the user completes a round that is not the final round, the results screen appears, and the user then presses the X (Continue) button, a static screen that includes inactive button prompts appears.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Select Quick Play\n2) Select any match that has multiple rounds\n3) Complete a round\n4) The Results screen appears\n5) Press the X (Continue) button\n5) Observe the static screen that appears for ~3 seconds.\n\nExpected Results:\nThis static screen must not exist.\n\nNote (1) The button prompts that display are dependent on the game mode. (I.e., if in Career Mode, in a tournament that includes a Team Manager, the L2 and D-Pad button graphics appear on the static screen.)\n\nNote (2) This issue occurs in Career Mode, Quick Play, and Exhibition.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6192,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,3,1224633600,0,0,0,4,'','Twice - Gameplay - Quick Play - Orlando Florida: Enemy NPC could not reach the user team\'s flag, and was stuck on an invisible bunker.','Summary:\nTwice, during gameplay in Quick Play - Orlando, Florida, the user\'s character moved to the enemy team\'s flag station, was eliminated, as the enemy NPC moved to the user team\'s flag station and the NPC became stuck on an invisible barrier and could not reach the flag.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Entered gameplay in Quick Play - Orlando, Florida,\n2) Moved to the enemy team\'s flag station,\n3) Was eliminated,\n4) Observed that the enemy NPC moved to the user team\'s flag station and the NPC became stuck on an invisible barrier and could not reach the flag.\n\nExpected Results:\nEnemy NPC must be able to get and return the flag.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6196,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,2,3,1224633600,0,0,0,3,'(10%-19%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Exhibition, in custom maps, opponents get stuck due to collision detection between bunkers placed together in groups.','Summary:\nOccasionally, in Custom Maps with bunkers placed together in groups, the opponent AI get stuck due to collision detection between bunkers, and cannot retrieve the flag to complete the map.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From main menu user selects Field Creator.\n2) Selects any map.\n3) Clears map of bunkers.\n4) Places a group of bunkers ( short brick bunker works more frequently) in a group near the opponent\'s flag station.\n5) Saved Field and exited Field creator.\n6) Selected Exhibition.\n7) Set up a 7 vs. 7, capture the flag speed-ball exhibition with the default teams.\n8) Selected custom map previously created.\n9) User character eliminates all opponents that appear to have a clear path to the flag. \n9) Occasionally, after the user\'s character team had been fully eliminated, the opponent(s) did not retrieve the flag and the match did not end\nbecause they appeared to be stuck on collision detection between the placed bunkers. \n\nExpected Results:\nOpponents must retrieve flag after the user\'s character\'s team has been fully eliminated\n\nNote(1):\nImages of custom map setup attached.\n\nNote(2):\nVideo-documentation available.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6200,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: The Player cannot bring Custom Maps into multiplayer','Summary:\nThe Player cannot bring Custom Maps into multiplayer\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Fromthe Multiplayer Menu, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in, and a custom map created.\n2) The Player selects Xbox LIVE.\n3) The Xbox LIVE Menu appears.\n4) The Player selects Player Match.\n5) The Player Match Menu appears.\n6) The Player selects Create Game.\n7) The Player Match Map Select Menu appears, and there is no way to select a Custom Map.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must be able to create Player Matches and System Link games with a Custom Map.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6202,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,10,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Audio/Sound - Gameplay: Corrupt audio plays when the Results Screen appears','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, at the end of a round in a match with more than one round, when the Results Screen appears, corrupt audio that sounds like a voice being re winded or fast-forwarded plays.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Career Mode.\n2) Select Play Tournament.\n3) Select any Tournament.\n4) When gameplay begins, play through the round, either winning or losing.\n5) Observe that when the Results Screen appears, corrupt audio that sounds like a voice being re winded or fast forwarded plays.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll audio must play correctly and not sound corrupt.\n\nNOTE(1): Video with the corrupt audio attached.\nNOTE(2): The audio issue also occurs when the flag is hanged at a teams home base.\nNOTE(3): The audio issue also occurs when the flag is dropped after the carrier is eliminated.\nNOTE(4): The audio issue also occurs when a dropped flag is picked up.','jhh\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/23/2008 09:18:07 AM]\nDupe.\n\n[Justin Westplate (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/25/2008 10:29:42 AM]\nNot a dupe, re-opened on 10/25/08.test\n',''),(6203,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,10,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Audio/Sound - Gameplay: The audio for hanging the flag plays a second time.','Summary:\nDuring CTF gameplay, in a round that does not end the match, when a team hangs the flag the audio plays a second time in the results screen. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter a CTF match that is more then 1 round\n2) When either team hangs the flag, the audio from hanging the flag plays a second time in the results screen\n\nExpected Results:\nThe flag hang audio must not play in the results screen.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6204,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - Multiplayer: When on the Yellow Team, the misfire when firing yellow paintballs appears blue','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer gameplay, the misfire while using the yellow paintballs appears blue.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Multiplayer\n2) The Player on the yellow team fires single yellow paintballs.\n3) The marker misfires and it appears as a blue paintball.\n\nExpected Results:\nYellow paintball misfires must appear yellow.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6207,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: At the Load Map Screen, the text boundary, Left Bumper icon, and Right Bumper icon overlap white lines','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Field Creator, at the Load Map Screen, the text boundary area containing the Left Bumper Icon, Right Bumper icon, \"Pre-Made\" text, and \"Custom\" text overlap a series of white lines.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Field Creator.\n2) When the Load Map Screen appears, observe that the text boundary area containing the Left Bumper Icon, Right Bumper icon, \"Pre-Made\" text, and \"Custom\" text overlap a series of white lines.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe text boundary area containing the Left Bumper Icon, Right Bumper Icon, \"Pre-Made\" text, and \"Custom\" text must be moved up so they do not overlap the series of white lines that appear on the bottom of the screen.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6208,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Exhibition: At the Load Map Screen, the text boundary, Left Bumper icon, and Right Bumper icon overlap white lines','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Exhibition, at the Load Map Screen, the text boundary area containing the Left Bumper Icon, Right Bumper icon, \"Speedball\" text, and \"Woodsball\" text overlap a series of white lines.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Exhibition.\n2) When the Load Map Screen appears, observe that the text boundary area containing the Left Bumper Icon, Right Bumper icon, \"Speedball\" text, and \"Woodsball\" text overlap a series of white lines.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe text boundary area containing the Left Bumper Icon, Right Bumper Icon, \"Speedball\" text, and \"Woodsball\" text must be moved up so they do not overlap the series of white lines that appear on the bottom of the screen.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6209,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Exhibition: When disconnecting the active controller, the reconnect controller message text appears cut off','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Exhibition, if the user disconnects the active controller at the Match Settings Screen, the reconnect controller message text appears cut off.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Exhibition.\n2) When the Match Settings Screen appears, disconnect the active controller.\n3) Observe that when the reconnect controller message appears, the text is cut off.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll in-game text must appear in full and must not be cut off.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6212,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,3,'(30%-39%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Speedball - Las Vegas, Nevada: The User starts 10 seconds before the opposing team in Tournament Mode.','Summary:\nOccasionally, during gameplay, Las Vegas, Nevada, if the User loads into tournament mode, the User is able to start 10 seconds before the opposing team and run down to shoot all opponents after the 3 second countdown. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n2) Select XPSL Las Vegas, Nevada,\n3) After the the initial count down, observe the Users Character is able to run down to the opposing team\'s side before the opposing team starts.\n\nExpected Results:\nBoth teams must start at the same time.\n\nNOTE(1): The User can start shooting the opposing team and win the match before the opposing team even starts the match because the User starts 10 seconds before the opposing team.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6213,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 006 - Menu System: While loading into any match in career mode, the loading screen becomes static for over 5 seconds before entering gameplay.','Summary:\nLoading into gameplay is static for more than 5 seconds at the end of the loading screen\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Career Menu.\n2) The Player selects Play Tournament.\n3) The Tournament Selection Menu appears.\n4) The Player selects any available Tournament.\n5) The Player presses the A (Continue) button, and a loading screen appears that has a ~5 second to ~8 seconds static screen before the load finishes.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Loading Screen must have a static screen at the end of the loading sequence.\n\nGames must not pause without game-representative on-screen graphics. When the pause time is greater than five seconds, the game must indicate the reason and provide on-screen animation. This is a violation of TCR 006.\n\nNotes:\n1) This is PreCert TCR 006 Issue 1 of 1.\n\nNotes:\n1) This occurs for all loading screens into Gameplay. \n2) Now, occasionally, a static shot of gamplay appears instead of the loading screen.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6214,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,3,'(10%-19%)','Occasional - Gameplay - Dynasty Training Drills - Fitness Stage 3: After completing the training objective the game did not continue to the next stage and the level was failed after the timer reached zero.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Dynasty Training Drills Fitness Stage 3, when the Player completed the training objective and, on the last bunker, turns back around to face the field during the slide, the game did not continue to the next stage and the Player remained in the level. After the timer counted to zero, the Player failed the level.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career,\n2) Select Dynasty Training Drills,\n3) Select Fitness,\n4) Select Stage 3,\n5) Complete the objectives of shooting the orange cones in front of the indicated bunker and running and sliding to the next indicated bunker,\n6) While sliding towards the final bunker, press and hold the Right Control Stick to the right to turn the Player Character back towards the field,\n7) Observe that the game does not continue to the next level, the Player remains in the level and then fails the level after the timer reaches zero.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen the level objective is completed successfully, the game must continue to the next level.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6218,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Career: The Player is not able to proceed past the first round after doing Dynasty Training Drills before Tournament mode.','Summary:\nIf the Player completes a level in Dynasty Training and then proceeds to the tournament mode, the Player is only allowed to complete the first match, after completing that match, the Player is taken back to the Dynasty Training Menu of the level the Player last played, not allowing the Player to proceed through Career Mode.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu,\n2) The Player selects Dynasty Training Drills,\n2) The Player completes Accuracy Training 1,\n3) The Player exits to the Career Mode Menu,\n4) The Player selects Play Tournament,\n5) The Player proceeds to complete the first semifinal match of the East Coast Invitational,\n6) The Player observes that after the load screen the User is in the Dynasty Training Accuracy Menu. (If the User enters the Tournament again they will have to replay the semifinal match again.)\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must be able to continue through tournament mode after completing training levels.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6220,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Career Mode - Tournament 11, California Exhibition: Banners do not appear on the team home bases','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Career Mode, in Tournament 11, California Exhibition, the NPPL Championship Paintball banners do not appear on the team home bases, as they do in every other tournament.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Career Mode.\n2) Select Play Tournament.\n3) Select the Division 1 California Exhibition tournament in Hungington Beach, California.\n4) When gameplay begins, observe that the NPPL Championship Paintball banners do not appear on the team home bases.\n\nExpected Results:\nNPPL Championship Paintball banners must appear on the team home bases so that it is consistant throughout gameplay.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6225,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Career Mode - Tournament 16b, SoCal Invitational: Banners do not appear on the team home bases','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Career Mode, in Tournament 16b, SoCal Invitational, the NPPL Championship Paintball banners do not appear on the team home bases, as they do in every other tournament.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Career Mode.\n2) Select Play Tournament.\n3) Select the Semi-Pro SoCal Invitational tournament in San Diego, California.\n4) When gameplay begins, observe that the NPPL Championship Paintball banners do not appear on the team home bases.\n\nExpected Results:\nNPPL Championship Paintball banners must appear on the team home bases so that it is consistant throughout gameplay.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6226,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Career Mode - Tournament 19b, Texas Invitational: Banners do not appear on the team home bases','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Career Mode, in Tournament 19b, Texas Invitational, the NPPL Championship Paintball banners do not appear on the team home bases, as they do in every other tournament.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Career Mode.\n2) Select Play Tournament.\n3) Select the Semi-Pro Texas Invitational tournament in Houston, Texas.\n4) When gameplay begins, observe that the NPPL Championship Paintball banners do not appear on the team home bases.\n\nExpected Results:\nNPPL Championship Paintball banners must appear on the team home bases so that it is consistant throughout gameplay.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6228,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check: Multiplayer menu system, is user disconnects their controller, then disconnects the network cable from their system connector, they are not returned to the Main Menu.','Summary: While in the multiplayer menu system, is user disconnects their controller, then disconnects the network cable from their system connector, they are not returned to the Main Menu after reconnecting their controller and clearing the disconnected message.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User enters the Xbox LIVE multiplayer menu system.\n2) User disconnects their controller.\n3) User disconnects the network cable from their system connector.\n4) User reconnects their controller.\n5) User clears the disconnected message.\n6) User observes they are not automatically brought back to the Main Menu.\n\nExpected Results: When user disconnects the network cable from their system connector while their controller is disconnected, they must be returned to the Main Menu system.\n\nNote(1): This bug also occurs in the following menu systems and their respective sub-systems:\nRanked Match\n- Quick Match\n- Custom Match\nPlayer Match\n- Quick Match\n- Custom Match\n- Filters Screen\n- Create Game\nLeaderboards\n- Personal Career Eliminations\n- Career Team Efficiency\n- Career Finish Time\n- Ranked Woodsball Eliminations\n- Ranked Speedball Eliminations\n- Ranked Eliminator\nSystem Link\n- Create Game\n- Join Game\n\nNote(2): This issue does not occur in the following locations:\nIn a ranked match lobby(host or client)\nIn a player match lobby(host or client)\n\nNote(3): This causes many TCR issues, with messaging and expected menu functionality.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6230,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer Ranked CTF: The level Houston, Texas does not appear in the map rotations','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer Ranked CTF matches, the level Houston, Texas does not appear in the map rotations, preventing the Player from playing in Houston, Texas\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu,\n2) The Player selects Ranked Match.\n3) The Player selects Capture the Flag.\n4) 3 clients join.\n5) The Player starts the match.\n6) The level Houston, Texas is never playable.\n\nExpected Results:\nHouston, Texas must be playable in Ranked Matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6231,1224720000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer Ranked CF: The level Charlotte, North Carolina does not appear in the map rotations','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer Ranked Center Flag matches, the level Charlotte, North Carolina does not appear in the map rotations, preventing the Player from playing in the leve.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu,\n2) The Player selects Ranked Match.\n3) The Player selects Center Flag.\n4) 3 clients join.\n5) The Player starts the match.\n6) The level Charlotte, North Carolina is never playable.\n\nExpected Results:\nCharlotte, North Carolina must be playable in Ranked Matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6232,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: The camera shakes when the User\'s character enters the prone position.','Summary:\nFrequently, during gameplay, if the User\'s character enters the prone position, the User observes the camera shakes.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User enters gameplay in any level.\n2) During gameplay, User presses and holds the \"B\" button to make their character enter the prone position.\n3) The User observes the camera shakes.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe screen must not shake when the User is in the prone position.\n\nNOTE: If the User attempts to crawl, the camera shakes even more violently.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6233,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: Users are returned to a different Player Match menu after quitting out of a Player Match.','Summary: Users are returned to a different Player Match menu after quitting out of a Player Match. The default Player match menu lists three options: Quick Match, Custom Match, and Create Game. After quitting out of a player match, the user is returned to a menu that displays only two options: Create Game and Join Game.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default Player Match.\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s match.\n3) Users begin gameplay.\n4) User 1 manually quits out of the match, User 2 gets disconnected.\n5) Users observe they are returned to a different Player Match menu, with only 2 options: Create Game and Join Game.\n\nExpected Results: Menus must be consistent after quiting out of a match.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6234,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Multiplayer: Friendly fire is not turned on in Ranked matches.','Summary: Friendly fire is not turned on in Ranked matches. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a Ranked, Eliminator match.\n2) Users 2-4 join User 1\'s match.\n3) Users begin gameplay.\n4) User 1 attempts to shoot their teammate.\n5) User 1 observes their teammate does not get eliminated.\n\nExpected Results: Friendly fire must be turned on during Ranked matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6235,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania: The User observes floating benches, located behind the Red-team base.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, if the User navigates to the Red-team base, the User observes that there are 2 benches behind the base which appear floating a few feet off the ground.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User enters gameplay in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.\n2) From their starting position, the User navigates their character to the Red-team base.\n3) User observes that there are two benches floating off the ground, located behind the Red base.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe benches must not appear floating.\n\nNOTE: This occurs in both Single Player and MultiPlayer.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6236,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - When a Host or Client disconnects out of a multiplayer game, they are not brought back to the Main Menu.','Summary:\nWhen a Host or Client disconnects out of a multiplayer game, they are not brought back to the Main Menu.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 Creates a Rank Match or Player Match\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s game\n3) User 2 sets Ready, User 1 Starts the Game\n4) Gameplay Begins\n5) If either user disconnects the ethernet cable from the console\n6) The message \"You have been disconnect from Xbox Live and will be returned to the Main Menu.\"\n9) When User selects OK, the User is returned to the System Link Menu.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen user selects OK on the \"You have been disconnected from Xbox Live and will be returned to the Main Menu.\" message, the user must be returned to the Main Menu.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6237,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,2,'(80%-89%)','Frequently - Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: Users load in floating above the ground with the camera bouncing uncontrollably.','Summary:\nFrequently, Users load into gameplay floating above the ground with the camera bouncing uncontrollably. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 hosts a Ranked or PLayer Match in any game mode (Elimination,CTF,CF)\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s game\n3) Users load into gameplay and observe they are floating in the air and the camera is bouncing up/down.\n\nExpected Results:\nUsers must load into gameplay correctly.\n\nNOTE(1): This bug is most prominent in Woodsball ranked matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6238,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer - Game Lobby: Clients are brought back to the Main Menu if the Host disconnects the Ethernet cord from the console.','Summary:\nOn the Multiplayer game lobby screen, if the Host disconnects the Ethernet cord from the console, the Clients are brought back to the Main Menu.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu signed into Xbox Live\n2) The Host selects Multiplayer\n3) The Host selects Xbox Live\n4) The Host selects Player Match or Ranked Match\n5) The Host selects Create Game and selects any game settings\n6) The Host proceeds to the Game Lobby\n7) The Client joins the Host\'s created game and enters the Game Lobby\n8) The Host disconnects the Ethernet cord from the console \n9) The Client receives the message, \"Disconnected from the Host.\"\n10) The Client selects OK and observes they are brought back to the Main Menu.\n\nExpected Results:\nClients must be returned to the Xbox Live screen if the Host disconnects on the Game Lobby.\n\nNote: This also occurs if the Host manually quits out of the game lobby.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6239,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,3,1224720000,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally - Crash - Loading Screens: Game crashes when loading into gameplay after hours of continuous play.','Summary:\nOccasionally, the game will crash on the loading screen when entering gameplay after a few hours of continuous play.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Play various modes of gameplay for 2+ hours,\n2) Loading into gameplay in any gameplay type,\n3) Observe that the game crashes occasionally when loading into gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nGame must not crash.\n\nNote (1) This has occurred when loading into the following locations:\n- Once, after completing Fitness Stage 2, loading into Fitness Stage 3.\n- Once, loading into Exhibition - Woodsball - San Diego Field.\n- Once, loading into the 6th match of Career Mode - NPPL Houston (Pro).\n- Once, loading into the first match of Career Mode - Tempe Invitational (Division 2).\n- Twice, loading into Quick Play, San Diego, California.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6240,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Speedball - Bakersfield, California: The Jump locations for the \"snake\" bunkers are misaligned with the bunkers.','Summary:\nDuring Multiplayer gameplay, Speedball, Bakersfield, California, the Jump locations for the \"snake\" bunkers are misaligned with the bunkers.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Multiplayer,\n2) Select Xbox Live,\n3) Enter Speedball gameplay at Bakersfield, California,\n4) Navigate the User\'s Avatar to just in front of any of the \"snake\" bunkers (especially the two near the center of the field),\n5) Observe that the Jump distance is extremely far away from the actual bunker.\n\nExpected Results:\nGameplay functions, such as Jump, must be consistent throughout gameplay.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6241,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,8,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Credits: In the credits, there is white text that appears as \"Additional Music provided by\" and the line below it is in yellow text that reads: \"DeWolfe Music Library\" which appears inconsistent with the rest of the credits.','Summary:\nIn the credits, there is white text that appears as \"Additional Music provided by\" and the line below it is in yellow text that reads: \"DeWolfe Music Library\" which appears inconsistent with the rest of the credits. This is located close to the very end of the credits.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Select Credits from the main menu\n2) Watch the right side of the screen as the screen scrolls through the credits\n3a) Observe, the white text appears as:\n\"Additional Music provided by\"\n\nChange to:\n\"Additional Music provided by\" in yellow text \n\nBy changing the text to the color yellow to remain consistent with the rest of the credits\n\n3b) Observe, the yellow text appears as:\n\"DeWolfe Music Library\"\n\nChange to:\n\"DeWolfe Music Library\" in white text\n\nBy changing the text to the color white to remain consistent with the rest of the credits','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6243,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: If all of the Clients on the enemy team, exit the game during gameplay, the Host remains in gameplay.','Summary:\nDuring multiplayer gameplay, if all of the Clients on the enemy team, exit the game , the Host remains in gameplay.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default Player Match game lobby\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s game lobby\n3) User 1 presses the Left Trigger button to add one bot to their team\n4) Users progress to gameplay\n5) Gameplay begins, User 2 presses the START button to access the pause menu\n6) User 2 selects Quit Match and exits the game\n7) User 1 observes they are still in gameplay with no opponents on the enemy team.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser 1 must not stay in a game with no opponents on the enemy team.\n\nNote: This issue also occurs in System Link.\nNote: If this occurs during an elimination match, the Users must either exit via the pause menu or wait for the time limit expires.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6244,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,2,3,3,1224720000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Scoring - Gameplay: The user is given an elimination point for eliminating the flag carrier as the flag is being hung.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, in a Center Flag or Capture the Flag match, if the user shoots the enemy teams flag carrier as the flag is being hung, the user will get the point for eliminating the flag carrier, and the enemy team will get the point for scoring the flag.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter gameplay in a center flag or capture the flag match,\n2) Move to the right or left of the flag station 10 feet,\n3) Press the up directional button to cause your team to charge and become eliminated,\n4) Wait for the enemy teams flag carrier to get with in arms reach of the flag station,\n5) Shoot the enemy team\'s flag carrier,\n6) Observe that the paintballs do not reach the enemy team\'s flag carrier until after the flag has been hung.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must not be given a point for eliminating the flag carrier as the flag is being hung on the flag station.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6245,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,3,1224720000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Options: Options are not set to default settings when starting a new game','Summary:\nIn the Options menu, if the user changes the settings in the Options menu, exits to the New Game/Load Game screen from the Main Menu, selects New Game, proceeds to the Main Menu, selects Options, the settings are not set to the default setting and are instead the same settings as the previous save profile\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Options on the Main Menu\n2) Changes any of the settings in the Options Menu\n3) Backs out to the Main Menu\n4) Backs out from the Main Menu to the New Game/Load Game screen\n5) Selects New Game\n6) Proceeds to the Main Menu\n7) Selects Options\n8) Notice that the settings are from the previously exited save profile and are not set to the default settings\n\nExpected Results:\nAll settings in the Options menu must be set to default settings when creating a New Game','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6246,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,9,2,3,1224720000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Collision Detection - Woodsball - Train Depot Field: User\'s character is able to clip into and get stuck in side of the train cars.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Woodsball- Train Depot Field, if the user\'s character moves to a train car, moves to the end without the hitch, when facing the end of the train car move just to the left of the right wheel, move into the prone position, on the way into the prone position press forward, move into the crouch position when one the ground, Observe that the user\'s character is clipping the train and is now stuck in the train. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter gameplay in Woodsball- Train Depot Field,\n2) Moves to a train car\n3) Move to the end without the hitch\n4) Face the end of the train car,\n5) Move just to the left of the right wheel, while pressing against the end of the train,\n6) Move into the prone position,\n7) On the way into the prone position move forward by pressing up on the left analog stick,\n8) Move into the crouch position as quick as possible,\n9) Observe that the user\'s character is clipping the train and is now stuck in the train.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser\'s character must not become stuck.\n\nNote(1)\nVideo Capture is available.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6248,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,4,1224720000,0,0,0,2,'(80%-89%)','Frequently - TRC [R021] - Multiplayer: The user experiences a Loading screen longer than 2 minutes when signing out and signing back in within the first 11 SECONDS of the Loading Screen from the Game Lobby into Gameplay','Summary:\nThe user experiences a Loading screen longer than 2 minutes when signing out and signing back in within the first 11 SECONDS of the Loading Screen from the Game Lobby into Gameplay.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default Player Match.\n2) User 2 joins User 1\'s match.\n3) User 1 begins the lobby countdown.\n4) User 1 presses the PS Menu button, and prepares to sign-out by highlighting their Online ID.\n5) User 1 signs-out as quickly as possible when the loading screen appears.\n6) User 1 immediately signs-in to their Online ID after signing out. (Timing specific, needs to be done as quickly as possible)\n7) Users observe a loading screen of 2 minutes or longer.\n\nExpected Results:\nUsers must not experience a Loading Screen lasting longer than 30 seconds.\n\nNOTE(1): Host and Client\'s connection times out and they are returned to the menu system.\nNOTE(2): Also occurs during Ranked Match.\nNOTE(3): Host recieves an incorrect \"Connection with the host has been lost\" message.\n\nTRC [R021] - The title does not leave the User in an unplayable state for long periods of time.','jhh\n','[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/27/2008 03:33:53 PM]\nWe could not reproduce this bug. It may be fixed.\nIf it still occurs please send a video capture. \n\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/28/2008 09:45:59 AM]\nVideo on FTP here: /Paintball/AMP QA Bug Captures and Dumps/Video Capture/PS3\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/28/2008 01:04:27 PM]\ncould not reproduce it\n\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 05:37:28 AM]\nVerified in the 10/28 build. Steps to reproduce has been edited and simplified.test\n',''),(6251,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,3,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Gameplay: When sprinting and jumping over a beam bunker, if the user relases the Left Bumper, the user continues to sprint','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in any Speedball match, if the user sprints towards a beam bunker, jumps over it, then releases the Left Bumper just as the user\'s character lands, the user\'s character continues to perform the sprint action.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select any mode of play.\n2) Select any Speedball match in any location that has jumpable beam bunkers (e.g. the NPPL Buffalo Tournament in Career Mode).\n3) When gameplay begins, eliminate all AI opponents and grab the flag before friendly AI characters do.\n4) Find any beam bunker the user is able to jump over, and back away from it so that it will only take the user ~5 seconds to sprint towards the bunker and jump it.\n5) Simultaneously press the Left Bumper and Left Stick forward to sprint towards the beam bunker, and immediately begin counting.\n6) When the user\'s character is close enough to jump over the bunker, press the A button to jump.\n7) Just as the user\'s character lands (~5 seconds after beginning the sprint), release ONLY the Left Bumper so that the user is only pressing the Left Stick forward, and observe that the user character continues to sprint.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen the user releases the Left Bumper, the user\'s character must stop sprinting.\n\nNOTE(1): Bug appears to be timing specific. When the user simultaneously presses the Left Bumper and Left Stick forward, the user should immediately begin counting seconds. It should only take ~5 seconds from the time the user starts running until the time the user\'s character lands.\n\nNOTE(2): When the bug occurs, the user\'s character continues to sprint (the marker continues to pump up and down) until the user turns using the Right Stick at a sharp angle. The user is also able to shoot their marker while it is pumping up and down.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6252,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,2,'(90%-99%)','Frequently - Video/Graphic - Gameplay: When the User\'s Character Slides or Jumps while running the arm holding the marker keeps moving as if the User\'s Character is running','Summary:\nFrequently, during gameplay, if the User\'s Character Slides or Jumps while running the arm holding the marker keeps moving as if the User\'s Character is running, distorting the view of the User.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the initial start of any level,\n2) During gameplay Press and hold the Left Bumper while tilting the Left Analogue Stick forward, \n3) Proceed to run towards a bunker until a the \"Press A Button to slide or jump\" prompt appears,\n4) Press the A Button to slide or jump.\n5) Observe the arm holding the marker is still moving as though the User\'s character is running.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Running animation must not appear while the User\'s Character is sliding or jumping.\n\nNOTE(1): The animation distorts the Users aim wile in the air or sliding on the ground.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6256,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 014 - System Link Games List: The game name always appears as \"SV_PAINTBALL\"','Summary:\nThe game name always appears as \"SV_PAINTBALL\"\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the System Link Menu, with a joinable System Link present.\n2) The Player selects Join Game.\n3) The Games List appears, and the following text appears as the game name:\n\n\"SV_Paintball\"\n\nExpected Results:\nThe System Link game name must not contain debug text, and must appear as the Game Type; \"Capture The Flag\", \"Center Flag\", or \"Elimination\". \n\nGames must not output debug information via the network, on-screen messages, or a file on any storage device. This is a violation of TCR 014.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6257,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 103 - System Link Games List: Only one System Link game is listed at a time','Summary:\nOnly one System Link game is listed at a time\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the System Link Menu, with at least two joinable System Link present.\n2) The Player selects Join Game.\n3) The Games List appears, and only one System Link game appears on the Games List.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must list all joinable System Link games at the time of the search.\n\nThe game must discover sessions for system link play in no more than three seconds. This is a violation of TCR 103.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6260,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 081 - Player Match: During Player Match Gameplay, the match still appears joinable on the Player Match Games List.','Summary:\nDuring Player Match Gameplay, the match still appears joinable on the Player Match Games List.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Player Match Menu, with a Player Match game currently in gameplay.\n2) The Player selects Custom Match.\n3) The Custom Match Menu appears.\n4) The Player changes the filters to a Player Match that is in gameplay.\n5) The Player presses the A (Search) button.\n6) The Games List appears, and the Player Match that is currently in gameplay appears on the Player Match Games List.\n\nExpected Results:\nA Custom Match game search must only return available Player Match games that are joinable.\n\nGames must have a Quick Match and a Custom Match option for both Standard and Ranked game session options. The Quick Match option must allow the player to enter the game session using a sequence of default button presses. This is a violation of TCR 081.\n\nNotes:\n1) The Player\'s game also appears Joinable to Friends or Players that attempt to Join Session in Progress. The Join does not succeed (the game is not joinable once gameplay begins)\n2) This is related to TCR 115. \n3) This is related to issue 6141.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6263,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,4,1224720000,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Multiplayer: All User\'s experienced an infinite load screen after the Host spammed X from the Lobby until a minute after viewing the load screen.','Summary:\nOccasionally, Host started a match, began spamming X to start the match and continued to spam X while the loading screen appeared, game was caught in an infinite load screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Selected Multiplayer,\n2) Selected Local Network,\n3) Selected to Create a match,\n4) As another Client joined the match and pressed X to enter gameplay,\n5) The Host began spamming X, and continued to do so until the Loading screen,\n6) Observed the game was stuck on an infinite load screen.\n\nExpected Results:\nGame must load properly into multiplayer matches.','jhh\n','[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 04:19:02 AM]\nVerified in the 10/28 buildtest\n',''),(6264,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,2,'(90%-99%)','Frequently (90% - 99%) - Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: In the Your Gear Menu in Xbox LIVE and System Link matches, the menu is extremely laggy and skips over items','Summary:\nFrequently, in the Your Gear Menu in Xbox LIVE Player Match and System Link games, the menu is extremely laggy and skips over items when users scroll through the available gear options. Only menus with two available items do not have any skipping.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Multiplayer,\n2) Select either System Link or an Xbox LIVE Player Match and host a game,\n3) Choose any location, game type, round limit, and available gear options,\n4) In the Lobby, press the [Left Stick] to access the Your Gear Menu,\n5) Scroll through all the available gear options by pressing up, down, left, and right on the [Directional Pad],\n6) Observe that it takes a long time for gear to appear on the user\'s character; additionally, gear is often skipped over as the user scrolls through the menu.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Your Gear Menu in the pre-game Lobby must function correctly.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6265,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 081 - Player Match: Clients are returned to the old Player Match menu when the game ends normally','Summary:\nClients are returned to the old Player Match menu when the game ends normally\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match, with the Player as a Client.\n2) The match ends.\n3) The End of Match Results Screen appears.\n4) The Player presses the A (Continue) button.\n5) A loading screen appears, and the old Player Match appears that has options \"Join Game\" and \"Create Game\".\n\nExpected Results:\nAfter a game ends, the clients must be returned to the correct Player Match Menu, with the options \"Quick Match\", \"Custom Match\" and \"Create Game\".\n\nGames must have a Quick Match and a Custom Match option for both Standard and Ranked game session options. The Quick Match option must allow the player to enter the game session using a sequence of default button presses. This is a violation of TCR 081.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6267,1224806400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Programming Guidelines 11.1 - Menu System: The Save Verification messages do not appear in the HOME Menu','Summary:\nThe Save Verification messages do not appear in the HOME Menu\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu.\n2) The Player presses the HOME Button.\n3) The HOME Menu appears.\n4) The Player selects Wii Menu, and the \"Return to Wii Menu?\" message appears without the Save Verification text.\n\nExpected Results:\nBoth the \"Return to Wii Menu?\" and the \"Reset Game?\" messages must appear with the Save Verification message.\n\nProgramming Guidelines 11.1\n\nNotes:\n1) This also occurs if the Player selects \"RESET\" instead of \"Wii Menu\".','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6268,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Player Match: The Host is moved to the System Link Menu when all the clients quit out of their game','Summary:\nThe Host is moved to the System Link Menu when all the clients quit out of their game\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match, with the Player as the Host.\n2) All the clients quit out of the game.\n3) The \"All players have left\" message appears.\n4) The Player selects Ok\n5) A loading screen appears, and the System Link Menu appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nAfter a game ends, the Host must be returned to the correct Player Match Menu, with the options \"Quick Match\", \"Custom Match\" and \"Create Game\".\n\nNotes:\n1) This issue also occurs if the Players disconnect during the Match Lobby countdown.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6269,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The Viewloader eVLution 3 hopper appears improperly.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, with the Viewloader eVLution 3 hopper equipped, the User observes the hopper appears with a chrome reflective surface which is inaccurate to the way it looks in the menu system.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the main menu, select any Game Mode,\n2) With the Viewloader eVLution 3 hopper equipped, select any level,\n3) observe the Viewloader eVLution 3 hopper appears improperly during gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll equipment must appear consistent throughout gameplay.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6270,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The WGP Stratos airtank appears improperly.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, with the WGP Stratos airtank equipped, the User observes the airtank appears with a chrome reflective surface which is inaccurate to the way it looks in the menu system.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the main menu, select any Game Mode,\n2) With the WGP Stratos airtank equipped, select any level,\n3) observe theWGP Stratos airtank appears improperly during gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll equipment must appear consistent throughout gameplay.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n'