,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Player Match: The Host is moved to the System Link Menu when they quit of of their game','Summary:\nThe Host is moved to the System Link Menu when they quit of of their game\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match, with the Player as the Host.\n2) The Player presses the START (Pause) button.\n3) The Player selects Quit Match.\n4) The Player selects Yes.\n5) A loading screen appears, and the System Link Menu appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen the Host quites, they must be returned to the correct Player Match Menu, with the options \"Quick Match\", \"Custom Match\" and \"Create Game\".\n\nNotes:\n1) This issue also occurs if the Players disconnect during the Match Lobby countdown.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6279,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The Redz Enzy 08 Red left glove appears improperly.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, with the Redz Enzy 08 Red gloves equipped, the User observes the left glove appears with the sponsor text inverted, which is inaccurate to the way it looks in the menu system.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the main menu, select any Game Mode,\n2) With the Redz Enzy 08 Red gloves equipped, select any level,\n3) observe the Redz Enzy 08 Red left glove appears improperly during gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll equipment must appear consistent throughout gameplay.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6282,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Player Match: The clients are moved to the System Link Menu when all the Host quits out of the game','Summary:\nThe clients are moved to the System Link Menu when all the Host quits out of the game\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match, with the Player as a client.\n2) The Host quits out of the match.\n3) A \"Host has left\" message appears.\n4) The Player selects Ok.\n5) A loading screen appears, and the System Link Menu appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen the Host quites, they must be returned to the correct Player Match Menu, with the options \"Quick Match\", \"Custom Match\" and \"Create Game\". \n\nNotes:\n1) This is related to issue 6278.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6284,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The Sly Tyrant Half gloves appear improperly.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, with the Sly Tyrant Half gloves equipped, the User observes the exposed skin appears greasy or shiny like the hands are made of plastic.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the main menu, select any Game Mode,\n2) With the Sly Tyrant Half gloves equipped, select any level,\n3) observe the exposed skin appears improperly during gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll equipment must appear properly throughout gameplay.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6287,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Ranked Match: The Host is moved to the System Link Menu when all the clients quit of of their game','Summary:\nThe Host is moved to the System Link Menu when all the clients quit of of their game\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Ranked Match, with the Player as the Host.\n2) All the clients quit out of the game.\n3) The \"All players have left\" message appears.\n4) The Player selects Ok\n5) A loading screen appears, and the System Link Menu appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nAfter a game ends, the Host must be returned to the Ranked Match Menu.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6288,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity hopper appears improperly.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, with the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity hopper equipped, the User observes the hopper appears with a chrome reflective surface which is inaccurate to the way it looks in the menu system.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the main menu, select any Game Mode,\n2) With the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity hopper equipped, select any level,\n3) observe the Viewloader Dynasty Vlocity hopper appears improperly during gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll equipment must appear consistent throughout gameplay.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6289,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Credits: test team members missing from the credits.','Summary: Test Team members missing from the credits.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Credits.\n2) User observes 3 Test Team members are not included.\n\nChange to: \n\nDavid V. Mitchell\nJustin Kettner\nJames Tjaden\n\nBy adding David V. Mitchell, Justin Kettner, and James Tjaden to the credit text.\n\nNOTE(1): These name are in addition to the existing Test Team names in the credits.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6290,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224720000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Gameplay: If the User\'s Character is sliding and gets hit to bring up the Cheat Meter, the User\'s Character continues to slide an extended distance.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, if the User\'s Character begins a slide and is hit by a paintball, the Cheat Meter is displayed, while the Cheat Meter is displayed the User\'s Character continues to slide for an extended distance.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Select any gameplay,\n2) Proceed from the home base toward the opponents base,\n3) While sprinting, press X to slide,\n4) Allow the User\'s Character to get hit while sliding so the Cheat Meter is displayed,\n5) Observe the User\'s Character continues to slide while the Cheat Meter is displayed.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser\'s Character must slide the proper distance at all times.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6292,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 071 - Player Match: There is no way to access the Gamer Card of the listed Players on the in-game Stats Screen','Summary:\nThere is no way to access the Gamer Card of the listed Players on the in-game Stats Screen\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match.\n2) The Player presses the BACK button.\n3) The in-game Stats Screen appears, and there is no way to highlight or select any highlighted Gamertag.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must be able to highlight any in-game Gamertag, and view the Gamer Card of the selected Gamertag.\n\nGames must provide the player the option to access another player’s gamer card wherever gamertags are enumerated. This is a violation of TCR 071.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6293,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 071 - Ranked Match: There is no way to access the Gamer Card of the listed Players on the in-game Stats Screen','Summary:\nThere is no way to access the Gamer Card of the listed Players on the in-game Stats Screen\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Ranked Match.\n2) The Player presses the BACK button.\n3) The in-game Stats Screen appears, and there is no way to highlight or select any highlighted Gamertag.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must be able to highlight any in-game Gamertag, and view the Gamer Card of the selected Gamertag.\n\nGames must provide the player the option to access another player’s gamer card wherever gamertags are enumerated. This is a violation of TCR 071.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6294,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,2,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Scoring - Player Match: Scores of the bots do not show up on the in-game Stats Screen','Summary:\nScores of the bots do not show up on the in-game Stats Screen \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, Player Match, with at least one bot present.\n2) The Player presses the BACK button.\n3) The in-game Stats Screen appears, and there score or listing for the bot.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe bots must be listed on the in-game stats screen.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6295,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,2,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Scoring - System Link: Scores of the bots do not show up on the in-game Stats Screen','Summary:\nScores of the bots do not show up on the in-game Stats Screen \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, System Link, with at least one bot present.\n2) The Player presses the BACK button.\n3) The in-game Stats Screen appears, and there score or listing for the bot.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe bots must be listed on the in-game stats screen.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6296,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 022 - Field Creator: The Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed after selecting Store Custom Field for ~3 seconds to ~5 seconds','Summary:\nThe Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed after selecting Store Custom Field for ~3 seconds to ~5 seconds\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Field Creator.\n2) the Player presses the START (Pause) button.\n3) The Player selects Store Custom Field.\n4) The Player quickly presses the Xbox Guide button, and the Xbox Guide Blade does not appear for ~3 seconds to ~5 seconds.\n\nExpected Results:\nGames must ensure that system UI can be rendered at least every 66 milliseconds in all areas of the game for any display mode. This is a violation of TCR 022.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6297,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 022 - Gear Store: The Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed after selecting Gear Store for ~3 seconds to ~5 seconds','Summary:\nThe Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed after selecting Gear Store for ~3 seconds to ~5 seconds \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Career Menu.\n2) The Player selects Gear Store.\n3) The Player quickly presses the Xbox Guide button, and the Xbox Guide Blade does not appear for ~3 seconds to ~5 seconds.\n\nExpected Results:\nGames must ensure that system UI can be rendered at least every 66 milliseconds in all areas of the game for any display mode. This is a violation of TCR 022. \n\nNotes:\n1) The time it takes until the Xbox Guide Blade appears seems to take longer when more items are unlocked.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6298,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 022 - Team Outfit: The Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed after selecting Team Outfit for ~3 seconds to ~5 seconds','Summary:\nThe Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed after selecting Team Outfit for ~3 seconds to ~5 seconds \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Career Menu.\n2) The Player selects Team Outfit.\n3) The Player quickly presses the Xbox Guide button, and the Xbox Guide Blade does not appear for ~3 seconds to ~5 seconds.\n\nExpected Results:\nGames must ensure that system UI can be rendered at least every 66 milliseconds in all areas of the game for any display mode. This is a violation of TCR 022. \n\nNotes:\n1) The time it takes until the Xbox Guide Blade appears seems to take longer when more items are unlocked.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6299,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 029 - Field Creator: An unnecessary message appears after storing a Field Creator map.','Summary:\nAn unnecessary message appears after storing a Field Creator map.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Field Creator.\n2) The Player presses the START (Pause) button.\n3) The Pause Menu appears.\n4) The Player selects Store Custom Field.\n5) The Store Custom Field list appears.\n6) The Player selects any slot.\n7) The Map Name Menu appears.\n8) The Player selects Done, and the following text appears:\n\n\"Custom field saved succesfully.\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Custom field stored successfully.\"\n\nby changing the text \"saved succesfully.\" to the text \"stored successfully.\"\n\nWhen an error prevents a game from performing a task dictated by the player or expected under normal gameplay, the game must display a user-friendly message that addresses the error. The game must transparently handle software errors that are not relevant to gameplay. This is a violation of TCR 029.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6300,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Menu System: The Pre-earned text for the Achievement \"Speedball Chief\" is incorrectly displayed','Summary:\nThe Pre-earned text for the Achievement “Speedball Chief” is incorrectly displayed.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Gamer Profile signed in that has not earned the \"Speedball Chief\" Achievement.\n2) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n3) The Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n4) The Player selects the Gamer Profile.\n5) The Player selects View Games.\n6) The Player selects Paintball 2009.\n7) The Player selects the Achievement Speedball Chief, and the following Pre-earned text appears: \n\n“Win at least 50 Speedball Ranked matches over Xbox LIVE”\n\nChange to:\n\n“Win at least 50 Speedball Ranked Matches over Xbox LIVE”\n\nby changing the text \"matches\" to the text \"Matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6301,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Menu System: The Pre-earned text for the Achievement \"Woodsball Chief\" is incorrectly displayed','Summary:\nThe Pre-earned text for the Achievement “Woodsball Chief” is incorrectly displayed.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Gamer Profile signed in that has not earned the \"Woodsball Chief\" Achievement.\n2) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n3) The Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n4) The Player selects the Gamer Profile.\n5) The Player selects View Games.\n6) The Player selects Paintball 2009.\n7) The Player selects the Achievement Woodsball Chief, and the following Pre-earned text appears: \n\n“Win at least 50 Woodsball matches over Xbox LIVE”\n\nChange to:\n\n“Win at least 50 Woodsball Ranked Matches over Xbox LIVE”\n\nBy changing the text \"matches\" to the text \"Ranked Matches\".','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6302,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Menu System: The Post-earned text for the Achievement \"Speedball Chief\" is incorrectly displayed','Summary:\nThe Post-earned text for the Achievement \"Speedball Chief\" is incorrectly displayed.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Gamer Profile signed in that has earned the \"Speedball Chief\" Achievement.\n2) The Player presses the Xbox Guide button.\n3) The Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n4) The Player selects the Gamer Profile.\n5) The Player selects View Games.\n6) The Player selects Paintball 2009.\n7) The Player selects the Achievement Speedball Chief, and the following Post-earned text appears: \n\n\"Won at least 50 Speedball Ranked matches over Xbox LIVE\"\n\nChange to:\n\n\"Won at least 50 Speedball Ranked Matches over Xbox LIVE\"\n\nBy changing the text \"matches\" to the text \"Matches\".','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6303,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Gameplay: Xbwatson reports errors when in Gameplay','Summary:\nXbwatson reports XNET errors when in Gameplay\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, while monitoring the Xbox 360 console and the Player using Controller 1.\n2) The following text appears in the XbWatson output:\n\n\"[XNET:1] Warning: recv failed: 10054\"\n\nExpected Results:\nThere must not be unexpected errors reported to XbWatson\n\nNotes:\n1) This also occurs in career mode. \n2) Other output has also been seen.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6312,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,15,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Legal - Career Mode: The User appears to be able to turn on ramping for Career Mode.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Career Mode, if the User selects Career Mode, then selects any tournament, then during the round of gameplay accesses the options menu and goes to the gameplay options, the option to turn on ramping appears to be available.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career Mode,\n2) Select Tournament Play,\n3) Select any tournament,\n4) Proceed through the screens that appear until the match starts,\n5) Press the START Button,\n6) Select Options,\n7) Select Gameplay,\n8) Observe that an option to turn on or turn off ramping appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nRamping must not be available during tournament play.\n\nNOTE(1): Both NPPL & ME rulebooks strictly prohibit the use of ramping in tournament speedball gameplay. It may; however, be left in woodsball.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6313,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Crash - Multiplayer: In a System Link match the game crashes with one Woodsball marker and one Speedball marker equipped.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Multiplayer, in a System Link match, with the Spyder MR2 Speedball marker equipped on any two players and the Tippman X7 MP5 SD equipped on two other players, the Host crashes on the loading screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Multiplayer,\n2) Select System Link,\n3) Make the Spyder MR2 Speedball marker available,\n4) Make the Tippman X7 MP5 SD Woodsball marker available,\n5) Two Players from either team select the Spyder MR2 Speedball marker,\n6) Two Players from either team select the Tippman X7 MP5 SD Woodsball marker,\n7) Observe the host crash while loading in to gameplay.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash.\n\nNOTE(1): Crash dump available.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6315,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,15,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Legal - Career Mode - All Millennium tournaments must implement the M7 rules (5 vs 5 Elimination).','Summary:\nDuring Career Mode, all Millennium tournaments must implement the M7 rules (5 vs 5 Elimination). \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1)Start Malaga Spain - Millennium Iberian Cup\n2)Notice that the game is not a 5 on 5 Elimination type match and does not implement the M7 format\n\nExpected Results:\nAll Millennium tournaments must implement the M7 format rules. \n\nNOTE: For each Millennium tournament, we should make it so that the user has a roster of 5 with no team switching out.\n\nList of Millennium tournaments:\n12a - Malaga, Spain - Millennium Iberian Cup\n16a - London, England - Millennium SPL Campaign Cup\n19a - Toulouse, France - Millennium SPL World Cup\n22a - Nurburgring, Germany - Millennium MAXS CPL European Masters\n25a - Paris, France - Millennium CPL French Open','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6316,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: All barrels starting from the FL Firebird barrel appears as the previous barrel listed in system link gameplay.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in a System Link match, all barrels starting from the FL Firebird barrel appears as the previous barrel listed.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Multiplayer.\n2) Select System Link.\n3) Host selects Create Match.\n4) Host selects a Speedball or Woodsball match.\n5) Host clicks the Left Stick in to edit the player gear.\n6) Host sets any paintball marker, any hopper, any barrel starting from FL Firebird barrel, any air tank, any harness, any woodsball combo, any mask, any gloves, any pants, and any shoes.\n7) Host continues to the Lobby and waits for clients.\n8) Host begins game.\n9) When gameplay begins, all users observe that the paintball marker barrel appears as the barrel listed before it,\n\nExpected Results:\nAll paintball marker barrels must appear correctly.\n\nNOTE: List of Barrels affected: \n\nFL Firebird shows as: JT Tetra\nInsert Nightstick shows as:FL Firebird \nDLX Luxe shows as: Insert Nightstick\nSpyder Pilot shows as: DLX Luxe\nSmart Parts All American Barrel shows as: Spyder Pilot \nBob Long Vice shows as: Smart Parts All American Barrel\nBob Long Rapper shows as: Bob Long Vice\nSly Diesel Black shows as: Bob Long Rapper\nSly Pro-Merc Black shows as: Sly Diesel Black','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6331,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Breakout Planner: User plan resets between the first and second round of any Quickplay, or Exhibition match.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Breakout Planner, in any quickplay or exhibition match, when the User completes the first round, and loads into the Breakout Planner for the second round, the planner resets the player positions back to the default settings.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu select Quickplay, or Exhibition,\n2) Select any match with more then 1 player on each side, and more then one round,\n3) Load the Breakout Planner and set custom positions for the User\'s Team, \n4) Begin gameplay, and complete the first round, \n5) Load into the Breakout Planner,\n6) Observe the Breakout Planner no longer has the custom settings from step 3,\n\nExpected Results:\nBreakout Planner settings must carry over from round to round.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6332,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,1,1224892800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gear Store: The Empire Events mask appears with graphical corruption.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, Gear Store, the Empire Events mask appears with graphical corruption in the form of moving black lines below the visor.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Career Mode.\n2) Select Gear Store.\n3) Move the cursor over to the Masks section (the user must complete the second tournament to unlock this mask).\n4) Select the Empire Events mask.\n4) Observe the moving black lines on the mask.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll graphics must appear without corruption.\n\nNOTE1: Video available.\nNOTE2: Graphical corruption also occurs when displayed in Team Outfit.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6333,1224892800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally (1%-9%) - Gameplay - Multiplayer: In System Link matches on two Woodsball maps, the users\' characters did not spawn into the level correctly','Summary:\nOccasionally, during System Link matches in the Tippmann and Train Depot Field Woodsball levels, the users\' characters spawned in the air above the maps and constantly fell towards the ground.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, the user selected Multiplayer,\n2) The user selected any kind of Woodsball game with any amount of players,\n3) He then selected System Link,\n4) He chose either Train Depot Field or Tippmann Field,\n5) Finally, he selected any game type with any amount of players,\n6) During gameplay, he observed that all the characters fell constantly towards the ground, making gameplay nearly impossible.\n\nExpected Results:\nCharacters must spawn into the level properly during System Link Woodsball matches.\n\nNOTE(1): This issue occurred with one human user and a team of bots, and also with three human users and no bots.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6334,1224892800,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,6,2,1,1224892800,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Crash - Speedball - Las Vegas, Nevada: The game crashed while spamming C and Z buttons on the load screen.','Summary:\nOnce, during gameplay, when the User was loading into Career Mode, Las Vegas, Nevada the User spammed the C and Z buttons on the loading screen and the User observed the game crash leaving a white dot on the left side of the screen and replaying the same 4 seconds of audio.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, selected Career Mode,\n2) With Las Vegas, Nevada Unlocked, loaded into Las Vegas, Nevada,\n3) On the load screen the User spammed the C and Z buttons,\n4) The User observed the game crash on the loading screen leaving a white dot on the left side of the screen and replaying the same 4 seconds of audio. \n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must NOT crash.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(6335,1224979200,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,10,4,1,1224892800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Audio/Sound - Gameplay: There is no buzzer sound when a character picks up a flag or returns it to the base.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, there is no buzzer sound when a character picks up the opponent\'s flag or when he returns it to the flag base.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, enter into any mode of gameplay with Capture the Flag.\n2) When gameplay begins, retrieve the enemy\'s flag.\n3) Return the flag to the flag station.\n4) Observe that there is no buzzer when the user\'s character picks up the flag or returns it to the base.\n\nExpected Results:\nThere must be a buzzer sound when a character (user\'s character or AI) picks up a flag and when it is returned to the base.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6336,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,4,1224720000,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally - Technical Check - Multiplayer : When the user selects a match from the games list, the user is brought back to the games list instead of joining the game lobby.','Summary:\nWhen the user joins a default multiplayer match by selecting the match from the games list, after the loading screen into the lobby has finished, the games list appears on the screen for the user instead of the game lobby.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User1 creates a default multiplayer match\n2) User2 selects join game, default filters\n3) User2 selects User1\'s match from the games list\n4) The loading screen appears and finishes\n5) Occasionally, after loading the user has the games list displayed on screen\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must load directly into the game lobby of a selected multiplayer match.\n\nNOTE(1): If the user presses the circle button when the games list appears after loading, the user will receive an error message upon trying to join the match again and must back out to the main menu in order to join a new match.\nNOTE(2): TTY attached.\nNOTE(3): Has taken at least 30 ticks for this to occur.\nNOTE(4): This issue seems to occur more frequently from a fresh boot on both user\'s consoles.','jhh\n','[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/26/2008 09:38:31 PM]\nTTY report added to the issue on 10/26/08 from the 10/23 build\n\n[vDev13 Fun Labs (AMP Dev) -- 10/28/2008 01:12:38 PM]\ncould not reproduce it\n\n[Dean Fingerholz (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/28/2008 01:58:12 PM]\nReproduced on 10.26.08 build. 2 new TTYs have been attached.\n\n[John Hart (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 04:19:02 AM]\nVerified in the 10/28 buildtest\n',''),(6345,1224979200,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,9,2,1,1224892800,0,0,0,3,'(10%-19%)','Occasionally - Collision Detection - Train Depot Field: User is able to Dive into the wood stacks and become stuck inside','Summary:\nOccasionally, during Gameplay, at Train Depot Field, the user Dove into the wood stacks and became stuck inside.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Entered Train Depot Field,\n2) Navigated to a stack of wood,\n6) Ran towards the center of the wood pile,\n7) Dove just before reaching the wood stack,\n8) Observed that by diving into the wood stack the user\'s character had becoming stuck inside.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll objects must have proper collision.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(6346,1224979200,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,3,3,1,1224892800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Dynasty Training Drills - Leaning and Snapping Stage 2: The user\'s character fails an objective before time runs out when remaining in the snapping position','Summary:\nDuring Dynasty Training Drills, in Leaning and Snapping Stage 2, if the user\'s character eliminates the opponents in the snapping position, remains in the snapping position as time runs out, the user\'s character fails the objective before time runs out\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Dynasty Training Drills on the Main Menu\n2) Progresses through the drills until the Leaning and Snapping drill is unlocked\n3) Progresses through Stage 1 of Leaning and Snapping\n4) Proceeds into Stage 2\n5) The user\'s character eliminates the indicated opponent while in the snapping position as quickly as possible\n6) Remains in the snapping position instead of returning to the normal position as the remaining time runs down\n7) The user\'s character fails the objective before time has run out\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user\'s character must not fail an objective until time is up','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(6347,1224979200,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,12,3,1,1224892800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Gear Store: When the User selects to buy something the prompt asking to buy the item is defaulted to Yes.','Summary:\nAfter selecting to buy an item in the Gear Store, the User is prompted with the message, \"Do you want to buy this item?\", the default selection is Yes.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter the Gear Store,\n2) Select to buy any item, \n3) Observe the prompt asking the User, \"Do you want to buy this item?\", the default selection is Yes.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe default selection in the prompt must be No.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(6348,1224979200,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,9,3,1,1224892800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Collision Detection - Woodsball - Gold Mine Field: The user\'s character becomes stuck on top of the table in the small shed','Summary:\nDuring Exhibition, in Woodsball - Gold Mine Field, if the user\'s character enters the small shed to the right of the user\'s flag station, sprints and dives towards the table in the corner, the user\'s character is able to dive on top of the table and becomes stuck when standing or crouching\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Exhibition on the Main Menu\n2) Selects a Woodsball match\n3) Selects Gold Mine Field\n4) Proceeds into gameplay\n5) Moves into the small shed to the right of the spawn point\n6) Sprints and dives towards the table\n7) The user\'s character is able to get on top of the table while diving, and becomes stuck if the user\'s character stands or crouches while on the table\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user\'s character must not be able to dive onto the table\n\nNote: The same shed appears in Woodsball - Jungle Park\nNote: User\'s character is able to get off the table while in the prone stance','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(6349,1224979200,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,12,2,1,1224892800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Exhibition: Left and Right navigation is unresponsive.','Summary:\nIn the Exhibition menu, if the user presses the 2 (Woodsball) Button, selects the Train Depot Field, presses Left or Right on the + Control Pad 1 or more times, presses the B (Back) Button, and attempts to navigate Left or Right through the Woodsball fields, the menu remains unresponsive.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu navigate to the exhibition menu,\n2) Press the 2 (Woodsball) Button and navigate to the field selection menu for woodsball tournaments,\n3) Highlight Train Depot Field,\n4) Press the A Button to go to the Match Summary,\n5) Press and hold Right on the Control Stick,\n6) Press the B (Back) Button to go back to the field selection menu,\n7) Observe that the menu has lost right and left functionality with the Control Stick and the + Control Pad.\n\nExpected Results:\nMenus must function properly.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(6351,1224979200,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,8,3,1,1224892800,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Career Mode - Results: The credits text appears the same after completing a tournament a 2nd time.','Summary:\nDuring Career gameplay, when the user completes a tournament that has previously been completed, the results screen appears with the same credit text as the first time it was completed, i.e. 800 Credits for completing National Shootout Challenge.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu select Career Mode\n2) Select Play Tournament\n3) Select any tournament\n4) Complete the tournament in 1st place\n5) Complete the same tournament a second time in 1st place\n6) The results screen appears with the same amount of credits awarded to the user the second time completing the tournament as the first time completing the tournament\n\nExpected Results:\nThe results screen must appear properly at all times.\n\nNote(1): Although the results screen shows that the user is being credited again for completing a tournament a second time, the credits are not added to the total credits appearing in the Gear Store or Team Manager menus.','jhh\nassigned\nreassigned\n','test\n',''),(6353,1224979200,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,4,1224720000,0,0,0,2,'(50%-59%)','Frequently - Crash - Multiplayer: If the Host ejects their game disc via the XMB during the countdown to loading into gameplay, the Host crashes on a black screen.','Summary:\nIn the Multiplayer Game Lobby, if the Host ejects their game disc via the XMB during the countdown to loading into gameplay, the Host crashes on a black screen, their PS3 beeps three times and the green indicator light remains on.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Multiplayer,\n2) Select Playstation Network,\n3) Select Player Match,\n4) User 1 creates a game,\n5) Users 2-3 join User 1\'s game and ready-up,\n6) User 1 presses the X button to begin the countdown,\n7) User 1 immediately presses the PS button to bring up the XMB,\n8) User 1 highlights the game disc and presses the triangle button,\n9) User 1 selects Eject Disc,\n10) User 1 observes a black screen, their console beeps three times and the green indicator light remains on as their system crashes.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not crash when the disc is ejected.\n\nNote(1): TM Log Files attached (unable to retrieve a PS3 Core Dump; no Core Dump available after this crash occurs).\nNote(2): This issue may be related to issues #3756, 4131, 4218, 4627, 6072.\nNote(3): If the Host is on the Loading into gameplay screen when the game disc is ejected, the Clients are returned to the Player Match Menu, but if the Host ejects the game disc while still in the Game Lobby Countdown the Clients are returned to the Filters Menu.\nNote(4): After the PS3 crashes, it takes a User approximately 10-12 seconds of holding the power button to power down the console.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6354,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay - Woodsball San Diego Field: The world shakes continuously when the Player moves along the windows of the Tippmann house','Summary:\nIn Woodsball San Diego Field, the world will shake continuously when the Player slides along the windows under the awning of the Tippmann house.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) During gameplay, in Woodsball San Diego Field,\n2) The Player proceeds to the Tippmann house.\n3) The Player moves against the wall with the windows under the awning.\n4) The Player moves left/right along the wall and the world starts shaking continuously.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe world must not shake continuously when the Player moves against the Tippmann house.\n\nNotes:\n1) The issue can be resolved by crouching and standing again.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6358,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 043 - Menu System - Field Creator: Text Input devices are not recognized when entering a name to store a custom field','Summary:\nText Input devices are not recognized when entering a name to store a custom field\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, with a Text Input Device connected.\n2) The Player selects Field Creator.\n3) The Field Creator appears.\n4) The Player presses START (pause) button.\n5) The Player selects Store Custom Field.\n6) The Player selects a slot to store the custom field to.\n7) The naming a Custom Field screen appears.\n8) The Player uses the Text Input Device and nothing is recognized.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe TID must be recognized on all keyboard input screens.\n\nGames that allow a player to use a virtual keyboard in their game must also accept input from a physical text input device (TID). This is a violation of TCR 043.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6372,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,4,1224979200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay: The speed difference between \'running\' and \'sprinting\' is not noticeable.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, the speed difference between \'running\' and \'sprinting\' is not noticeable enough.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Proceed into any mode of gameplay\n2) When the match begins, move the left stick forward to begin \'running\'\n3) Notice the movement speed of the user\'s character\n4) Now, move the left stick forward and press and hold the L1 button to begin \'sprinting\'\n5) Observe that the speed difference between \'running\' and \'sprinting\' is barely noticeable.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user\'s character must move slower when \'running\'.','jhh\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 07:11:03 AM]\nStill occurs in the 10/28/08 PS3 build.test\n',''),(6375,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,4,1224979200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: Bunker colors apply to Millenium bunker inconsistently','Summary:\nIn the Field Editor, applying colors swatches to the Millenium bunker yields inconsistent results.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu user selects Field Creator\n2) Loads any Map.\n3) Places a millenium bunker on the field,\n3) Highlights Color Swatch Tool.\n4) Scrolls until color tool displays selection with blue swatch in front of black swatch.\n5) Presses Circle button to load bunker colors.\n6) Observe that the majority of the millenium bunker is blue with the remaining edge colored black.\n7) Scrolls through colors until color tool displays selection with black swatch in front of yellow swatch.\n8) Presses circle button to load bunker colors.\n9) Observe that now the majority of the millenium bunker is yellow with the remaining edge colored black.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe application of the Color swatch choices must have consistent results.','jhh\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/29/2008 07:11:03 AM]\nStill occurs in the 10/28/08 PS3 build.test\n',''),(6378,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: With the green and black color scheme selected, the black color appears gray','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Field Creator, if the user applies the green and black color scheme to the bunkers, the black color appears gray in color.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Field Creator.\n2) Select any pre-made map.\n3) When the level editor appears, press right on the Directional Pad, and then press down on the Directional Pad until the green and black color scheme appears (the green square should appear in front of the black one).\n4) Press the B button to apply the color scheme.\n5) Press the Y button to go into flyby mode, and observe that the areas of the bunker that are supposed to be black in color appear gray in color.\n\nExpected Results:\nWith the green and black color scheme selected, the black color must appear black.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6379,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: With the blue and black color scheme selected, the black color appears gray','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Field Creator, if the user applies the blue and black color scheme to the bunkers, the black color appears gray in color.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Field Creator.\n2) Select any pre-made map.\n3) When the level editor appears, press right on the Directional Pad, and then press down on the Directional Pad until the blue and black color scheme appears (the blue square should appear in front of the black one).\n4) Press the B button to apply the color scheme.\n5) Press the Y button to go into flyby mode, and observe that the areas of the bunker that are supposed to be black in color appear gray in color.\n\nExpected Results:\nWith the blue and black color scheme selected, the black color must appear black.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6383,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: When applying a vertical mirror to the Giant Brick bunker, the two bunkers appear offset from one another','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Field Creator, if the user applies a vertical mirror to the Giant Brick bunker, the two bunkers appear offset from one another.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Field Creator.\n2) Select any pre-made map.\n3) Select the Giant Brick bunker (5X5X10 ft).\n4) Press right on the Directional Pad twice, and set the mirror to vertical.\n5) Observe that the two bunkers that appear do not line up properly, and appear offset from one another.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen applying a vertical mirror to the Giant Brick bunker, they must line up properly.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6384,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: When applying a 4-way mirror to the Giant Brick bunker, the two bunkers appear offset from one another','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Field Creator, if the user applies a 4-way mirror to the Giant Brick bunker, the four bunkers appear offset from one another vertically.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Field Creator.\n2) Select any pre-made map.\n3) Select the Giant Brick bunker (5X5X10 ft).\n4) Press right on the Directional Pad twice, and set the mirror to 4-way.\n5) Observe that the four bunkers that appear do not line up vertically, and appear offset from one another.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen applying a 4-way mirror to the Giant Brick bunker, they must line up properly.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6385,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Field Creator: When applying the red and blue color scheme to the Small Cube bunker, the color scheme does not appear correctly','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Field Creator, if the user applies the red and blue color scheme to the Small Cube bunker, the color pattern appears as the blue and red color scheme.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Field Creator.\n2) Select any pre-made map.\n3) Set the bunker type to the Small Cube (3X3X3 ft).\n4) Press right on the Directional Pad, and select the red and blue color scheme (the red square should appear in front of the blue square), and press the B button to apply.\n5) Observe that when the color scheme loads, the color pattern on the Small Cube bunker appears as the blue and red color scheme.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen applying the red and blue color scheme to the Small Cube bunker, the color pattern must appear properly.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6392,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Dynasty Training Drills: The B button accesses the Help Menu when pressed at the Pause Menu','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Dynasty Training Drills, if the user presses the START button to access the Pause Menu, selects \"Help,\" then presses the A button to return to the Pause Menu, if the user presses the B button, the Help Menu reappears.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Dynasty Training Drills.\n2) Select Accuracy, Fitness, or Leaning and Snapping.\n3) Select any stage.\n4) When the training drill appears, after \"Go,\" press the START button to access the Pause Menu.\n5) Select \"Help\" and press the A button.\n6) When the Help Menu appears, press the A button to return to the Pause Menu.\n7) When the Pause Menu appears again, press the B button, and observe that the Help Menu appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nPressing the B button while in the Pause Menu must not perform any actions.\n\nNOTE(1): If the User repeats steps 6 and 7, the Help Menu continuously appears.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6393,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Career Mode: Upon completing an uncompleted Tournament the User is able to press the Start Button at the Tournament Unlock screen bringing the User back into the match.','Summary:\nCareer Mode: Upon completing an uncompleted Tournament the User is able to press the Start Button at the Tournament Unlock screen bringing the User back into the match.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu Select Career Mode.\n2) Select Play Tournament.\n3) Select an uncompleted tournament.\n4) Play through the tournament normally.\n5) Upon completing the tournament Press the X Button at the Results Screen.\n6) At the Tournament Unlock screen Press the Start Button.\n7) Notice the User will then be brought back to the Match where the User\'s Character and Team will be going through the victory animations.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Start Button must not have functionality during the Tournament Unlock Screen.\n\nNote: The User is able to press the Start Button and Quit the Match this will cause the User to skip the Gear Unlock screen and causes the game not to save.\nNote: The user is also able to press the Start Button to enter the Match again during the Gear Unlock Screen.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6394,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 022 - New Game Menu: The Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed until the FMV starts after selecting Continue','Summary:\nThe Xbox Guide Blade cannot be accessed until the FMV starts after selecting Continue\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the New Game Menu, with a Gamer Profile signed in, a Saved Game present and the Continue option available.\n2) The Player selects Continue.\n3) The Player quickly presses the Xbox Guide button, and the Xbox Guide Blade does not appear for ~3 seconds.\n\nExpected Results:\nThere must be no delay between when the Xbox Guide button is pressed and when the Xbox Guide Blade appears.\n\nGames must ensure that system UI can be rendered at least every 66 milliseconds in all areas of the game for any display mode. This is a violation of TCR 022.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6397,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,8,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Dynasty Training Drills - Fitness Stage 2: There is missing punctuation on the Instructions Screen','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in Dynasty Training Drills, in the Fitness Training Drills, Stage 2, there is missing punctuation that appears on the Instructions Screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Career Mode.\n2) Select Dynasty Training Drills.\n3) Select Fitness.\n4) Select Stage 2.\n5) When the stage appears, observe that the following text appears with missing punctuation:\n\n\".... The problem with the snake bunker is its low profile which makes it extremely difficult to capture....\"\n\nChange to:\n\".... The problem with the snake bunker is its low profile, which makes it extremely difficult to capture....\"\n\nBy adding a \",\"(comma) after \"profile\"\n\nNOTE(1): Text must also be changed in the Help Menu when accessed from the Pause Menu.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6403,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: The camera does not reset from the position it was in, when closing the Your Gear menu and then re-opening it.','Summary: The Players camera does not reset from the position it was in, when closing the Your Gear menu and then re-opening it. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The Player creates a default Player match.\n2) The Player presses LS (Your Gear) button to select gear.\n3) The Player scrolls over to Harnesses.\n4) The Player presses the B (Back) button.\n5) The Player presses the LS (Your Gear) button to select gear again.\n6) The Player observes their camera position is still focused on harnesses.\n\nExpected Results: Camera position must reset to markers after re-opening the gear menu.\n\nNotes:\n1) This issue occurs when selecting any equipment and backing out and re-entering.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6405,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,12,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Menu System - Multiplayer: The Player is unable to select Speedball Marker gear after exiting the Match Lobby of a Woodsball Match.','Summary:\nThe Player is unable to select Speedball Marker gear after exiting the Match Lobby of a Woodsball Match.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer Menu,\n2) The Player selects Player Match.\n3) The Player creates a Woodsball match, any level.\n4) The Player enters the Match Lobby.\n5) The Player presses the LB (Your Gear) button.\n6) The Player selects a Woodsball Marker.\n7) The Hopper, Barrel, and Air Tank become unselectable.\n8) The Player presses the B (back) button to exit.\n9) The Player then creates a default Speedball Match.\n10) The Player enters the Match Lobby.\n11) The Player presses the LB (Your Gear) button.\n12) The Hopper, Barrel, and Air tank remain unselectable.\n\nExpected Results:\nWhen a Player creates a Speedball match, the proper equipment must be selectable.\n\nNotes:\n1) If the Player selects another Speedball Marker, the equipment becomes selectable again.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6406,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,4,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Speedball - Toronto, Ontario: A group of audience members appears to be floating','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, in Toronto, Ontario, a section of audience members appears to be floating above the ground on the left side of the map.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Quick Play,\n2) Select Toronto, Ontario,\n3) When gameplay begins, run over to the left side of the field (towards the gray scoreboard,)\n4) Once in front of the scoreboard, turn to the right and move forward, all the while keeping the mesh netting on the character\'s immediate left,\n5) Pass to the right of two groups of audience members,\n6) Stop next to the second group and turn to the left,\n7) Observe that this group of audience members appears to be floating above the ground.\n\nExpected Results:\nAll audience members must appear properly.\n\nNOTE(1): Screenshot attached.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6407,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Gameplay: User is able to press START and accept the size of the team even though there is not enough or too many players on the field in the team manager between rounds.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, any tournament where the User is able to switch out team mates between rounds, during the team manager, if the User benches all players, observe that the user is able to press the START button and continue into gameplay.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) With a full roster of players (9 players plus user\'s character) start any tournament (Charlotte, North Carolina)\n2) Proceed to the quarter or semi finals\n3) Complete the first round\n4) Between the rounds, the team manager appears\n5) Have all team mates either benched or in play\n6) Observe that the User is able to press START and continue into gameplay\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must not be able to continue into gameplay without having the correct number of players in play.\n\nNOTE(1): May be related to bug 5520','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6409,1225065600,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Career Mode: If the User quits out of Dynasty training mode, enter the Tournament mode and Pauses the match, the training menu will display with the name of the Users last training exercise.','Summary: Gameplay, Single Player, Career Mode, if the User quits out of Dynasty training mode, enter the Tournament mode and Pauses the match, the training menu will display with the name of the Users last training exercise.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Career mode and Dynasty Training Drills.\n2) Engage any type and stage of training.\n3) Before the stage ends Pause the game and select the exit option.\n4) Back out to the main selection screen for Career mode and select Play Tournament.\n5) Select any Tournament, engage gameplay, and at any point in the match press the Pause button.\n7) Observe the Pause menu is that of the Training Menu and has the heading of the last exited Training exercise. \n\nExpected Results: The Pause Menu must display the proper menu for Tournament.\n\nA crash dump of the bug is included in the ftp.\n\nA picture of the bug is included.\n\nNote(1) - If the User selects the Restart option in the match it will restart with no other players on the field and the User unable to move or fire.\n\nNote(2) - If the User selects the Restart option in the breakout manger the game will crash.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6410,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,7,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','TCR 029 - Multiplayer System Link: When the Player disconnects the Ethernet cable during the loading screen, the Player receives 2 disconnect messages','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer System Link, when the Player disconnects the Ethernet cable from the back of the Xbox 360 console during the loading screen into the match, the Player is given two disconnect messages.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Multiplayer System Link Menu,\n2) The Player selects Create Game.\n3) The Player creates a default match.\n4) The Match Lobby appears.\n5) The Player presses the RB (Add Bots) button to add 1 bot.\n6) The Player presses A (start) button to Start the match.\n7) The loading screen appears.\n8) The Player disconnects the Ethernet cable from the back of the Xbox 360 console.\n9) The Player receives the \"Disconnected From System Link\" message.\n10) A loading screen appears.\n11) The Player receives the \"Disconnected From System Link\" message again.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Player must not receive the Disconnect message more than once.\n\nWhen an error prevents a game from performing a task dictated by the player or expected under normal gameplay, the game must display a user-friendly message that addresses the error. The game must transparently handle software errors that are not relevant to gameplay. This is a violation of TCR 029.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6425,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,9,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,3,'(20%-29%)','Occasionally - Collision Detection - Gameplay:The fly-by camera clips into the User\'s Character.','Summary:\nOccasionally, during gameplay, in any level, the User observes that the fly-by camera clips through the User\'s Character at the end of the match when the User wins the match.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select any Game Mode,\n2) Select any level,\n3) Win the match,\n4) Observe, occasionally the flyby camera clips through the User\'s Character at the end of the match. \n\n\nExpected Results:\nThe fly-by camera must not clip through objects.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6428,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: The framerate drops when the cheat meter appears after the Users Character is hit by a paintball.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, any game mode, any level, the User observe the framerate drops to less than 30 frames per second when the cheat meter appears after the Users Character is hit by a paintball.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select any Game Mode,\n2) Select any level,\n3) From the initial match start get hit by a paintball from the other team,\n4) Observe the framerate drops to less than 30 frames per second when the cheat meter appears.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe framerate must not drop below 30 frames per second.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6430,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,1,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Leaderboards: The Career Team Efficiency Leaderboard does not function','Summary:\nThe Career Team Efficiency Leaderboard does not function\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Xbox LIVE Menu, with a Xbox LIVE enabled Gamer Profile signed in.\n2) The Player selects Leaderboards.\n3) The Leaderboards Menu appears.\n4) The Player selects Career Team Efficiency, and no scores are listed. \n\nExpected Results:\nThe Career Team Efficiency Leaderboard must be properly updated with Career stats.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6431,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,1,1,12,4,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Menu/GUI - Multiplayer: The controls for adding and removing bots are not display in the game lobby','Summary: If the User joins a game lobby, the user can press the LB or RB (left or right bumper) buttons to add bots to the lobby, the user can press left and right triggers to remove the bots, no graphic or information is displayed informing the user of this in the game lobby.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a default Player Match game lobby.\n2) Observe no graphic or information, informing the user about the ability to add and remove of bots from the game is displayed \n\nExpected Results: Adding and removing bots controls must be displayed in the mutiplayer game lobby.\n\nNote: This issue also occurs in Local Network.','jhh\ntesting\n','test\n','Fri 14th November 2008 18:03:33 TBog changed:<li>the assignment to TBog</li><br>'),(6432,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: Equipment goes back to default after the match is over.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, if the User selects custom equipment from the lobby and finishes the match the custom equipment does not carry over to the next match.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, select Multiplayer,\n2) Select Xbox LIVE, \n3) Select Ranked Match,\n4) Create a game,\n5) Select custom equipment,\n6) At the end of the Match, quit and select a new match,\n7) Observe the custom equipment selected does not carry over to the next match. \n\nExpected Results:\nAll settings must save between Xbox LIVE matches.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6434,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,4,1224979200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - In gameplay, if the user is running up against a wall, the prompt to perform a dive appears, but the user cannot actually perform the dive.','Summary:\nIn gameplay, if the user is running up against a wall, the prompt to perform a dive appears, but the user cannot actually perform the dive.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter gameplay in any arena.\n2) Using a sprint, run up against the border of the arena, or in Woodsball, run up against a wooden wall.\n3) User observes that the prompt to press X for a dive appears.\n4) Press X button as prompted.\n5) Observe that the user\'s character does not dive despite the prompt appearing on the screen.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe prompt to perform a dive must not appear on screen if the user in fact cannot perform a dive.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6435,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: The camera shakes when the User\'s character jump over a bunker.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in any Multiplayer mode, if the User\'s position the player near a short bunker, \"Press (A) to Jump\" appears, if the User jump over the bunker the camera shakes. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Multiplayer.\n2) Select any mode of play.\n3) Select and enter gameplay in any level.\n4) During gameplay, position the player near a short bunker, press the (A) button to make the player jump over the bunker.\n5) Observes the User\'s camera shakes.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe screen must not shake when the User is jumping over a bunker.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6436,1225152000,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,5,1224633600,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: The camera shakes when the User\'s character slides.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay in any Multiplayer mode, if the User\'s is moving, \"Press (A) to slide\" appears, if the User slides the camera shakes. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu, select Multiplayer.\n2) Select any mode of play.\n3) Select and enter gameplay in any level.\n4) During gameplay, move the User\'s player forward, press the (A) button to make the player slide.\n5) Observes the User\'s camera shakes.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe screen must not shake when the User is sliding.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6437,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,4,1224979200,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Technical Check - Multiplayer: The Ranked Match Game Lobby restrictive text appears for the Client within a Player Match Game Lobby, when that Client accepts an invite from the Play Online menu after backing out of the Ranked Match menu system.','Summary:\nIf the Client receives a game invite from a Player Match game and proceeds to navigate anywhere within the Ranked Match menu system, returns to the Play Online menu, and then accepts the game invite into the Player Match, the Client observes that the Ranked Match Game Lobby text will appear within that Player Match Game Lobby.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 and User 2 are PlayStation Network friends.\n2) From the Main menu, User 1 (HOST) hosts a Multiplayer, PlayStation Network, Player Match game with any settings.\n3) From the Main menu, User 2 (CLIENT) navigates to the Play Online menu.\n4) Within their game lobby, User 1 presses the \"TRIANGLE\" button to bring up the Friends screen.\n5) User 1 proceeds to invite User 2 to their game.\n6) Within the Play Online menu, User 2 observes the game invite.\n7) User 2 selects Ranked Match, there-by entering the Ranked Match menu system.\n8) User 2 then presses the \"CIRCLE\" (Back) button once to return to the Play Online menu.\n9) User 2 presses the \"SQUARE\" button to bring up the Messages XMB screen, and accepts User 1\'s game invite.\n10) User 2 enters User 1\'s game lobby.\n11) User 2 observes the Ranked Match Game Lobby texts, \"Waiting for X More Players\" and \"The game cannot start with uneven teams\", appear within User 1\'s Player Match Game Lobby.\n\nExpected Results:\nRanked Match Game Lobby text must not appear within Player Match Game Lobbies.\n\nNOTE: This only occurs through invites. If the Client was to join the game via the Games List, this bug does not occur.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6442,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,4,1225152000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - NPPL Commanders Cup: There is no final FMV after completing the tournament','Summary: \nDuring Career Mode, NPPL Commanders Cup, there is no final FMV after completing the tournament\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter Career Mode, in NPPL Commanders Cup\n2) Complete the tournament\n3) Observe that there is no final FMV for completing the career mode\n\nExpected Results:\nFMV must play after completing the career mode','jhh\n','[Kyle Kleven (AMP QA Lead) -- 10/30/2008 03:25:53 AM]\nStill occurs in 10/29/08 PS3 build.test\n',''),(6443,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,4,1225152000,0,0,0,3,'(20%-29%)','Occasionally - Video/Graphic - Career Mode - Breakout Planner: The camera view appears to be overlooking a flag station for a brief moment','Summary: \nOccasionally, during Career Mode, before the Breakout Planner, the camera view appears to be overlooking a flag station for a brief moment before entering into the Breakout Planner\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Entered Career Mode\n2) Proceed through the tournaments and into the Breakout Planner\n3) Occasionally, observed that the camera view appears to be overlooking a flag station for a brief moment before entering into the Breakout Planner\n\nExpected Results:\nThe camera view must transition smoothly from the loading screen to the Breakout Planner','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6447,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,4,1225152000,0,0,0,3,'(20%-29%)','Occasionally - Gamplay - Exhibition (Custom Field): Enemy NPC becomes stuck on bunker when attempting to return the flag.','Summary:\nOccasionally, during gameplay on a custom field, when an enemy NPC has the flag and moved back to the NPCs flag station the NPC will became stuck and be unable to return the flag.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Load save with custom field or create the field from the layout photo attached,\n2) Enter the custom field in a 1v1 capture the flag match,\n3) Observe that when the enemy NPC is returning the flag it will become stuck on the bunker closest to its teams flag station, after moving toward the center of the filed from the bunker restricted zone.\n\nExpected Results:\nEnemy NPCs must not become stuck on bunkers when returning the flag.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6448,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,4,1225152000,0,0,0,4,'','Twice - Gameplay - Field Creator: When User entered fly mode in CPC French Open, camera was stuck and would not move around field','Summary: During gameplay, when User entered fly mode in Paris, France or CPC French Open in Field Creator, the camera would not move around the field and was stuck in place. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Selected Field Creator from Main Menu,\n2) Selected CPC French Open,\n3) Removed all bunkers,\n4) Changed bunker color to yellow and black,\n5) Placed several large Hamburger bunkers in top half of field,\n6) Pressed Triangle to enter fly mode,\n7) Observed that camera was stuck in place and L stick would not move camera around field. \n\nExpected Results: Camera must not be stuck during fly mode. \n\nNote: Video footage is Available on the FTP. \n\nNote: This also happened in Nurburgring, Germany with different bunker set up and color scheme.','jhh\n','test\n','<h5>Fri October 31 2008 17:33: bug updated:</h5><li>bug frequency, description, bug class, target, notes</li>'),(6449,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,4,1225152000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - During gameplay, the window of opportunity to jump over a bunker is too short.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, if the user is running at a snake bunker, while holding down L1 to sprint, the prompt to press X button to jump appears and then disappears too quickly for the user to notice it and perform the jump. It becomes too difficult to anticipate when the prompt will appear so the user will run into the bunker instead of jumping over it.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Enter gameplay in any speedball arena.\n2) While sprinting, run toward a snake bunker.\n3) Observe that the prompt to press X button to jump appears and then disappears too quickly for the user to see it and react to it.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe user must be given enough time to see the prompt and react to it.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6450,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,2,3,4,1225152000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Scoring - Results: Round Results show a single Survivor on the Losing Team in Elimination Matches.','Summary:\nResults: Round Results show a single Survivor on the Losing Team in Elimination Matches.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Start any Elimination Match (either in Career Mode Tournaments, Quickplay, or in Exhibition) with more than one Round,\n2) Complete a Round,\n3) Observe the Results Screen shows a single Survivor on the Losing Team.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Results Screen must display the correct scores.\n\nNOTE(1): This bug ONLY occurs on the Round Results Screen. The final Match Results Screen displays the correct number of Survivors.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6451,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,4,1225152000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Crash - Multiplayer: If the Host has a simulated PPPoE connection, and exits the game lobby, when the first of 10 Clients attempting to join the game enters the lobby, the Host observes their game crash on an empty game lobby.','Summary:\nWhile in a Player Match, Game lobby, if the Host has a simulated PPPoE connection, and exits the game lobby, when the first of 10 Clients attempting to join the game enters the lobby, the Host observes their game crash on an empty game lobby.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 Hosts a default Player Match game lobby.\n2) Users 2 - 11 navigate to a default Player Match Games List.\n3) Users observe and highlight User 1\'s game.\n4) Users join User 1\'s game consecutively (one after another).\n5) Immediately after User 1 observes a Client enter the game lobby, User 1 presses the CIRCLE button to access the exit confirm screen and selects \"Yes\".\n6) User 1 observes their game crash on a blank game lobby.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser must not observe the game crash when exiting a game lobby.\n\nNote: The PPPoE setting used for the Host, is set in the Network connection settings menu in the System software screen.\nNote: This issue was reproduced during an at home test, the connection used during the at home test is the following: 6194kbps down / 753 up\nNote: Console did not produce a full crash dump.\nNote: TTY attached.\nNote: Once, a client that attempted to join remained on a loading screen indefinetly.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6452,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,17,3,4,1225152000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Options - If the user sets the music volume to 0, the live-action videos will still play at normal volume.','Summary:\nIf the user goes into Options, Audio, and sets the Music Volume to 0, it is noticed that the music in all of the live-action videos play at its normal volume. NOTE: this also includes the videos that play in Career Mode that play after the user completes a division.\n\n1) On a new profile got to Options, Audio.\n2) Set the Music Volume to 0.\n3) Enter Career Mode for the first time.\n4) Observe that the live-action introduction video of the professional paintball players has normal music volume.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Music Volume that the user sets in Options must be reflected throughout all areas of the game.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6453,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,17,3,4,1225152000,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Options - If the user sets the Master Volume to 0, the live-action videos will still play at normal volume.','Summary:\nIf the user goes into Options, Audio, and sets the Master Volume to 0, it is noticed that the music in all of the live-action videos play at its normal volume. NOTE: this also includes the videos that play in Career Mode that play after the user completes a division.\n\n1) On a new profile got to Options, Audio.\n2) Set the Master Volume to 0.\n3) Enter Career Mode for the first time.\n4) Observe that the live-action introduction video of the professional paintball players has its normal music volume.\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Master Volume that the user sets in Options must be reflected throughout all areas of the game.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6454,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,4,1225152000,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Video/Graphic - Gameplay: Camera clipped through the ground during Autosave after losing a Match.','Summary:\nOnce - Gameplay: Camera clipped through the ground during Autosave after losing a Match.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main Menu, selected Career Mode,\n2) Selected Tournament 16a - Millennium SPL Campaign Cup,\n3) Lost a Preliminary Match,\n4) Pressed the X Button to skip the Opponent\'s Flag run,\n5) Observed Camera clip through the ground during Autosave.\n\nExpected Results:\nCamera must not clip through the ground.\n\nNOTE(1): Screen shot attached.\nNOTE(2): Similar to bug 6281.\nNOTE(3): This problem may occur more often when losing a Match. If the User presses the X Button to skip the Opponent\'s run to grab the User\'s Team\'s Flag, the Camera will focus on the Flag Runner Opponent where that Opponent was positioned when the User pressed the X Button. This enables the final Camera view to be located absolutely anywhere on the course and increases the chances of the Camera being placed under the ground or inside of a bunker.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6455,1225238400,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,4,1225152000,0,0,0,2,'(50%-59%)','Frequently - Crash - Multiplayer: When 14 Clients attempt to join simultaneously to a Host using a simulated connection speed of 1.544 mbps/256KBps, the Host crashes.','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer, when 14 Clients attempt to join simultaneously to a Host using a simulated connection speed of 1.544 mbps/256kbps, the Host crashes in the Game Lobby.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Host using a simulated connection speed of 1.544 mbps/256KBps hosts a default Player Match\n2) 14 Clients join the Host\'s game simultaneously \n3) Frequently the Host crashes in the Game Lobby\n\nExpected Results:\nUsers must not crash.\n\nNOTE: During this bug, the Host encounters severe lag when Client\'s are joining.\nNOTE: Frequently some Clients encounter 45 second loading screens into the Game Lobby.\nNOTE: Crash dump uploaded to the FTP under the following location: /Paintball/AMP QA Bug Captures and Dumps/Crash Dumps/PS3/Paintball_PS3_10.21.08_#6455\nNOTE: 2 TTYs are attached .\nNOTE: The throttled connection is set up using the NEW UI PC tool.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6457,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,4,1225152000,0,0,0,4,'','Twice - Crash - Multiplayer : During 14 player gameplay, one client soft locked on the round results screen with corrupt audio.','Summary:\nDuring ranked or player match multiplayer gameplay with 14 players, one client soft locked on the round results screen with corrupt aduo.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) The host created a default player or ranked match\n2) 13 clients join the match\n3) Gameplay begins\n4) On the first round results screen, one client soft locked on the round results screen with corrupt audio \n\nExpected Results:\nThe game must not soft lock on the round results screen during 14 player gameplay.\n\nNOTE(1): The user will eventually recover and recieve the diconnected from host message. After selecting OK on the message, the client will recieve an infinite load screen when attempting to join a newly hosted match.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6458,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,2,4,1225238400,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Video/Graphic - Multiplayer: One client observed a flashing HUD, and sporadic screen tearing while in a Player Match with 14 users.','Summary: One client observed a flashing HUD, and sporadic screen tearing while in a Player Match with 14 users.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User 1 creates a Default, Player Match.\n2) Users 2-14 join User 1\'s match.\n3) Users begin gameplay.\n4) Once, a client observed their HUD was flashing, and the screen was tearing sporadically. (After the in-game countdown)\n\nExpected Results: Users must not observe video/graphic corruptions.\n\nNOTE(1): This issue occured after the countdown during the first round, and continued throughout the rest of the match.\nNOTE(2): The screen tearing was small, but occured very frequently.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6459,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,4,1225238400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - Career Mode: The Ramping during gameplay does not function properly','Summary:\nThe user is not informed that Ramping is not allowed in Career Mode, and therefore does not function.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Career Mode on the Main Menu\n2) Selects Team Manager\n3) Upgrades the user\'s player\'s Marker Handling skill to level 3 or higher\n4) Selects Play Tournament on the Career menu\n5) Proceeds into gameplay on any level\n6) Pushes the START button to enter the Pause Menu\n7) Selects Options\n8) Selects Gameplay\n9) Sets the Ramping option to ON\n10) Returns to gameplay\n11) Pushes the R1 button or R2 button repeatedly at a fast pace\n12) Notice that the user\'s character is not ramping\n\nExpected Results:\nThe following text must be displayed when \"Ramping\" is highlighted in the Options -> Gameplay menu:\n\n\"Ramping is not available for use in NPPL, XPSL, and Millennium Series tournaments.\"\n\nNote: This change must be applied to the Options -> Gameplay menu on the Main Menu, as well as in Career Mode gameplay.','jhh\n','test\n','<h5>Fri October 31 2008 17:33: bug updated:</h5><li>bug frequency, description, bug class, target, notes</li>'),(6460,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,4,1225238400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Gameplay: Hand appears floating when reloading while wearing both smart parts defender & Quick Grip Glove.','Summary:\nIn game-play, with both the Smart Parts Defender jersey and the Quick Grip Gloves equipped, the user\'s character\'s hand appears floating when reloading hopper.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From Main Menu user selects Career Mode.\n2) Selects Gear Store.\n3) Purchases the Smart Parts Defender jersey and the Quick Grip Gloves.\n4) Exits Gears store and selects Team Outfit.\n5) Equips the Smart Parts Defender jersey and the Quick Grip Gloves.\n6) Enters any mode of game-play.\n7) Reloads hopper.\n8) Observe that the user\'s character\'s hand appears floating.\n\nExpected Results:\nUser\'s character\'s hand must not appear floating.\n\nNote():\nImage attached.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6462,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,4,1225238400,0,0,0,3,'(1%-9%)','Occasionally - Gameplay - Exhibition (Custom Field): If bunkers are arranged with a small gap between bunkers, occasionally AI will pick a path to run that the NPC is unable to fit though.','Summary:\nOccasionally, during gameplay in a an Exhibition Match on a Custom Field, if bunkers are arranged with gaps between them the Enemy NPCs will continue to run at the gap that is too small, and become stuck and unable to retrieve the flag.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) From the Main menu enter the filed creator,\n2) Create a field with many bunkers place just close enough so that the NPCs can not pass though the gap,\n3) Save the field,\n4) Enter the newly created filed in Exhibition Mode,\n5) Occasionally during gameplay the user observed that NPCs became stuck in the gaps because they the AI had picked a path that was to narrow for the NPC to pass through.\n\nExpected Results:\nNPCs must always be able to retrieve the flag.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6464,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,5,3,4,1225238400,0,0,0,5,'','Once - Technical Check - Leaderboards: The Scoreboards did not update after the user completed Career Mode while signed out of the Playstation Network and then signed in after Career was completed','Summary:\nOnce, in the Scoreboard, if the user completed completed Career Mode while signed off of the Playstation Network, signed in after completing Career, the Scoreboards did not update to show the user\'s progress\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User booted the game while signed out of the Playstation Network\n2) Selected Career Mode on the Main Menu\n3) Completed Career Mode\n4) Pushed the Playstation button to open the Playstation XMB\n5) Signed into the Playstation Network\n6) Returned to the Main Menu\n7) Selected Multiplayer\n8) Selected PlayStationNetwork\n9) Selected Scoreboard\n10) Selected the Career scoreboards\n11) Once, the Scoreboards were not updated to reflect the user\'s progress while not signed into the Playstation Network\n\nExpected Results:\nThe Scoreboards must update properly when the user signs into the Playstation Network','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6467,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,6,2,4,1225238400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Crash - Multiplayer: If the user disconnects the network cable from the PS3 just after the Create Room \"Please Wait\" screen, the user crashes on the Create Game screen.','Summary:\nIn Multiplayer, if the user disconnects the network cable from the PS3 just after the Create Room \"Please Wait\" screen, the user crashes on the Create Game screen.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) User selects Multiplayer\n2) Selects Selects Playstation Network\n3) Selects Player Match\n4) Selects create game\n5) Selects any map\n6) Selects continue\n7) User observes the Create Room \"Please Wait\" screen\n8) (Very timing specific) As soon as the Create Room \"Please Wait\" screen disappears, the user disconnects the network cable from the PS3\n9) The user observes a crash on the Create Game screen\n\nExpected Results:\nUsers must not crash.\n\nNOTE: Crash dump is on the FTP.\nNOTE: This bug is VERY timing specific, the user must disconnect the network cable as the Create Game screen flashes after the \"Please Wait\" screen disappears.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6468,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,8,3,4,1225238400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Text - Team Manager: Marker Handling description text contains features not available in Career Mode.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, in the menu system, in the Team Manager, description for Marker Handling levels 3 through 5 displays that Ramping becomes possible.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) Navigate to the main menu.\n2) Select Career Mode.\n3) Select Team Manager.\n4) Increase any team mates Marker Handling skill to level 3 or higher.\n5) Observe that the description text says that \"Ramping becomes possible\".\n\nExpected Results:\nText for Ramping must be removed in the Career Mode Team Manager.\n\nNote(1): Text appears for Marker Handling level 3, 4, and 5.\nNote(2): Ramping is not available in Career mode.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6474,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,4,3,4,1225238400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Video/Graphic - Tournament Selection Screen: In a save with the Career Mode completed Tournaments with Two selections have the wrong corresponding graphic and tournament name','Summary:\nTournament Selection Screen: In a save with the Career Mode completed Tournaments with Two selections have the wrong corresponding graphic and tournament name.\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1) With a Completion save from the Main Menu select Career Mode.\n2) Select Play Tournament.\n3) Proceed to any tournament that has 2 choices.\n4) Notice that the Text lists the second tournament while the title card is for the first tournament.\n\nExpected Results:\nTitle cards must appear with the appropriate Title.\n\nNote: This happens on the following tournaments: \n12 Malaga, Spain Shows Florida Invitational\n16 London, England Shows SoCal Invitational\n19Toulouse, France Shows Texas Invitational\n22 Nurburging, Germany Shows Tempe Invitational\n\nNote: Pressing the Down Button will change the Title Text, while Pressing the Up Button will change the Title Card.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6477,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,3,4,1225238400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - User\'s character is not in his current location if the user presses the PS button right as the user\'s character jumps.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, any level, if the user\'s character goes up to a snake bunker, jumps, immediately user presses the PS button, lets the game sit idle momentarily, notice that the user\'s character is not at his location from when he jumped. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1)Start any match\n2)Move to a snake bunker so that the user\'s character is prompted to jump\n3)Jump and immediately press the PS button\n4)Let the game sit idle momentarily\n5)Press the PS button to resume into gameplay\n6)Notice that the user\'s character is not at his location from when he jumped \n\nExpected Results:\nThe user\'s character must be in his current location when pressing the PS button.\n\nNOTE: It appears as though the user\'s character continues to float from where he had jumped. If the user sits idle in the XMB screen long enough, resumes gameplay, the user\'s character will be hundreds of feet in the air.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6479,1225324800,0,0,0,0,0,0,1,3,2,4,1225238400,0,0,0,1,'(100%)','Gameplay - User\'s character is able to break collistion if the user presses the PS button right as the user\'s character jumps.','Summary:\nDuring gameplay, any level, if the user\'s character goes up to a snake bunker, jumps, immediately user presses the PS button, lets the game sit idle momentarily, notice that the user\'s character is not at his location from when he jumped. \n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1)Start any match\n2)Move to a snake bunker so that the user\'s character is prompted to jump\n3)Press the X button to jump\n4)User\'s character moves towards the bunker and right as he jumps press the PS button to bring up the XMB \n6)Let the game sit idle at the XMB for at least 1 min.\n7)Press the PS button to resume into gameplay\n8)Notice that the user\'s character is outside the level and the user\'s character no longer has collision detection \n\nExpected Results:\nThere must be collision detection at all times.\n\nNOTE: This bug is similar to 6477. If the user does not get this bug to occur, bug 6477 occurs.\nNOTE: This occurs on the following maps; \nSan Diego, CA\nJacksonville, FL\nHuntington Beach, CA\nCharlotte, NC\nMalaga, Spain\nLondon, England\nParis, France\nNurburgring, Germany\nBakersfield, CA\nMiami, FL\n\nNOTE: Video Capture available.','jhh\n','test\n',''),(6480,1227772687,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,1,16,1229904000,0,0,0,12,'asset test','test desc','test notes','','','Thu 27th November 2008 09:58:07 bug inserted in database');
